\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It's about - about five years. Yes. That was a - that was a very small house. Originally I understand from my people there was a -
 a big shepherds hut in Glen Park was eventually taken to the brickyard and stored there and had it - part added to it, you know. But wheels - wheels was actually on the hut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The wheels were still there you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It didn't have foundations then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
You see, it was - very small place and - my grandmother lived in rather a bigger house you know, 'cos she owned the place - originally how they got there was that a Judge Tauton had a runaway horse and my grandfather stopped 
this runaway horse and - Judge Tauton helped him to start a business which they started in lime and making bricks.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's how that business started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's how the business started. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 So you lived in the shepherd's hut for about five years?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About five years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you live after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 North Lee - Boddingtons Lane - it's a big scattered village - you see - I drove down Church Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Ah yes. Oh yes, yes, I do, yes. Oh yes, seen that - yes. Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
'Course then you see there's an east of end of North Lee which is about a mike away. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Of course North Lee Commons, you know the old enclosures act and that went up the big field and about twenty acres I suppose of common land and that's the east end of North Lee. We 
was in the centre of a Lane, Boddington's Lane, that runs down through the centre, so we were rather isolated away from other people. I suppose nearest house was about - two hundred yards away and then the rest was quarter of a mile away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The church was how far away from you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh about a mile - about a mile, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To the east did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well from east - leading to the north - north end of the village see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you lived in Boddingtons Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Boddingtons Lane, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did you live in that house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I would think about - let me see if I - about twelve year. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After you went from there you were about seventeen years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, well you see I per - yes, my family - I would say yes but of c
ourse - from Boddingtons Lane I left there when I was about - eleven and half because I went to Freeland with to live with my granny because she was an old lady and she was isolated in a little old - I dread to think of it - it was very small little place
 
you know and - I'd - someone had to be with her and so I lived with granny, just a small house but - and a room was partitioned off as a - I remember a curtain you know with a - I lived - I slept in a section here maybe and granny over that side. Now if I
 
could - digress for a moment from that I - I always remember the old lady with long prayers you know - pray - praying aloud you know and - object poverty you know she lived - it was struggle for existence and she used to talk quite a lot - I must go down 
t
o a - Watts' and get my butter - I'd better go tonight and - jovial old lady you know but - always full of this idea that she must do next. And she was supplemented I think by sisters of Mercy from the church, Freeland, you know, bringing little drops of 
soup. They used to come. And I used to - in the morning - go to - Tautons to - go to Tautons to clean the knives and forks as a supplement to paying for - while I was with granny which I had a sum of eighteen pence a week, you see. It used to help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
Tauntons was a - were people of - of means - of rather - were at the time because Judge Taunton I think was the father of these two daughters.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The Judge Taunton you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And I think they lost their money but they - they lived in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 genteel}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 way and people of the tremendous - utmost sincerity you see which I think - reflecting back was tragic in it's consequences because they abhorred the chapel people you know and as they visited my grandmother they used to tell her to - sh
e would be shut out of heaven if she didn't come to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She was chapel was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She was chapel, yes. Oh yes, yes. I'm speaking of Freeland now. Yes. Yes, yes. Oh yes, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your granny went to the one in Freeland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Freeland, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What denomination chapel was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think it was - Methodist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And it was this Judge Taunton's house that you went to clean the knives and forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. Well it was two Miss Taunton's then - the daughters you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What relation were they to the Judge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I think they were - were daughters, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And it was the Judge whose horse your father had caught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 My grandfather. Yes, yes, yes. Yes, that goes back - yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
So it - I can't - difficulty in regar
d to the historical history of - of Breakspeares, the late Bishop Tregarth who used to be rector of St Allits - had a long conversation with him about it and - Breakspeares go back in history quite a lot and I - you probably know that the only English was
 a Breakspeare. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh - that'd be Nicholas Breakspeare, I think he was born at Langley. Yes. So it's - and - the Breakspeares have a - what do you call it - a heraldry is it. Coat of Arms. Yes. Yes. Now what Breakspeare it was I would not know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you moved to your granny your family were still living in North Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In North Lee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And they lived on there for a while - where did they move after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They - they - my father bought a house at the top of the hill in North Lee and - five acre 
field and a one acre field, he came in for money when his mother died, and I always remember my father and mother counting golden sovereigns on the table which was quite a pile, you know, and - of course their conversation was dealing on debts that they m
ust pay up and - it was quite a big item really because there was so much owing to grocers and butchers and - that was thing - that they settled and of course as I say they bought the house in North Lee and we settled down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did you stay then in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - we stayed in that house - 'til - after the war - after the first world war because as I - we grew up we entered into the Army - there was seven of us went into the Army and my mother and father then was left - father was in
 reasonable health but mother was just - a week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
And - being in the Army, seven of us - my mother died through - I think it was probably ill health and shock, because - my brother - the one over there - came over from Canada and joined up in the Army and I
 was reported missing - just empty, void and destitute of ideas because my father then had allowed himself to drift into a - a way of life which - was really abhorrent that he had sisters in good positions - my - his sister at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 , Slatters - have you heard of Slatters garage they have there - oh yes, they're quite a big business you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And so he used to wander away down to his sister's but when we came - when we came - when - when I came him from service after four and a half years of the world wa
r - he was in a terrific - terrible condition you know and I was suffering then from the after effects of war and I had a complete breakdown - I - the completion of war service and the first examination I was sent away to hospital. I got shell shock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember what year that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well it - the end of the war from - from the service - first examination, straight into hospital. But of course I had malaria and I suffered a lot from dysentery and - as I say shell shock which affected my memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did the family move from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  to North Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh just simply because of - of space - of family you see. We shifted into this house - which was a big house. I think it was a - a - a tremendous big barn at one time for the farms you know.
 And eventually made into a - places here one could - won't say live - exist because - in that sense it was a big house - roomy place, stones laid as - as you might say, pavements on the footpath but covered with coconut matting. The fireplace was one wit
h
 a beam - with a - iron right across I suppose on a chain hanging down which my mother had a huge saucepan - pot we called it - she could hand there and kindle the fire you know and cooking for eleven or twelve you can imagine is to have a - a net - was c
alled a net - put these potatoes in, you know, there was this big - basin, what we called on a Sunday make the gravy one - a gravy pudding. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
I can always putting this - and me cutting it up and dropping salt and pepper an pouring the water on and do it - wit
h a big cloth you know, turning this thing round - dropping it into the pot - dropping the potatoes in it - at the appropriate time and cabbage - green stuff - that was put in loose you know and it was a terrific battle to keep the fire going to - I don't
 know - and it was cooked properly, then I nipped in - we were all ravenous you know - the table, we used to gather round you know and - eager to get dug in.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So the meat pudding was tied up in a cloth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And put in the pot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 With the other vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's true, yes, all done - under one heading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was in the kitchen that this was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, that was in the house you see because I mean to say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was all one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 All one room. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was this house just one room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The barn hadn't been partitioned off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
Only - as a draught protector say leading into the kitchen there so - a boarding along here so far - screen we called it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 One entered the doorway a
nd, you know - came in - and of course it was big barren place really. Cold - very cold - void I would say and destitute of ideas. It was just somewhere where you assembled and you continued your existence but we learnt to live with things of that sort be
cause we didn't know different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you all have to sleep in that one room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. I think we had two rooms upstairs. What we called the garret - you went up steps up to another room but the smaller children slept in the same room as mum and da
d. And I remember four of us sleeping on one bed. Three - there and two that way. And it was a terrific it was because I - we used to - clothes used to come off - I don't think we found - really knew what it was to be really cold in that time in life. I s
uppose we were cold we - but - I think it was question that we got tolerated - to conditions you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you go to bed in your clothes then to keep warm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No - oh no, we just in a shirt. "Course we never had anything different at that time of day. We didn't have - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you first moved there you would have been about five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you sleep then in the same part as your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were five you had a brother of about three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And there was another little brother born two or three years after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 When did you move out of your parents' room into the other room?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I suppose that was about - probably be about six or seven. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then you moved in with the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 With - with older boys up in the garret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many beds were there in that garret room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well there was a - two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Four of you in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And the rest - upstairs. We slept - we slept between four - I wouldn't be positive -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So there were two beds in the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where was the room your parents slept in - was that another garret room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - no, just this - ground floor - this was the next room - steps leading up into the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Three storeys really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well yes, that house - and the first room - living - bedroom and a second one - at the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So downstairs there was simply this large room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In which all the living activities had to go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 True. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No scullery or wash house or anything of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well there was a little place at the back where - we used to keep - have a bowl, you know, and - and wash but a
t that time you see insofar - as this - as hygiene - hygienic things went, it was no question of having a bath. One never done that sort of thing - I question whether that happened in - in village life. One washed and was extremely clean in regard to the 
arms and neck and - but otherwise no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Of course people had no running water and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Mater of fact we had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 yoke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - you've seen these old fashioned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 yokes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 with - well we used - I used to go to a field - to a field which was about
 two hundred yards to this well in a field and it was lovely water. The well we had was very deep and - the water wasn't good to drink so we always went down this field - there was always a question of who got the water supply in. In the cold weather - re
member when I was quite a little kid going down this field with this yoke struggling to bring this water back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have to take it in turns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well no, it just de - it just simply depended who was available that time you see. My mother you see
 - did the washing - taking her - we call it oval shed the back-there was a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 copper}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 thing in there and she used to - plunge - you know, quite a lot of washing to do - and a long, long clothes line used to - you know - and it was terrific. 'Course the
re's no rinsing or - she just simply used to drip from the line and hang it down - see and - it was a continuous battle of regards to cleanliness - that respect. And my mother's health was - very - well it was had. I can always remember my mother - when s
he come down stairs she used to lean against a screen and - she - I suppose it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 indigestion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 - people at that time said it was roaring wind - you know, you're stomach make - and - she used to cry a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 She was probably weak from having so many children?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I think that was it you see. And - well one time she went away for about two months and she came back and in the meantime me -one of my brothers went to a farm - not far away. We lived with this farmer and his wife for that period of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 All of you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, only two of us. In the family. Then the others roughed it. By that I mean, well - rough life you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I would be about nine then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long was your mother away for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About three months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did she go - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I - no, I know we went to the convalescent home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because her health was so poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. Yes. And of course mother's always deny themselves the necessities of life which she readily did. A
nd my father - of course he had a wage from his own people - I think he had about fourteen shillings a week. Well unemployment then was chronic and my elder brothers was out of work a good deal of the time and it was always a question of - what shall we d
o
 next, so what can we do. And so - my brothers - when they were about eighteen - in the springtime went up the country as they used to call it then - hoeing and fagging, what they call fagging, round the fields so that the binders could go round and they'
d
 sleep rough, in the barn you know, and - they'd say well Jesse has gone off down the country. My mother wouldn't know where he was going - or wouldn't know properly if he came - 'cos there was no question of working, take it for granted that he just wand
ered of you see, so that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So how far a field might he go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Say about - twenty mile out. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Wouldn't she see him then for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no. And she didn't see him - he went off - he went - made his - made way down to Yorkshire. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In search of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
In search - yes. And he got down to Yorkshire and he got in a stone quarry - granite - quarry and he worked there for a long time and then eventually sent for his brother, Percy. And Percy wander
ed away down there. Tramped - down there you see and - he lived down there for - or - just - time he'd been away down there. And - he was a rather amusing character was Jesse because he - he - would do things so unusual, in the sense that I remember my br
other Tammy, Percy, he was at a Salvation Army meeting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
who'll be saved - who'll be saved? And Jesse shouted, Jesse Breakspeare. Just for one pint and then he shot away. My brother followed him you know, to a public house and he had a drink there. He was
 that type of fellow. And - in Northleigh there - he was in debt to different people - and he'd read a list out aloud who he owed money to. And he would eventually pay them up when he got work. And - then later on he went to Canada but - an immigration sc
heme which was run by a man named Turner who used to run a Twill - a sports outfit in Twill Street and - so he went to Canada and when he came back in the first world war he went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 Witney}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and paid the debts which he - which had come - to which he owed that time and paid - and they didn't know any thing about it. They'd forgot all about it - been paid up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you have any idea how old your father was when you were born? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 
Or did you know the year he was born himself?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know how old he was when he passed away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think he was about sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know what year that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No I'm afraid my memory's not - no. It's in the churchyard of course - there's a tombstone up but it - let me see - well I came out of the Army - it'll be about - about - eight years after the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, the first world war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So it would be about 1926 - you'd be married a couple of years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. That - that he about right, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about your mother - do you know anything about her age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16326247\charrsid5840491 I would think my mother would be about - about fifty-four I think - yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't know what year that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that after you came out of the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, she died when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She died when she got that awful shock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes, she died - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So she died sometime during those war years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you said she had this awful shock and your father sort of went to pieces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I wasn't quite sure whether perhaps her mind was unsettled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No, she - she was quite remarkable woman and - I would say very intelligent in - in regard to - to life - in the sense that if she met someone of - of education she'd perhaps be -
 ponder - and say well - can't you see I can't follow you - up the steps. Say, you're a person - or mentally you - you - in conversation would say can't you see that you're a person - of great possibilities. She would never understand in that sense - and 
yet she was most intelligent in her way of life and reading the book of life. See. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So when she died it was during that first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where was your father's own village - where had he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - yes, he was born in - he was born at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 . Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 His occupation - he worked in this brickworks you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What exactly did he do in the brickworks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - he - he was the man that - that run the lime kiln - to burn the lime and to see it come to - which was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 skilful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 business 'cos it was a question of sitting up at nights to watch it burn through in the making of - of bricks and of drainage pipes, and of looking after the men who work in the yard - pudding the clay which they did wit
h their bare feet on boards - they'd run along and they'd get quite - soluble and - then eventually put it into the shaping - completion of the brick in it's raw state and then finally going to the lime kiln. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And he was in charge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was in charge - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many men worked there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About - I would say there would be about five men in the yard. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was your father getting the most pay of them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, I - suppose his money would be about fifteen shillings but the rest would be about eleven - twelve shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anybody sort of over your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was his own concern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - oh, his mother's concern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was your mother's family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was my grandmother's family. Grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That grandfather was your mother's side of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had your father had another job before he worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, he - always - yes, worked with the family, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he continue that all his life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, when - when - when his mother died - and of course we bought this - he bought this house in the village - and - he probably - just simply - lived on - doing odd jobs but he was never put out to do work for other people. With - m
y brothers persuaded him to - to get a farm. And he said no, he wouldn't do that. He said, I've worked hard all my life and you must learn to work but I'm going to take life easy now, which he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And those acres attached to that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did they do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well we bought some cattle - about three - and then we bought pigs and - that was on a very small way which really wasn't very profitable but it was a crude way of doing things. My father was very gifted in the sense of
 persuading and telling other people what to do but he seldom did it himself. He was quite a - an intelligent man. Had a reasonable education from his mother you see but - I think - that he was - very thoughtful man in conversation we had as children we w
ere adding up or calculating different things, not very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 skilful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 in arithmetic - he did it straight away in his - you know. I think he lived in a sphere away from us because he was really quite - intelligent man. I think it had often - applied with the - peo
ple at that time. You see, moving in steps in the sense that you - interviewing me and you say, yes, right, but I'll go up that step and I'm sure he can follow. And you go up one more and you say, no. It's impossible - he doesn't follow me, so you come ba
c
k and you're working on the same level - that I'm working on you see. I think that was a trend - in that - in that time. But the common people, we - we just simply conversed in a crude type of way and we understood it - one another but on the other hand, 
y
ou see, brains was - worked on different levels. I always remember a clergyman there who lived there for forty years, he lived as a recluse most of that time, as a boy he was interested in antique - my father had a three legged cot and I remember the vica
r
 saying to me - in a very gruff voice - now William junior, I want to see William senior, I want that three legged cot. And my father I remember that time was - at work. And he was asking me what I would do for a living when I grew up. And I told him I di
d
n't know. And - he said, what are you reading? I said, well I want to read - learn to - I want something that I can learn to read properly and understand. Well - he - never buy a book, he said, on the art of reading. Get the leader of any newspaper and th
e
 editor has wrote that and it's brought - brief and concise and therefore, he said, you've got the mastery of everything. It doesn't matter if you're in - not interested in the subject, but the art of - reading he says, you - you've got it. Now if I go on
 
to speak about this clergyman, he was there for forty years. He lived there - for himself - he accumulated antiques - terrific houseful of it I suppose - he always went about in winter and summer with an umbrella, and this is no exaggeration because I wan
t
 to be very truthful on all these things, we could walk behind and - we could have made marks on the umbrella with the dust that accumulated on this umbrella and - in - entering the pulpit or reading the lessons he could go through the Bible almost withou
t
 looking at the book, and go through most of the services. And in the pulpit he never had any notes whatever. And I can remember as a boy him preaching about - aeroplanes that would be in the sky and things that would be in the sky - when I was quite a - 
a
 youngster about eleven years of age. If I go on in - as far as he was concerned - the ranks he - rank of - tied land to the - land that belonged to the church - he was going round collecting rent and when I - he wanted to go to a house he - would I accom
p
any him because - this Mr. Porter had a ferocious dog - he was bent on collecting this money you see and when he died - he preached on the last Sunday and my Uncle found him on the vicarage on the Wednesday - they hadn't seen him, or heard from him - and 
h
e was dead. And he was on an old long sofa which was dropped into the floor. He never used upstairs room in the vicarage, and he'd left the cobwebs hanging down from the ceiling which he used to walk in between. And - of course he had two relatives - two 
n
ephews - came in for money. I think he had - was worth about eighty thousand pound. He'd lived a life which - the village - he entered there as a - must have been at an early age and environment was such - and - things became - as he see life - so - it be
c
ame so habitual to him that - habits became more or less characteristic of the man. Although man of such brilliance - of - for education - well it's very difficult to understand how it could have happened that way but the books - they had bonfires - my Un
cle - and my brothers accumulated these books and took them outside and burnt them - to this bonfire - and books of great value.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did they burn them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I don't know. How one book I had was - of course - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 ecclesiastical}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Polity and Doctor Joh
nson's Reply. You ever read that book? It starts of with something - few men there are who public evils do not readily espy, but fewer still who will wait - who with patience and talk with work for the common good - they wish well but hope that it would b
e
 none of them. But hoped it would rather be none of them. They'd rather sit on the wall and watch the - world go by, hoping things would go by. It wrote in quaint language and I - I read it but, you see, during the war my wife got rid of some of my books.
 She got rid of that. And I was talking to a cl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 ergyman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you when you took that book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well this was after war when my brother gave it to - lent it to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 Was he Vicar or Rector?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he die before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After it. He had a - he had a - a male child - preserved in spirits in a jar -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did he have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well he got - well heaven knows where he got it from - but one of my - one of my cousins who 
lived a life as a poacher, not - not of necessity, but he enjoyed this life of catching rabbits and that sort of thing, had one of these big pockets you know and he'd take them to a public house. Carry it about with him. You know, to show people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it a child that had been born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Born. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not a foetus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It wouldn't have been - no, not - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 , it was a stillborn child I suppose, yes. But it was a male child. But - yes - but this - but this clergyman used to - this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 Reverend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 Scott - I remember an old antique bookshop - opened to an old man - I forget his name now - he lived in that passage where picture palace is, goes down into Dorset Green. Used to be a bookshop down there. He - yes - he says, I remember it,
 he used to come into my place, he said, I remember the old gentleman well. But he used to come in with a carrier - used to come in with a carrier - a cart - with a - what shall I say - a van type of thing and he used to ride in there and - of course he'd
 make a collection of anything that he could get hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did nobody come in and clean in his house then or housekeep for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Only my Uncle I suppose or his daughter. But he never let into the room - only just outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did your uncle go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, my uncle you see, was in the lime business too and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was he your mother's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, he was a relation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Uncle Briggs - uncle Ted Briggs, yes. He - he was a - lived in a little cottage adjoining 
the vicarage, see, and so they were never allowed into the old man's room. He kept that - that was why you see his father - he preached on a Sunday and found on the Wednesday - was a story which is very difficult to see because - my uncle, he went about -
 six months afterwards went away to Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your father really gave up the lime works did he after he came into that money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What happened to the business then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 Well - that died - from Long Hanborough we had a business - a public house called the Shepherd's Halt. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That business was then carried on by his relatives in the centre of village. He went down church way and past the church and down the bottom there was a - a - a little way up the hill was a lime kiln see there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You can still see rubble and things there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Well you see they had to enter that - the cousin - the relative took on then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After your father left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 These little old jobs he used to do - what sort of jobs were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well it was a question of - of - on allotments you know or doing things for - on Eynsham Hall Estate. Oh yes, he was on Eynsham Hall Estate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you mean gardening or farming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Farm work and - and upholstery. Oh yes, in upholstery he was there for some time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would he get regular money for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, he would do. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said he never worked for anybody but himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I was wrong. He did work for a time at Eynsham Hall. Yes. On this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 
forestry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 work - with the keepers you know, and he would sit up at night with a young pheasants - keep the foxes away. And they would - they have batteries of hens you know - hens to sit on the - pheasants eggs and - surrounded by - cork which wa
s - with tar on - keep the foxes away and they'd make terrific noise at night, you know, frighten - foxes away. He did that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was after he gave up the lime kiln?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, yes. I think it would be for about two years did that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And after those two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After those two years I say he did odd jobs. Yes. I think it was more to find something to occupy his time. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about money - didn't he need the money - did he have enough for what he wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, I - I think as time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 went}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  on he - he probably got short of money but his sisters, you see, had two sisters, and one as I say was a - in a - in the - bus - business, you see. Slatters - at Handbury, yes, quite a big concern there you see. 
And - so he was supplemented in that way. Just managed to carry on. But he was very - unkempt in his make up although very clean - never used a razor - scissors you know and sort of trim up sort of business you know - that sort of thing, and - as time - y
ears went on - it got more and more that way. He smoked a clay pipe. And took a pride in what they call colouring a clay pipe. Gradually he used to work up into - half way up you know, and he smoked rather a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What do - you mean when you say colouring a clay pipe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Making - well - the continually smoking, from the bottom of the pipe - bowl of the pipe - would colour up - to a dark shade you know. And you work up evenly and smoothly 'til it got about half way up the pipe. But - those people then, th
ey - if they broke a pipe - clay pipe - you've seen those clay pipes have you? Yes. No, but the stem break off and they still smoke it 'til it was very short. And he used to smoke one very short and - later on he developed cancer of the throat. And that w
as - I think was just continually - yes, I think so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 My - mother came from Freeland. yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had she had a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, that I can't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I think she must have married rather early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have any other relations living with you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Just your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 True. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And no lodgers ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No lodgers, no lodgers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It wasn't really a house for lodging was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother ever give any money to anybody to help her with any of the cleaning or housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not even for any little jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She always did the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother make the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. She made - made our little clothes you know, yes, and little coats out of old - dresses or anything - had a remarkable way of doing that, I don't know how it was done, but it was done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did she get the material from - these dresses then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I - that'd be difficult to say. May be from relatives - I would think so. Any old coat that was in the - she'd dismantle and make up into little trousers and put the little buttons on. I remember the 
first time my mother making me - getting me ready for school and the first day of going to school my two brothers that took me dismantled me of my trouser buttons - cut little holes in my trousers - and pull the brace through and put little - little stick
s in so that they could play buttons at school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When did they do this - did your mother know they'd done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When I got home, yes. When I got home what had happened. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did she say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well as all mothers say you know - it was quite a - a thing, you see, because - they did the - they did the same thing at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They took these buttons off when you got to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember her buying any material?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father do anything in the way of sewing or making clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother ever buy any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 second-hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  or new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She'd probably buy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5968627\charrsid5840491 second-hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  clothes. But - I don't think - that was very easy to do because we lived i
n an isolated place and for mother to go - a distance would be out of the way. So I don't think it was a question of - of - it was a question of making up - I do remember my - the first little suit I ever had was corduroy thing and you could smell it a mi
l
e away. You now, and I remember wearing it for the first time on a Sunday and parading in this lane - no one about - but I hoped I would he seen - with this little suit on, you know and I - I can always - always remember that. It was just - terrific thing
 because I'd never been dressed in that way before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And had she made that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, that - what she'd actually bought. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she bought it new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, she bought that new. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember her buying any other new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember her mending clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, yes, because - it - all times at school - we would get a rip you know, here and - I can always remember - coming home - my - my - my trousers torn out again. She'd say, oh come 
here - and I lay across my mother's knees and she'd do the stitching in - you know, where it was torn. Yes. Because - that time - at school we had a saying - if your shirt was hanging out a little bit, they'd shout, diddy, giddy gout, shirt's hanging out,
 one yard in and one yard out, so that you'd stand against a wall rather than - and once you did that they'd realize that there was something - they'd dig you out of it, you know, that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How do you mean you'd stand against the wall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well because you'd hide it - you see. Because of the shirt hanging out of it you know, and they would pull it more. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother or father mend shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do if the boots or shoes needed repairing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - what ha
ppened was we - we - we made do and mend in the sense that I would have my elder brother's on - although they wouldn't fit bit if - for one - which - it was a question of just walking along - laces - if you laced them up they were loose. And I've gone to 
school many a time with boots far too - size too big. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't remember them being mended then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your father doing any mending of clothes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. He wouldn't - he wasn't of that make up. Fat
her wasn't that make up at all, he was quite incapable of - of - of doing things of that sort. He probably would have done 'cos he was a very energetic man - very busy man - very quick in movement. He was - he never wore - my father never wore any socks -
 
he never wore any socks. He would came home, I can remember now, and emptying his - emptying his shoes - boots rather - tipping them - any little segment that gathered there and then - gathered a few embers from the fire into this - into this and skake up
 and down to dry out - and - then get a little bit of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 hay}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 and put in the bottoms of the shoes - maybe a little bit of rag - but hay generally - and then they'd be ready for the morning. I had a brother - he never wore any socks - and he would be about eight
y-four now - he doesn't wear socks today. Never has wore socks. My father was very, very fast walker. He never - if he stopped to light his pipe he would run a distance to make up for that - for that time, you know what I mean. Full of go so that he never
 
suffered in consequence for not wearing socks. Why he didn't wear them I do not know. My brother, Frank - he doesn't wear - he never did wear socks. I - I had an uncle - who never wore socks. He was about six foot three - giant of a man - very long in the
 
body, very short in the legs, of terrific powers and strength, he never foundered the cold, never foundered the heat. Go about - near naked with a ruffled coat on and sleeves way up here. No - never done his boots up. They used to lap over - you know, and
 
he used to come into Oxford with lime - with horse and cart - money - he'd carry money about with him in his pocket - probably have a hundred pound. But he lived that type of life - a rough, hard life and I used to say Uncle Alf, you must find the cold. N
o boy, I don't find the cold and don't find the heat. In the winter - would stones - his hands would he wet and nasty and rough and raw but - no. Never worried one little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember when your mother would buy - you only remember the one suit she bought don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it for a special occasion or anything that she bought that suit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I suppose it was just the time - when - I was going to Freeland church. She was very keen about me - living that - leading a good li
fe, you know and - of course Northleigh church was - what it was and my mother had been brought up at Freeland and being a - a person of - of religious ideas - rather high church - Freeland church was rather keen to get me there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 And - puzzling thing reall
y is so far as I - think back with my mother leading a life and reading the Bible - never getting - life - as she was entitled to in bringing up a family - and sending seven men into to serve the country, never had any reward, not all the way through in s
pite of all her prayers that was offered and given. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, no recognition. And therefore I'm perfectly bewildered to - wonder why she hung on to a faith which was never realized. Always praying that something would happen, you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 know}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  which never did happen. And 
- my father - mother's distress and he'd got a wonderful way of - of getting what he wanted was to be - it'd be a question of threepence he'penny. That would be tuppence for a pint of beer and threeha'pence for a half ounce of tobacco. And it - my mother'
s
 name was Mary, he always called her Polly. There Polly, who do you think I've met today? This was a preliminary to getting this threepence ha'penny. Tell a fairy tale you know. Then eventually come out - well come on, because I've got to be off quick you
 
know, what I want. Yes, I know what you want but I - you can't have it. And this - argument probably go on for a few minutes 'til eventually my mother would sacrifice the threepence ha'penny. And I can always see my father making a dash away down - you kn
o
w - to get to the public house to get his pint of beer, his half ounce of tobacco. Of course, in regard to matches, when he got there in a public house you always found a little stand here with matches in. You'd take one out loose and - you know - and - t
he clay pipe, if you wanted one, that was available. And of course I - I - now I do remember often - as soon as my father was - gone - my mother got into tears, you know. It was sad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because she was very short of money I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, desperately
 short you see. And - the grocer - we used to have it come in once a month you know, they used to come in from Witney and - he'd come in and he'd have a list and he knew the list of my mother - monthly you know. He'd start rattling away and mum says, you 
s
top a minute - you wait a minute. I can't - I think it was a - forty pound of sugar and - so much tea and so much this, that and the other you know, then she'd deliver this - mother could pay off a little sum and of course - it was a question of - of her 
p
aying off. But - you know - it's always - mothers' always - and so it's harder and most honest people what's striving always to keep on the level and keep straight. They believed in that you see. And they believed in their betters - they believed in peopl
e - they know best and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The people with money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They looked up to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, oh yes. Such as Squire Mason and people of - in the village with the - with money you see and position, which I - even at the most early age I ca
me in contact with the - an agnostic - and - I suppose I would be about eleven then and do you know I - I was positively bewildered because all the things I'd learnt about hell fire and I believed in it - I believed in torture and that sort of thing for w
i
ckedness and all that - suddenly I came in contact with this man and he was telling me different things and he said, whatever you do, boy, when you leave school - never sell your labour cheaply because that's only thing you have. And always learn to be - 
t
o be kind and good and I - this man persuaded me to see life in a different way and - and now - from then onwards I thought out what a kind of man he was - I - that'd talk to children in the village and catch hold of their hands and play with them and tha
t
 was a thing I'd never seen before with people that was - supposed to be leading a life which was - was real - unchristian like. And then from then onwards I began to query and puzzle what had happened to life in - in a Christian way. So I said then that 
I
 would - believe in some things but I could really understand. And I only understood this man. And - I - living in contact with him - lent me - or rather - I had suppressed emotions you know, and this thing gradually built up within me and as I read - new
spapers and things I began to see things in a different light and - before I left school I would not sing the rich man in his castle, the poor man at his gate, God made him high and mighty, and all of their estate. I would not sing that - at an early age.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was very young to question your upbringing and life wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who was this man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 A man named Organ. He used to live in Oxford.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he do in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was the shoemaker. He was shoemaker. And he was
 one of those men which I remember now - stands out - a most honest and truthful man. Living a life which was a climb above those which was - professing a - a Christian faith. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old would you have been when you first started talking to this man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About eleven. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where was it you used to talk to him and see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 
Well - what I call the village well - what we called the village well when we went to this well to get out water - we had a - one of those things with a little coin and you drop it down and fill it up you know, and he said, that's too heavy for you boy. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I said, no, I said, I've been used to it. Well, he says, let me do it - and he pulled it up. And then I got in conversation with him. And - he said, how old are you? And 
I told him. And - he said, well, he said, you could do well in the world, he said, but you - he says, you'll have to learn to - never sell your labour easily or cheaply, because that's the only thing you have. Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he talk to the other children about these things do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. I don't think so. No. Then suddenly I realized that I was - seeing something in a different light and away from my parents and there - after that, moving about as I did - I would - if I could get 
any 1 on a farm, secrete an egg or - what we commonly call pinch one - for my mother, I would do so. Now, we kept a few hens and it was the hens - mum, here's an egg I've got for you. Look, I said, I didn't think they'd - I thought they'd stopped laying n
o
w. I would tell her all manner of lies because I thought it was a greater truth to do a thing of that - it's not the written word - I don't think it's the word that one tells literally, I think it's a life that probably one - one lives and so what I call 
- which considered lies I considered to be a truth then at that early age. I would do - my mother would never, never had - thinks I'd brought eggs or anything like that if she'd have known but she would have it belonged to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you did this under the influence of this man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he lend you books to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think I read many books at that early age, I think I read comics. Dreadful books some of them. Oh yes, I think some of the comics at that day was - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he talk to you about theories - did he talk about socialism and capitalism and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. But - I think - I - unconsciously I was following a trend then in a way to - to be - more of the soapbox type you know and bein
g against people in position. I would ignore them - I would not salute them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you'd been brought up to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. I'd been brought up to salute them and to respect and honour and obey in every respect. This sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say you would not salute them, under his influence you stopped doing so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I did stop doing so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was said about this - did anybody say anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, my schoolmaster. I would at that - one man I did salute and his wife. We did that at 
school and I - even at that early age I thought it was the right thing to do. But otherwise I would not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Only your schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Only my schoolmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who can you remember that you stopped saluting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The - the Masons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they say anything about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I suppose not because I - they - they understood really - in ignorance I suppose they imagined it to be. Oh yes. Yes. But - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Most people always went on doing what they'd been brought up to do didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh 
yes, yes, but I - you see, no - in the village you would never see a man on - on the allotment on a Sunday or digging his garden only to dig a few spuds - potatoes for - for necessary for the dinner, but not to go and - oh no, that was very wicked, and ev
e
n then - that never went to church would do - wouldn't do things of that sort. And - you see, and although very few people went to church in Northleigh, he perhaps half a dozen that - the men of the village was keen bell ringers, a peal of six balls there
,
 and they would go in their working clothes Sunday mornings and Sunday nights and you'd see then with their old rough mufflers on - old rough corduroy trousers on and they would ring the peal of bells. Then they'd come down and they'd leave the church - n
ever stopped to church. Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father go to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 My father - yes, he went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he do the bell ringing too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, my father didn't. No. My brothers did. My father would - my father would use ordinary swea
r words you know, but he never used any very rough words. Kneel down and pray at night, same as my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they pray out loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not my mother or father, but they would pray - my mother would be longer in prayer. The same as my granny woul
d probably carry on for five minutes - in prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your granny would pray silently or out loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Out loud. Out loud. Yes. Marvellous it was. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 
And - yes, because you see - I would do - he munching an apple which I'd been - pinched, you know, whe
n I come home that night, in the compartment, listen to granny praying and I - w - very, very interested in granny because she would - she would do this sort of thing and believe in it in - with all sincerity. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You see, I think it was a mistake in this - th
is - I suppose it was a question of necessity than a need of something which never came. Away then through the years, always hoping against hope that this would happen. The crux of the whole matter was that - people - of the ordinary person never got anyt
h
ing to get out of the - out of the life that they were in. They were always hoping it would come gradually - I believe personally in revolution - the only way things could happen would be in a revolutionary way. You se, because, the utmost sincerity of pe
o
ple, and I believe that they were sincere, that their way of life was the proper way - and it was a - was hopeless to the mass of - of potential qualities of life when I went to school or possibilities of a doctor of a lawyer or solicitor was there in the
 very school I went. With - with the possibility of education but education was crude. I left school when I was twelve and a half you see and want work. And what I learnt at school is practically negligible. Nothing. I don't - if it's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you get this idea or revolution - was it from this Mr. Organ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Unconsciously it may have been his influence which led up to it you see. Because I suppose the way of talk then and the habits that I accrued from that became - more or less - formed into char
acter you know - and became more or less characteristic in me. Even some of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. Father - father was a man as I say that was a tremendous amount of energy but a way of 
life was - out of the way. But mother would be extremely busy washing in the shed and - he'd tap - tap - tap at the table - so mother come eventually come along, you know very well I've got to get that. Well it's only just a question of pouring - pouring 
him a cup of tea out. But mother - but mother had to do that. She had to do that - everything like that, he would not do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you mean he wouldn't even make a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He wouldn't make a cup of tea. Mother had to make everything. But it's no
t - it - it wasn't laziness - it was just a question of - his way of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say then that as far as you remember he never did any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing lie that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about making the fire - did he ever make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In a way, yes. He would do it in his own way. Be - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  a funny way of doing it you know - just a way of - of men of different - make up have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would he do the fire where the big pot cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, he would do - do a little to that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would he do it regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no. No. But he would - mother would - it would be quite unconscious he was putting extra burden on mother - 
it wouldn't be done - you see, it would be done }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 thoughtlessly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 - as I - as it often happens I suppose, one doesn't know how the other person lives. And that happens with man and wife. They live - they live together side by side for years and - that - they -
 they fall out and they - they they're not on speaking terms and the wife is saying, I know what you're thinking and he's saying, I know what you're thinking. But you know, they can be - they can be quite wrong. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother and father have a lot of arguments and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes. Rather friendly ones. Not - no big quarrels but it was - things of necessity which lead them into a temperament which would be - say normal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about decorating and painting - did he ever do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember him repairing anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If something broke - a piece of furniture or something - what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh he would just simply leave it. If a 
leg of a chair collapsed which - that did happen - it wouldn't be a question of repairing it - put something underneath to - bolster it up. Yes. That was his main trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you don't remember him making any improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And d
o you remember him doing anything for you or your younger brothers and sisters? Like dressing you or helping you on with your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no, I think it - father's - interest was in so far as - when we got into trouble - what he could tell us 
- what would happen to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of things would he say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - once I - once in Eynsham Hall Park I - I did lot of climbing - we did go up trees you know, just simply scamper up and I fell out. And I hurt my arm you know and I - I had 
it up for a long time, fortunately I didn't break it, and father said, pity I hadn't broke my b - neck, you know, swear word. Which he - he didn't mean. Oh no. But you see, that was his make up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would he ever tell you stories or talk to you about interesting things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
He - only - yes, he would in so far as weather was concerned. He had great sense of humour. I played cricket quite a lot you see and - he would say on a Sunday - hm, weather boy. Rain today I suppose. And he would be - he knew quite a
 lot about the weather you know and he would tell me what would be likely to happen. And he'd console me, he'd say that it would clear up later on - weather - we'd have a nice day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He'd talk about the weather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He'd talk about the weather. He'd g
ot a way of - of ding a whistle like a train whistle - anything to disturb you know or create an atmosphere. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 
He would - often sit by the fire and - play with his hand quite a lot, like this here - apparently what had happened - it was some time in the burning of the lime kiln - he - he'd had - lighting had affected that arm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And if you watched him doing this - could you do that boy - he'd say. Could you do that boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Twiddling his fingers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. You see we - he was - embarrassed if we said what are
 you doing that for dad? Could you do it boy? See. But it was only just to - I think it was quest - you know - relaxing his arm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean he didn't like you to realize there was something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. True. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember your mother going out and leaving him in charge of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, no, no. There was never a question of - of mothers at that time I remember rightly - being concerned about looking after children. As soon as you was four or five years of age you lo
ok after yourself. You see - coming from school - if we were late coming home that was no concern of mother. If we come home when it was dark. Because - that was always expected that we eventually would come home. Holiday times we'd start of in the mornin
g and come back at night - we'd be away all day long. No one'd be concerned or worried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would she know where you were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you take any food with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. We - no, we'd manage on - fruit - out of the hedgerow you
 know, hips and - this - what you call hips and haws is it. We would - you know - or anything like that there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 
Or - get onto a farm say and if we could work anything - I know we were - a small farmer had sons and he would - perhaps get some eggs and we'd g
et in - what we called a hollow place and - we'd had - had a little pot and a pan in there always secreted - you know - we'd make little meals up like that there.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That must have been fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, it was great fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember your father taking you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. Oh no, no, no, no. Oh no, when we went for a walk, father always used to shoot away ahead of mother - he was a - that man of impatience to move quickly you see. And - you see - speaking of his sen
se of humour - he would hide in the hedge perhaps and make a noise like an owl - you know - do all sorts of things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she think he was amusing - did she laugh if he did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. She would be amused at - his antics you know such as he could perform like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you don't remember him looking after the little ones - you had brothers and sisters much younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't remember him keeping an eye on a baby or a toddler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, oh no. Oh no, no, no. No, he 1 - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any jobs in the house that you had to do as a regular thing to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I did it - quite voluntary - I was never told. I don't think this - applied to my brothers. I don't think they were concerned. My moth
er was a continuous source of - worry to me. I could never leave the house very long unless I wondered what had happened to mother. You know, especially if she - if she wasn't very well I would be - not very far away. I could always do something about the
 house. But the moment my mother was all right I was out and into trouble. You know what I mean? I was very sensitive in regard to my mother. Worried stiff, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When she used to cry you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 And - I was very - I was a 
very disturbed child I think, and very, very nervous and when I went to school I never learned very little at school - 'cos I could never tell the schoolmaster, or anyone, what I was thinking.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What you were thinking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I lived in a different world you see, to most of the children I think. My mind was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 centred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  elsewhere. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you think about your mother a lot then when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, when I was at school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And that was where your mind was?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say you didn't have to be told what to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember any particular jobs you used to do often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Get - getting the potatoes ready. Helping to peel them and - any odd jobs such as - if the washing was dry,
 mother the washing's dry - shall I get some of it in for you? You know, I - drag the big trug out there and - drag it in and - everything I could possibly do - feed the chickens, get ready for feeding the pigs - and that was a great interest you know, th
e
 pigs, I - I used to look after them quite a lot when I was a schoolboy. And speaking of the pigs there was - speaking - when they were about - out school - we had two pigs, one was for the butcher, one was for indoors. So we called the local man in who w
a
s the man for killing pigs - I don't know, poor pigs you know with twitch round there nose and dragged out onto a stool and - throat cutting, you know, to bleed and - burning - burning off the straw - one pig was sold to the butcher and one was cut up for
 indoors. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 
And what we - the two sides, what we called pictures on the wall - one side was hung down that side of the house an this side - big piece of brown paper over, you know, of course it was properly cured with saltpetre and - the rack - what we called
 the rack was hams and that and - the leaf was made into lard - big dish of lard, 'cos we used to eat a lot of lard then - not - not butter that time of day, very seldom butter - margarine and lard. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I can always remember my mother making up the - this big 
dish of lard you know. And that was of course kept. We had it on bread. And the bacon - she'd come down in the morning, get a knife and take a - a rasher off - get a toasting fork in front of the fire we had what called a trivet and hang it in front }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  the
 fire and the bread underneath and the fat drop on. Turn it round and that - you see, that's how we used to - do things, that time of day. A pig indoors and a pig to be sold. As I say picture - we used to call 'em pictures. Pictures on the wall. You imagi
ne a picture of a side of bacon hanging down there with a big - big piece of brown paper down and one this side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did that last you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh about - last quite a - quite a time. That was when we was in a position to - you know, to keep a pig - keep pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you keep pigs at your first house in Northleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 , no, there wasn't a convenience because we lived in - one house - what we called a turnpike house. We were - such day
s as the turnpike days and our - when this led of into a - another village I suppose, and ours was a very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 crude}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 place. So - there - it was impossible to keep pigs there - it was only just a little house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was the one that had been a shepherd's hut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your brothers and sisters do any jobs in the house - you say they didn't help the way you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember them doing anything to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 None of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not even the two young girls - didn't they help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well they were too young you see because they died very young. One - one'd be I think about four and the other about one, you see. And - of course Ivy - we used to push Ivy out into the field and mother
 said, be very careful, 'course naturally she was devoted you see. Well as we went out into the field we - a big tree, what we call a rabbit tree, an old oak tree, centuries old I suppose - and we used to leave the pram very often - by the oak tree, perfe
c
tly safe by this old oak tree as a protection. We would go then what we called bird killing. That was catching blackbirds, you know. But only for a short time and rush back to see if Ivy was all right, you know. And - the others would say - well, she'll b
e all right. But no, not for me. I wouldn't leave her very long. May be ten minutes and I'd look, I was always in a reasonable distance so I could watch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you care a lot about her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you take Winifred out too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't remember much about Winifred. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember doing anything else for your younger brother, say Reginald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No, he - you see, because one thought mostly of ones-if. The struggle for - existence was - was so importa
nt then that you lived in a way that - to keep a balance - to keep moving oneself - make sure any of - were in trouble you just simply - just rescue them out of it but then you go on - go away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember doing anything else for Ivy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 besides}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  asking her out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't remember feeding her or dressing her or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No, no. I don't at all because that would be out of my - out of my - reckoning. I don't think a sense of feeling for other people was 
very deep that time. Only - as I say - most exceptional for my mother. Especially after contact with this - my - man Organ. Who was an agnostic - there's no question about it, he was, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember if you did anything to help the other brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, only Fred - I think I had a - a reasonable amount of understanding and sympathy for because - he would be with out with the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 threshing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  machines you know. - Oh yes, ah yes, you see, the engine, the drum and the elevator, you see, he'd drag a lon
g to the farms and of course he was fascinated }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 this and he - he would work wherever this thrashing - that's where he con - contacted this tuberculosis I think. When he had his money he would count his money and - two shillings, four shillings, that's 
half a crown Fred. Oh yes, of course it is, you see, he would count his money near me, not me telling me - he - he didn't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Didn't know the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he didn't know - no, he didn't, no. And yet as I say he was exceptionally uncannily
 clever in machinery. He'd simply pick - pick a watch or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of things did you do for him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Only in that sense - yes - otherwise I don't remember I could have does anything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you counted the money for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, counted the money and - little things in that way. But otherwise he paddled his own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 canoe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  as you - you see. Which I think we all did at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say that after the age of about four or five children looked after themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I - we generally went about half past eight. We - of course at that time we only had paraffin lamp - seen that little paraffin lamp - be careful you'll be knockin
g that off you know, and was always afraid - of course we'd go upstairs with a candle. Candlestick you know. Biggish room upstairs and of course eyes were very keen at that time so it didn't matter - we'd just feel our way into - to bed. We always went to
 
bed at half past eight or nine o'clock. But as a - as a big family you see gathered round the fire - little ones creep in - it was difficult to creep in and - you got cold I suppose really and you - you went off to bed. Then of course you've got to get up
 and go to school and you'd - you'd make shift, of course we did, we went to school, we'd get up and dress ourselves and - get off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember a time when your mother or anybody else would put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - no, I - she'd come upstairs and see that we got in bed perhaps and - and then straight away downstairs. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But when you were very little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think she put you to bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, when we were very little, yes, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of age do you think you started going up on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - about five - six. Oh yes. But afterwards I would never go up into the top room. Now I - I don't know why but I could always hear footsteps from the - what we called the garret. They w
ere loud as though someone was actually walking through this house. Now you see, I don't believe in all this sort of thing so I - I'm so convinced that that always happened to me, I never told anyone. I was scared stiff. Even when I grew older I wouldn't 
go up into that top room unless someone else went. I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Didn't you tell your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I never told my mother. Because I didn't want to be laughed at, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was your mother the sort of person you could usually tell worries to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, 'cos I remembered once - what - what did I - I had something myself when I couldn't breathe - what would you call that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 A stitch do you mean - when you've been running?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. It was - not - not appendicitis - ah yes, pleurisy, yes. And my mo
ther was ill at the time and the doctor came and she said - I never told my mother see, and I kept. - what's the matter with you? I said, no, I shall be all right mum. Doctor would you look at this boy? And he looked - I'd had this for about three days th
en. He said, good gracious, you've got - he's got pleurisy. And I was to keep quiet - I never had any medicine. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you never told your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I never told my mother but he told my mother, doctor - this boy's got pleurisy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why was it you didn't tell you mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She'd enough - she'd enough trouble, my mother, I wouldn't - no, no, no, couldn't do that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't tell her to protect her from the worry you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, quite. Oh no I wouldn't tell my mother anything. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If you did have some little accident or each or pain would you tell her or did you never tell her about things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, no. I can remember coming home, my mother had been doing some - making - knitting - would it be knitting -
 you know these long things - crocheting. And I came in - and we always learned manners you know in that respect - I came in sit down and I - I sat on this and it penetrated right though you see. I went outside, excuse me mother - outside and - I pulled t
h
is thing right out - what had stuck right through my skin and I pulled it out and I never told my mother. And I - I didn't come back indoors for a bit and - eventually - mother was conversing with - went out - I came back indoors. She looked - boy, what's
 the matter with you? I said, I'm all right, mum, nothing the matter. And I passed it off at that. And she didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old would you have been then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About eleven then. And - I went to school and of course I got a bit of rag and wher
e I went down to school I - I prepared - you know, washed at the steam and cleaned this off. It went down my leg you know and cleaned that off and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The blood you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. And eventually that was O.K. So - I was all right - it was a bit p
ainful at school but - but we got over all things of that sort, we didn't - at school you see, you went to school and you became quite - you were rough, you'd fight yes, we used to fight hard at school, it was a - a way of life I suppose, we did these sor
t of things and - I always remember at school our hair was always very short because - pick up things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was a problem in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8286046\charrsid5840491 wickedest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  thing I ever did I think at school was the girl sitting in front of me, I see something moving and I reported it to the teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did the family have their meals in the house at Northleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh in - in the house itself. In the big room, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any times when you ever ate anywhere else - there wasn't anywhere else was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. No. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your mother cooked on a range - in a big pot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On a big pot in the open fire by a chain you know the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 linked}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  to the - to the chimney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there an oven beside that range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, but it was never used. It was one of those ovens that never answer the purpose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I suppose it was the way it was fitted in and - with a big family it wasn't reasonable to use it. It would never cope with a family such as ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the local baker - was there a local baker?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes - no - well - the baker was about - at that time - about two mile away. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  And he brought the bread at - twice a week. We'd have as many as ten little loaves for the family 
for those two days because ravenous appetites and of course mostly on - bread and lard and - it could be bacon, you know, it was chiefly bread and potatoes sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say little loaves do you mean like the small loaves are today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, small loaf, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your mother never baked then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did people take things to the baker to be baked in his oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, not at that time. But later on - going back to later on, before 1914, there was a baker in the village 
local and one could do that but then the distance was the question involved. Those living near in the locality would do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you never have anything like roast meat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, no. Oh no. Out of the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything else that your mother ever cooked on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There was no other cooking apparatus, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you tell me about the first meal of the day - did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Breakfast was a kind of an impromptu thing. One got up and - made do
 with what one could find. It could be margarine, it could be lard, it could be even bacon as I told you before. Pictures on the wall. One'd just come down and help themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you would cut it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 One would cut it - a rasher off. From the
 - where it wax hung. Get the - we called it a trivet - a thing that you - in front of the fire and the fork - toasting fork, and catch the fat, you know, and - and that was the way we used to - manage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  think you had a rasher for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh I would say, two or three times a week. Otherwise it could be little toast with a bit of lard on. Not always home cured lard but what we-called bucket lard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was the inferior type which possibly - I don't kno
w if the butchers sell it that way now but there was an inferior type of - it wasn't the pure lard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often would you have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 margarine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh we always had that pretty regular. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember ever having butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, we defi
nitely had butter but - go to the farm - always went to the farm you know, to get the butter and watch them often making it with a churning machine, turning the handle and sparkling of the spots of water on the butter, you know, in round pats. And that wa
s most delicious - that was extra luxury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often would you have that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
That all depends on circumstances. If the money was a little better - and we'd have more butter but - never often. It very seldom happened that way. Or if eggs 
were cheap - and I've known 'em actually twenty-four a shilling - which was exceptional but that happened occasionally. Twenty-four a shilling, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then you would have eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was breakfast a meal that you all took a part in together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say impromptu you mean people came down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Absolutely - yes, one came down, of course the other brothers would - if they had work - be off early and they'd make a - a breakfast which - not actually sitting down possi
bly standing up and just making - getting some bacon - roast it all down by the fire and - hurried business - not actually a breakfast in the sense that you would sit down to have one - arranged breakfast - it was out of the question. And - and especially
 
when going to school - come down, you would dress and have a wash then cut a piece of bread and lard or whatever was available at the time and - just - the child would do us both - get on with it sort of business. And mother wasn't always in attendance li
ke that there because it wasn't - awful lot of times she was not sufficiently well to be up and about to do things so - that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about something to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, yes, we'd make our own tea. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 We'd make our - I remember it was calle
d bongoora at that time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And it used to be very strong you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have milk in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. But we got milk - often had a skimmed milk and I - I would go to the farm which would be about - four hundred yards away and watch them actually do
ing the milking you know and - of course it wasn't hygienic at that time. The cattle'd come in - there was no washing of the teats they just - wet it and - you know, you'd have your half a pint or pint of milk and I - I remember coming back with the milk 
often taking little bits of straw off the top of the milk - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 dipping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 the finger in which of course was absolutely wrong, doing that you know. Oh yes, but more often than not we had skimmed milk which was ha'penny a pint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have milk out of a tin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Still talking about breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would there be anything different on Saturday or Sunday for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Always just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the midday meal - what was that when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that may - consist of potatoes perhaps - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 green stuff}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 , because we had a big garden and mother would generally manage that. But that would be sufficient, that would be all right for us going to school. Father, when he c
ame home, as he did - he used to come home to dinner - and she'd make do with a few potatoes or anything like that, or bacon - anything that was hard and rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He liked did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes, anything - it wouldn't matter how tough the meat was he w
ould - but - 'course it was rather selection and sensitive - cheese - we would not have cheese - no, or cake or jam. Not father wouldn't. No, no. Had - very ordinary common food. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean cheese wasn't considered a common food then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was
 I think, yes, but not to father because he detested the taste of cheese. And a knife that had been used he would know in a moment - would not have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often in the week do you think you had some meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - on Sundays - Sundays wa
s a day when we had a real cooked meal when we were - when we had the gravy one with the big round dish you know and the cloth tied over - the pudding, yes, the meat pudding. That was - and as a child I always thought that everyone had that on a Sunday, t
hat was the usual - thing to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think it was in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 necessarily}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  so. I think it applied to us in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say you had the meat then - always on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But what about other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, not on other days. Oh no, that would be out of the question, one couldn't afford to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But didn't you have that bacon at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, that - yes - that - we - we would have -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When - you say meat you're thinking of butchers meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I was meaning the bacon too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often would you have the bacon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh once a day - in general - yes, once a day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If you had a rasher at breakfast would that mean that you wouldn't have it at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh not necessarily so. Very seldom one would have it occasionally at midday. But - as youngster you see going to school, we'd come home and we'd have - say lard which was - quite a - just the ordinary common diet that one accepted that with some sugar spr
ead it with sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On - yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Coming home from school - do you mean in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Come home to dinner - you see - because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About what time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Twelve o'clock. One'd leave school at twel
ve - some children then would - because of the distance would stop in the playground. There wasn't a question of stopping in the school because the school was shut up during the hour and half, so they would linger round in the playground. Now, there was n
o water supply so that one was extremely thirsty - I can remember often being very, very thirsty but there was no water supply.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you had no means of a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no means of drink. If one stopped at school - there was no drink until you went home again at night. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you sometimes do this - stop at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You always went home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I always made tracks for home. Yes. And you - you followed that track, you went down Church Road then you turned right at the bottom. 
Oh I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It says }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  to the right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you went on up that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 True. Yes, yes. That - that's Boddingtons Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you went home you had this bread and lard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you had the potatoes and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That would be midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That would be at midday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you might have both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your father would come home for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. He would come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the evening what was your last meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Very seldom - after tea - tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You had a tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About what time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That would be about - five o'clock. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What would you have for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, that could be anything - it just depends. I can think - it could be home made jam, it could be little - a slice of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 magarine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 or anything that was going at that time. It's very difficult to say because - there was no prepared meals in the sense that one would think of it today
, so that - of times hastily one would - I would help mother - unpack my brothers food. We would have a hurried - tea and - and - and be off you know. The urge to be moving around, you know. It wasn't a question of having a meal in the sense - that - one 
would think of today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean the table wasn't laid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that true of midday also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So there were times - you wouldn't necessarily sit down to your midday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, definitely not. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You definitely did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the two young girls - were they not served up food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Oh well yes, because - Ivy, the girls - I think she'd be about four. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Of course mother was naturally devoted because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 A daughter after all those sons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, yes. Yes. And then - we used to take the daughter out in the - in the pram out - rough pram I can remember now, it - you see, we'd push it through the fields you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you'd keep going and looking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Ye
s, we would leave by - by an old oak tree which be - ten years old - I know I see it not long ago - old and gaunt you know and I've tried to theorise out what happened in - in regard to the progress of that tree. I've often thought that at some given mome
n
t it must have become - it must become - the fullness of life and then say - decadence had set in and - and I - in regards progress of life throughout my - throughout the village I often thought what progress could possibly have been made - form the time 
that church - building of the church until say 1914 and everything then was so }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 desperately}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 slow in progress, question say gradualism - evolution - I thought then at 1914 when we congregated together at a meeting held by the - Mr. Mason, for volunteers servi
ce, I think some were about - thirty of us - youngsters then. We'd been brought up together, volunteered for services and the youth of the village then snatched away into the - into the war effort, that was a thing which - left me rather baffled as to - w
hat it was all about. Construction or decay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That meeting that he held - did most of the young people go to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, they volunteered, you see - no one - us - I suppose we studied the thing out in regard to being a conscientious objector 
- one became emotionally and it was the right thing to do and with great fervour they joined - joined the thing. Which I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Going back to the food question, your' father would also help himself in an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 impromptu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  way would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He wasn't served up food at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, well now I - I must say this as far as may father was concerned, he was an individualist. Now - it can be cruel, not intentionally, but my father was a complete helpless man indoors in so far as food was con
cerned. My mother must - no mater how busy a life she led, he's coming - serve his meal up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes. With great patience.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he expect it at certain times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On no, he - no, no, he was - a man that would accep
t anything that came along providing it was to his taste. You see, whatever was given him he ate but - he would not get up from the table and put his - and get ready for himself. Mother must always do this. It was habit I suppose formed and became charact
eristic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he come in at a certain time every day - a set time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, because that was impossible. The - the nature of his work in regard - in regard to lime burning all depends on what happened in regard to the burn - it may be irregular and therefore he would be delayed and watching the progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said your mother didn't bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she ever buy jam too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember her or your father making any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Certainly father would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But she didn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. But quite capable of doing that - otherwise -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, she was quite a very intelligent woman but - time - you see, with a family such as ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she make any medicines at all or remedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Onion gruel was chief medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 given}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was given for feverish colds - anything in that nat - anything in that nature, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember how she made it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No I can't - I know it was a gruesome sort of thing. It was made of onions and boiled up you know to a pulp type of things and one had to take it - there was no getting away - one must do this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything else do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I remember I suffered with chilblains. Terrific. You know, and my mother's remedy was - holly. You used this holly and tickled your feet with it 'til little spots of blo
od, you know, and then a smarting sensation - take the irritation away. That was - yes, holly. You just - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember other people using that or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, only my mother and I can't remember - I know it was - in fact I reme
mber once when it - I couldn't use the holly because - chilblains on - one on each opposite toe - you know - came - very troublesome you know and - had about a fortnight way from school, owing to this - trouble. But I do know that this holly was very effe
ctive in - in getting - tingling sensation, smarts you know and - that would be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything lese you remember her making in the way of remedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did anyone brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your brothers didn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your father got these acre fields didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he grow vegetables and fruit on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, he had his small - Mr. Mason had a parcel of land - in two separate parts of the village I remembe
r and he let this out on - on a - a - of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16150256\charrsid5840491 buying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 twenty-one years. Paying so much down you know and then - and my father had an acre and I had an acre and - I always remember my father with his acre growing vegetables and having a pig sty you know and - rea
ring two pigs and there came a time when he really didn't want it and - money was run out - father was getting a little short of money and schoolmaster wanted to build a house and I - I was watching the school - master and his wife, and son - watching - l
o
oking over and that was called - there - they called me over to have a look and asking me who this belonged to. Well I said that belonged to my father. They questioned if he would want to sell it, they wanted to build a house there. I said I would consult
 
my father and I went to see my father and he said - oh yes, he would, he would sell it. But I said you want to a right of way to the remainder of your land which was agreed on and - where by this land was forty pound an acre my - my father let them have a
 
quarter of it for forty pound and they built a bungalow on there and - father promised me that he would see me all right. But - after he'd made the deal I said, what about it dad? Well, he said, look here boys, he says, I've kept you all those years for n
othing, he says, you can't expect anything from me. I said, O.K. And that was the deal made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you feel about that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh not a bit - no, no, no. I quite accepted it 'cos that was father's make up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he grow on that field - on the other parts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well he - he grew potatoes and - Swedes - anything which helped to go towards - the pigs. Perhaps a little bit of barley, you know, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would he get the barley threshed and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well he - oh yes - he could get t
hat threshed because - he'd take it to a small farmer, you know, and they had threshing machine, they would do it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he ever get his own barley made into loaves or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there any where for growing things round your house - barn?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes, we had two - quite big gardens you know. Oh yes. Grow quite a lot there. That was in Boddington's Lane - in the - lane I was telling you about, in this big house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you grew there and on the allotment as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, but that's when we got up into the village - or into the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When your father had moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So when you were growing round Boddingtons Lane he didn't have the allotment as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was a later stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Round your place in Boddingtons Lane, did you grow enough vegetables to be self sufficient or did your parents buy vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, we really had sufficient gardens there to be self sufficient. And my grandfather who 
lived at Freeland - he had an allotment at Northleigh. They had small allotments I think at Freeland and it wasn't sufficient for him so poor old granddad he came to Northliegh, because you see, my mother - his daughter - was on his way and - always remem
b
er my - by the way he was a grand man who - lovely man and my grandmother used to talk - talk to me about him and I used to tell granny what a nice fellow grandpa was and he - she always had a good sense of humour, why, she said, you say that but you know
 
he hit me once. I said, what - grandpa never hit you. Yes, well of course, she said, he was ill in bed and - I said, grandpa - dad - you must give that land up at Northleigh. And he said, well land I want and land I'll have and if I can't get it at Freela
nd I'll go where I can get it and he swung his arm round and - that's the time he hit granny, you know. When he came there he always came with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 handful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  of - of sweets. Peppermints you know, sort. And he used to say, come along and we used to go out into th
e field. And he used to scrabble the sweets then you know. It was one of those lovely things which - you know - wonderful thing how a man at that time in - living in such conditions could do that when - often - I wonder I why you know, the satisfaction he
 got from it. It was lovely thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember anything else about him - did he talk to you much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No, I don't think so, except on the - jovial sort of things, you know, child - like way. That was one of those things which - I suppose - that time of day - the love of children I think was a grand thing with - with - that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever remember your mother buying any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember her buying any tinned vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about dried vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. We never had anything like that. I did remember we had - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Quaker}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  oats quite a lot. I always remember a picture on the packet was - was a child smiling and it went - what Quaker Oats, exclaimed the
 kid, I'll try and eat some, and he did. When o'er his kindly features spread the smile that won't come off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was on the packet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, it was on the packet. I remember - I always - I always remember a picture on the wall upstairs - in regard to
 - to cream. It was on this cart - was showing a calf - this cream is so delicious, this cream equivalent is so delicious I almost wish I was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 calf}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 . And we boys used to think along that line, we used to talk about that you know. Wonder what it was like. I always remember too -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Wonder what the cream was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never had it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. And I remember feeding - feeding stuff the cattle had at that time - thing called mussoline, it was a crude type of thing I - I suppose - I could imagine it would the extraction from sugar. It was sweet and we used to pick it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Pick it out from what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 From the chaff you know that was mixed up for the cattle and clean it and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And eat it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. We would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You kept these pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you had hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No other animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you always have the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Freeland, yes. But granny only had about three hens - I think I to
ld you - I suppose it was a question of the people living opposite, they lived with - kept several hens you know. And I think I told you where - the boy - mate of mine he used to lend me an egg for granny - we'd use the term lend and I used to - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 fluster}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  gr
annie's hens 'til they made cackling noise you know, then, the Lord have mercy upon us, she used to say, those hens have laid again, you know, they'll never finish laying. The Lord provides - he's very good. Used to say all this to herself you know. But o
f course she would never have had that egg if she'd have known because she was a devout Christian woman and her sincerity went - far beyond on any question of reproach you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you used to do the same with your mother didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. And with my father. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you do it to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well my father's sight got very bad and - you know - he never had spectacles, oh no of course it would have been a boon to him. He could have done but he didn't. And - me and my brother we
 would get a - egg and make the hens make a noise then dad's go out and he'd say - those hens'll never cease to lay - they're good hens you know. And - he'd - we - we dropped into misfortune, we came away from a cricket match and we bought some eggs and t
o
ld dad - you know - the hens had laid again but by the way, we had a parrot, and this parrot had escaped and got into the fowl house. And when he came outside he said, what's that - a rat? I said, it could be a rat dad. And - he scrutinized later on - he 
said, that's not a fat - you've got a fowl about here, which we had. He'd killed one of these hens and he charged us ten shillings for this hen. It was - it wasn't worth tuppence. It was an old hen which we'd kept going you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your father charged you ten shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He'd - ten shillings for this hen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh but that was - I suppose war were about sixteen or seventeen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you find the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that was - that was the question we had to gradually - pay this off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did it take you quite a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, yes, yes. Because I - I put supplement - had a little bit because - I belonged to a - I'm sorry about this now but farmers run a sparrow club. That was to get rid of sparrows and sta
rlings, chaffinches and I worked and Eynsham Hall Estate and we had those triangle cages to catch rats which I could catch birds in. Well, four heads, I had to keep the heads, to a public house to be checked. Four heads a penny. Well you see, a penny in t
h
ose days was quite a lot. Sometimes I'd get as many as eight birds. And - take them to this public house which question of tuppence. So that helped a little bit gradually and paid that off. Otherwise - when I was out of debt in so far as that went - it wa
s
 a question of getting a packet of Woodbines which you'd get a packet of Woodbines for a penny then. But of - now I do remember one man on the estate, very industrious type of man, and - he was so keen on getting rid of birds and - that anything but my ri
ght name, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Harry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
, Charlie Jim, used several names - I know where there's some young fledglings. Now you want a new pair of shoes don't you? I say, yes, Mr. Blake, I do. Now don't spend it on - on cigarettes, or anything like - I said, oh no, I must - 'cos I 
want some new boots. Come along and he'd get his ladder, he'd climb up to where he could find birds you know, get these young birds or - you see - they counted equally as - grown up birds and he'd labour quite - to showing it to me however. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you had to pay this ten shillings back - was it your brother's aw well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh there was only two of us - that was involved in this question of - paying dad then ten shillings,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he pay half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He paid half, yes. I paid half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember whether you ever got some extra meat such as a rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes definitely - yes. Now we had a dog - my brother had a - a dog - a terrier. He was promised one from a well bred bitch and reluctantly this fellow - he - honoured - honoured his word. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 He give him the smallest one of the lot but I think this turned out to be one of the very best because we learnt - he learnt this dog to do all sorts of things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Believe me, he would carry a kettle - you know - he'd carry a stick. I remember the first time - bring that stick home. He came in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 broadways}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and it charred. And the next time he - took hold of the end and pulled it in. Well why I mention the stick is because firewood was most important things so w
e - we got out and about we always looked out for firewood, you see, because you'd got to kindle a fire and break the wood up and any dry stick one could get you always brought it home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 
And so this dog - we'd gone on Northleigh Commons and catch a rabbit and bring it home, of course, that was a question of going in the pot pretty quick. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
You'd get a rabbit then for about eightpence. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you cold buy one for eightpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You cold buy one for eightpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever sell the rabbits you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes, there was times when - Oh yes, that was a question of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 
killing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  the rabbit and - that was the question of getting tobacco - I would smoke a pipe even when I was quite young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I was - when I was about fifteen or sixteen I'd smoke a pipe. Clay pipe. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you'd get the tobacco with the money from the rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say the dog got the rabbits, you mean he would kill the rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. he would kill the rabbit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever kill rabbits by any other means?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - you see, in the autumn time especially, what we call rabbits would sit. That was in the grass that was rough and they called it odd - you know. How, you'd suspect that t
he rabbit would be there and - you would - go forward and put a stick up with a bit of paper on top - the rabbit - you'd get behind the rabbit the, always providing - you must - the following wind - he'd sent you - he'd be quite sure about that. Then you 
rush up and - as you got near the rabbit would sit tighter and you'd drop down on the rabbit. Catch it that way. Just with your hands. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You've done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you leave them alone when they were breeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
ach all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, not then. No. No. But otherwise - if they'd been out shooting for - say Eynsham Hall Estate and they had a big shoot like }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 pheasants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  or that sort of thing of course rabbits. Rabbits would be very - they'd sit tig
ht then - you'd get a long thorn and push down the hole as far as you could go, twist it round and round, you'd probably get a rabbit that way. And pull it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Out of the hole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, out of the hole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you get something round its neck then - how did you pull it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Well because the wood you see and the thorn would grip tight. Pull it out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father poach too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. Oh no, father was just the opposite in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh because he'd such respect to the powers that be. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In some areas people were allowed to poach, was this not so where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh that was illegal that was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There wasn't any areas near where you lived where it was considered all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh
 no, definitely not because - I remember on one occasion two men on a bridle road, that was - is of course - the right and left was belonging to Eynsham Hall Estate, Goodland. And this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 bridle
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  road ran through from Northleigh onto the main Witney Road and i
t - ran in from Northleigh to about - runs right through. Well they were down there and they caught - some rabbits. Now the keeper came along and said he was going to summons them fro trespassing. But, they said, we're not trespassing. But any rate they w
e
re summoned and they appeared before the magistrates at Woodstock and the keeper said that they were trespassing on Mr. Mason's estate which was of course off the bridle road. Now - Jack said to the other, he said, what were they on about. And while they 
w
ere arguing the case the magistrate fixed a fine, which I think was about seven shillings. Now I came across these two men - and one - look Bill. Jack said, oath - we're on oath - we were never there, he says, and it'd be no good for me to tell you a lie 
b
ecause I'm telling you now we did not go over there but he said they swore before sentence. I said, in that case I said, I'll write to Miss Mason. So I wrote to Miss Mason. By the way, my wife was a girl guide at that time, Eynsham Hall, yes. And I wrote 
t
o Miss Mason and she wrote back and said - something like this. Dear Billy, she - dear Billy, your letter took my breath away. And she went on to say that she'd put this matter before Mr Mason, her father, which evidently she did because sometime afterwar
ds the keeper finished at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Eynsham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Hall and I take it for granted that was the reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The keeper finished there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was dismissed you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think so. I think that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you think the men weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh definitely - they - they - they never trespassing but this evidence was sworn against them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did you decide to write to Miss Mason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because I thought of the injustice and I thought if I wrote to Miss Mason she would take the matter up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you were right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - I was quite justified in doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think I was about - this was - this was - immediately after the war. Yes. That was the time when I went on the parish council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When did you first meet Miss Mason - when you were quite a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I don't think I ever came in contact with Miss Mason because - in the sense that she probably got to know me though my activities in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So up to the first world war time you wouldn't have known her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. But following first world war - of course as I say I became active and then it was a question of a memorial - now - it -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old do you think you were when you started poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - I think that followed on really from the time I worked at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 Eynsham}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Hall. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What age was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I worked at Eynsham Hall when I was about - say - fifteen. Because earlier on I started at Witney at the - International Stores and I was there one week.
 Village had a festive - a club, what they called the club, you know, men paid into a club and they had a beano once a year. And - it - this happened on a - I think on a Thursdays which I stayed away and when I went back on the Friday I - they - you finis
h here, it's the end of the week. I said, O.K. with me, I said, you pay me now and I'll finish right away. But they wouldn't so I carried on to the Saturday then they begged me to stay on. But I wouldn't stay on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well because of the hours. A
nd this - they sent me off to go to - through Newland to High Cogges. This was - I - I - I told them I would not stay on 'til after five o'clock. Well they sent me away about quarter to four. Then I got away up Newland and I turned back with the goods and
 went back because I knew very well that it - it'd be too late - it'd be five before I got back before five o'clock. And it was terrific - terrific row over that business. But I did finish there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why do you think you stuck so much to your hours like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - I thought at an early age then one had to be very definite about things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think it was the influence of the shoemaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think so. Yes, I think - because - that was question then of - I believed in - in - in time - a 
fixed time when started work and when I left off, and I made my own arrangements then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you when you got that job at Witney?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At Witney? I suppose I was about - fifteen, because I came; I'd come away then from Sandhurst you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say the poaching was an organized thing what exactly do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - I mean in this sense. Now, you see, when you - when you - when you're join and growing up people trust young people well - now I worked on Eynsham Hall Estate and 
I - I worked with the keepers very often and the conversation was where they were likely to be to catch the poachers. And - I used to listen very attentively. Now people in the village they would trust me, although I was a youngster, they would absolutely
 
trust me with everything. I would give them information. They use nets you see. Well they'd go up at night when rabbits were out at feed - they knew here - where the hedges were and where the rabbits were likely to run. They'd set the nets along, they had
 a dog - well trained dog - and this dog would round like a sheepdog would round sheep, he would round the field and of course the rabbits dashed and they'd catch them in their nets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the keeper realize you were passing information?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh not on your life. No. He wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He would trust you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. 'Cos I was very - very shrewd you know and - you see, I suppose one - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  age at that time - joined the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  circle. One - the habits formed then I think became - ended in character - became characteristic in one grew up in a groove which I say it was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 vicious}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  circle - one did the winking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491  trick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 you know and you'd do all sorts of - of - indirectly one understood the language used in the village conveying a message, you know, to that one became shrewd and - and crafty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Conveying a message of what kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Of a - of a cunning - of a craft, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean people would speak in a sort of code?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On what matters - about the poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Or - or - y
es, on that sort of thing. When - habits I should think became characteristic of people at that time. Life was raw then and - the very struggle for existence led one along courses which made it just possible to survive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were telling me that your mother had less food so the family could have more - you saw this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Mother - often mother would come downstairs and - very hygienic insofar as for instance washing her hands and face and mother's hair was extremely long. She would - come
 right the way down here. I can always - we used to have a screen to keep the draught back you know, she used to stand up against the screen and brush it, she used to go back and - hair down here - I can see it now. And - I'd say, mum - what's for breakfa
s
t mum. You know. Meaning to say, what are you going to have? I don't want anything this morning, I'm not feeling too good. I think I mentioned to you what mother called it, the roaring wind. She - it was - I know - but - never any set meals, mother never 
had any set meals, I can never remember mother sitting down to have a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not even on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh - not on a Sunday because - on a Sunday - well you see, there was so many of us, big table and we were all round it and - getting everything out - it was too big a thing. I suppose she'd make do with something after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She was waiting on all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. Great sacrifice it was - to provide for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father have more food than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no, no. No, he wasn't big eater, father wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you allowed - when you did sit round the table - to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There wasn't a strict rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 Oh no, there was no - no - no manners in the sense that one understands at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491   }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 the - organized type of meal.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If your mother cooked something and you didn't want it what would she say - or didn't this apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no - I - we would eat almost anything that was - because we followed the routine - f
ollowed so regular and we got so used to it that I suppose probably - at - a given type of food we would - we may not have relished quite so well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Say on Sunday if she gave you your food and you left some uneaten on the plate what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Believe me there was never anything left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It just didn't happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Because I can always remember - in a little kitchen place at back with a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 green stuff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - greens was put in the pot you know and fork it round. We used to hook out with the 
fork any - if there's any little bits left in there, we used to fight for this sort of thing you know. Yes. Oh there was nothing left. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If there was something on the table you wanted - was salt put out on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Could you ask for it to be passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, we didn't do that sort of thing, we just simply -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Stretched?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. We - because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said there were no manners - things like how you held your knife and fork and how you sat, that wasn't worried about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If you put your elbows on the table it didn't matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, that was quite all - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Cold you get down from the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, one got down just - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If you'd have wanted to bring a comic or a toy to the table could you have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes. 'Cos we relished the comics at that time of day - one had comics Cuts and Chips - they were almost as big as what newspapers are today. And then we had the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you could bring them to a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The Sunday dinner - was that the only time that the family all sat down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you all have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When she served the dinner on that day how did she serve it. Did she put it on dishes on the table or did she serve from the pot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
She served from the pot and - all - there was a dish for the potatoes and then one of the elder brothers would - to the - to us that was on the smaller - smaller ones would put it out on the plate, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He would serve you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Then mother would oft times cut the pudding and little bit of meat that we had and then the grown ups would just simply help themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They would help themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 By the grown ups, who do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - elder brothers that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The ones that were grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would they help themselves - would they get up from their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 chairs}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and help themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, just scoop out you kno
w and - pull the dish up - you see because life was such - so unorganized very necessity that if one count formalities it would be ridiculous - one would never manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Ivy and Winifred and there was also a brother younger than you wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Reg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Walter and Reginald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember them eating before the meal or did they always eat with the family when they were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, with the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would they sit then when they were very little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well we had a - a high chair. Reg had a high chair. I can remember him - and I can remember once falling on the fire. And it burnt a patch here and he always - his hair always grew - he let it grow right over this you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did they manage then for their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I suppose my mother would - have a way of feeding - feeding, sitting on lap or in a chair which was safe, you know. And of course the treatment with us - I can remember we had a - my brother, Fred, which wasn't very brilliant, he d
idn't know a half a crown from a two shilling piece, but very brainy -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 With machinery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Most amazing. Well - we had a - he had a - made in a shape of an engine with a chimney - on a little - made of tin you know, and he'd put smoke - a ra
g in and smoke'd come out the chimney and Ivy - he would sit in this and he'd have guides. And we used to go up a hill and then of course we used to go down this hill and Ivy would be in there - mother didn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did Ivy enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, we - on wheels you know - some sort of pram wheels. And Ivy - yes, she would enjoy it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You told me how you would keep all your worries from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, that is true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never talked to her about anything that worried you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. No, that was - I think that was quite - I did the right thing there. But I was extremely worried about all sort - yes, about my mother - and everything, yes. Very nervous - very much afraid when I went to school because I was backward in rega
rd to sums, I never - you know arithmetic. But composition I was good at - on composition you know, that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But backward in arithmetic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anybody that you could talk to about the things that bothered you when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nobody at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You kept it all to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes, I puzzled - I always remember one day going to school when two men were baling hay from a rick - hay rick you know - and one day watching this p
rocess and suddenly I see a man - you know - in tremors. The other fellow got hold of him, put him - laid him on some hay and then made a rush for me. And I made a rush too. I thought he was going to do something to me. Well apparently what happened, this
 man had a fit. 'Course I didn't know that at the time. I was afraid of this man - I didn't come back the same way - across the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you didn't tell anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I didn't tell anyone about that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 O
h yes. Oh yes. Yes. That was - that was in a general way - one only understood that by - if - if - you wasn't well - if you had a cold or anything she'd do everything then to - but never made a fuss, oh no. No embracing or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She wouldn't do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She didn't kiss you goodnight when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. No. No. I think - I think life then was - was so busy and - and so strife ridden that that didn't happen. Just the necess - the very necessary t
hings you see and I say as regards to, if one wasn't well, yes, she'd do anything she could possibly to help then. But there wasn't no - affection showed otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father show affection towards you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Not at all. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were ill did he say anything then or show any care for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. Apparently it would appear to be quite indifferent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think he really was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, I do. I think it - that - yes, it wasn't - was a question ; incapability of
 giving expression - I think that run away through most people at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you didn't tell him any worries either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no. Oh no, that - that was absolutely waste of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did your mother and father expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
They certainly expect one to be most honest and truthful. Dad was a - that was - that was expected - that was the way that they understood life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Truth was - their way of what the law was. And that was truth. But you see that wasn't truth - that was such }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 damnable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 lies. Law and justice was peels as under that I - I accepted truth as I could see life - as one - what was necessary and what - if anything I could get for my mother - stealing wasn't the - question to me - it was a question 
of helping my mother. And I mean this country was never - never so rich as it was then all - so far - well - I think of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 works}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Ruskin - what was life and money was of the secondary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 importants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  in comparison. But the wealth was never utilized in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember what they expected of you in the way you behaved with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, no, all they did expect was one to be - truthful and honest and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did they expect you to behave towards your brothers and little sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, no, that - one accepted what - one accepted all things that happened in one's of course with my elder brothers, if you didn't do what was required you'd get into trouble. The question of getting wood ready for the morning - that was a problem, it 
was very difficult. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 
Well I had to go - sometimes about the house to get the dry coney sticks, anything, but one always had to get the wood ready for lighting the fire early in the morning because they had to to work early, you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your brothers expected that of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh you yes. And - and of course you got a clout if you didn't do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything else you had to do for your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 older}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have to run messages for them ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No. One could refuse that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They wouldn't clout you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Just the wood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why was it they could insist on the wood and they couldn't insist on other things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well because that was a pri
me necessity you see. They could - they - they would start off in the morning you see and when they came back at night if it was - toward wintertime - there was no daylight and - made a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If a child in the village hit you and you told your parents what would their attitude be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well you'd have to fight back. Yes. Yes. But then you see that wouldn't happened because you would never tell your parents. As regards the police - if you were playing antics in the village, which we did, suddenly at night you'd get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 clout}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 and - you'd say who's that and you'd be sorry you passed that remark because you'd get another one. You see, the police would hit you then. And - and hit you really hard. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did they hit you with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 With a stick or anything they had - their hand. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything else you think your parents }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 brought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  you up to consider important in life besides honesty and truthfulness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I can't think of anything which - in - in that sense, except they - the
y expected one to respect their elders and to - to - to respect authority. Such as the powers that be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did they think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, strong objection to that. And singing songs on a Sunday. Or - my mother would sew a button on the tro
users or anything like that for my brothers if - if it - it was quite necessary but never used a needle on a Sunday or do any darning. That was - that was - or singing a song on a Sunday, that was wrong. My father even - he - no - he wouldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You did tell me of an incident when your father did swear at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, he would swear - father would swear - yes, he would. Oh yes, he would use those words - swear words.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, my mother never heard my mother use a swear word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you children weren't allowed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 
And I'm rather surprised at my father because you see his mother - his mother was a - I think they had a background but she was a Smith and the Smith's I think lived at Kiddlington and they were in the t
imber merchant business - very respectful - chapel people and she was a very sedate lady and so - as regards my grandmother I can remember - paying visits which I had to do and I can remember when she was laid upstairs, bedridden - the first things' inspe
ction, boot laces and everything had to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 
be so neat and sedate and everything correct and - she questioned me about - what did I do when I had pennies, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
And did I save it. And then eventually she'd probably give me penny or tuppence as case may be. V
ery careful woman, she would never waste a ha'penny. But - daughter, auntie, if someone knocked at the door and it was a - tramps on the road then quite a lot - get someone knock at the door she'd shout - who's that Emily? It's someone begging Well - give
 her tuppence. Granny was always giving tuppences and pennies like that to people and yet the most careful woman, she never wanted not a bit of bread or anything like that. You know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who was Emily then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was the daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who lived with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Oh yes, free for all. Yes. And of course the argument then would - would - especially with my elder brothers - they were very powerful 
- they were very - quite strong, I often wonder why because my mother wasn't very big or my father but - my brothers was exceptionally - and of course they would fight. Yes, but - but then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Fight among each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, they would really set 
to you know. And the things'd go - and my mother would just step in between - come along, both of you go. And they would go like lambs. My mother's tre - tremendous discipline. In that respect - when she - one word from my mother and that was sufficient. 
O
n the other hand - playful - I remember - sometime - one of my brothers said - mum, out of doors you go. Just simply pick her up and put her out of doors you know. And she'd get a broom and they'd play you know and - of course they'd shoot upstairs or som
e
thing like that you know. Sense of humour. That was there. But - in regard to discipline, yes, my mother was supreme. What she said was law. And instantly obeyed. It was extraordinary you see because we were rather wild lot but anything my mother done or 
said - she meant it - if you knew she meant a thing you'd accept it - do it. Wonderful thing about our family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She never punished you then - you don't remember her punishing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, because we were very fleet of food - always escape. Long befor
e that happened and then of course it was question of - of chasing upstairs, round the beds you see and up into the top room and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your father ever punishing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I - I can never remember my father ever picking me up - he wou
ld have done - there were occasions when he's chased me and my elder brothers I suppose out into the field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you never remember getting a hiding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He never hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Or your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh my brothers hit me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your brothers would hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But did your father hit your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he try to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother ever hit you or your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were never sent to your room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You weren't punished really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not in that sense, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father discipline you also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was your mother who controlled you was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, mother was the - mother was the - sup
reme commander of the household. And I think - it was more of the influence of - of brother - and of father too - in our make up in life as I say - habit becomes character and character ends up into general make up in life. So I think, as a family, althou
g
h we grew up in - what would say - almost utter confusion - at, say thirteen or fourteen, it had been so implanted - a way of life as regards to honesty and integrity that it was accepting unconsciously we grew up into a family - into a world which we ent
ered and I think we were always honest and truthful. I can remember my - my father when he was - just after the war most forgetful and my brothers -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 These ideas about honesty - did you get them more from one parent than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 From both. From both. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you had a birthday as a child would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Oh no, that'd be quite - just the ordinary day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you receive an presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And no guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing to mark it as different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they say happy birthday to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I don't think so. I don't think that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Didn't they even tell you it was your birthday when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh I suppose I did - I think I remember that, yes. I remember birthday - but you see that was just a matter of something that happened - you didn't keep that as anything important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing personal for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was Christmas Day like - how was it different from other days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Christmas Day was going out round the village - singing carols.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You did that on the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, but we - we - we did rather exceptional long walks. Birdwalk Farm. Matter of fact - the case was in the paper not long ago about a girl taking drugs at this Birdwalk Farm - any rate we used to go to these farm
s you see and we got a few coppers. And - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother and father go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. My fa - my mother then on a Christmas Day would be busy getting a dinner you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When did you have Christmas Dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - it'd be midday. Just
 ordinary - be nothing out of the ordinary. Nothing exceptional. Perhaps a few more - two or three oranges then - or maybe apples.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And what in the way of meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, be much the same sort of thing, we never had anything special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of meat dish would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It would be what we called the gravy one. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Meat cut up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Like you had on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, mother'd cut it up you know. There'd be nothing different about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would there be anything different for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything to drink at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No. I remember - Christmas on one year or maybe two years - Masons' then had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 bullock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 that he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
would cut up and share out the men on the estate. I remem
ber having, as a boy, there - I didn't like it. It was boney and it was fat and it - it didn't look to me very nice and I thought I'm the boy and this is - this is the worst little bit they - last little bit they've got and they give it to me. Well all ri
g
ht, so I put it in my basket and I went along the park and I think to myself, I'm not going to take this home. They can keep it. And - but the trees - young trees, they had a fence round you know and spikes so that cattle couldn't - see, and I think to my
self, I'll hitch this on a spike. And I did. And I left }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 there. I looked forward to taking this home to mother you know. And I didn't talk it home, I left it on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Never took it home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't get any presents then on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no. No presents no. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything in the way of mistletoe or holly put up in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh we - holly, yes, we'd get holly because that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368487\charrsid5840491 plentiful}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - you could always go out in the field and get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you put it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Hung it round the house, you know. Behind two or three - picture - even the pictures on the wall - in the - by the way, I remember two pictures we had - one was a - an oil painting and I - it was a - a - an eagle taking
 a - about to take off from a tree and the mother at the bottom - saying - now I wouldn't know what it say probably in German, but underneath was, die mutter regret de kinde. So - the mother regrets the child, or something like that. And then another one 
w
as the butchers funeral and there - there's four oxen - two in the back and of course two in the front with the coffin resting on, horses and sheep and - or animals, jumping up in the air with glee, you know. The butcher's funeral. It - it was a - it was 
a wonderful thing because the Duke of Marlborough came up one time and he wanted to buy this. Yes. And mother wouldn't let it go. She would not let it go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did he know about the picture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He - he must have - oh he came - they were doing some re
pairs to the house and it just so happened that the Duke came up instead of his agent, a man named Angus. Well the Duke came on this occasion and - he was most interested in these pictures but mother wouldn't dream of letting them go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did she get them from - do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It came from a grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 From her grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, from father's mother - yes. Yes. And - by the - insofar as the Duke was concerned, on this occasion - and a man lived in a house about two hundred yards away
 and the field behind belonged to the Duke and this old gentleman named Mr Green, he was always keen to get a little piece of land enclosed from the field - a corner piece that maybe from here to your elbow there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 As small as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, as small
 as that - that would be about a quarter of an acre. Now - this Mr Green thought he'd see the man about our place and he thought it was Mr Angus. And he called Mr Angus over. And the Duke went over. Ah now, Mr Angus, he said, now I wonder if the little Du
k
ie would let me have this piece of land, and of course he went on told the Duke about it and the Duke rumbled what was happening. Well now you see, he said, I must see the little Dukie - and this conversation went on. 'Til eventually the Duke went away an
d
 my father quite inquisitive about it knew what was happening, he went down. He said, how did you get on with the little Dukie? to Mr Green. I see Mr Angus - I haven't seen the Dukie. Ah he's going to see the little Dukie. Ah, but my dad said, you've seen
 the little Dukie. And yes, he did, yes, he had this little piece of land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. He got it. But it was the Duke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And he never let on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he never let on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did they call him the little Dukie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because he was rather small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of person was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - at that time I wouldn't remember much about him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that incident before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, that was before the first world war - oh yes. Yes, that was - 'cos I remember my father telling the story many a time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any musical instruments in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Moth organ. Get one for sixpence then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. My brother - one went to Canada. He was really good singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you went carol singing did you all go on that - all the brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, we mixed up as a - you know - from lads in the village. Well, really it would be - two or three of my brothers and - like living ne
xt door we'd go round you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever all sing together as a family in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would your mother sing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, my mother would. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, he would - he - he - little ditties that he makes up. Of his own - yes, he'd make them up himself you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He sounds a real character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, he was. And so - my brothers would sing songs of - of course songs of that time - there were songs at that time which are ou
t of vogue now but I remember quite a lot of them. I remember one song that the publicans drew up. I tried to keep it - this was posted up in a pub - I've tried to keep a decent tap, ready money but no strap - the words was used, strap it up landlord - I'
v
e tried to keep a decent tap, ready money but no strap. Chalk is useful say what you will, but chalk won't pay the brewer's bill. Customers came in and I did trust them, I lost their money and their custom. To lose them both it grieved me so, so I resolve
d to trust no more. You see. That - that was about people owing him money you see. 'Cos that was tuppence a pint then you see, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That - well - you see, you'd say, hey landlord, strap it up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Go on the slate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Slang words you see, yes, put it on the slate. And of course fellows would say - to get into the public house if I could - if I could only get in there just enough to lift the latch I would be all right. To lift the latch would be a question of getti
ng tuppence to - lift the latch to get into the public house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And so the publican wouldn't have any credit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He wouldn't give credit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He got to that stage when there was no credit.
