\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never went away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. That was - our holidays was such that we wondered ar
ound as we thought fit. We'd wander out into the big open spaces - I can always remember one gentleman - in one field he - he used to walk and turn and look and I - his admiration I think was for the - was the sky and the scenery you know and everything a
r
ound which reminds me that he never had a sense of what he gathered from all that was never given back into reality - into life. He see there was something there that - it reminds me of the cynic who wrote - as he watched someone he said, this friend of g
reen, this hub of flame, fantastic beauty such as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 Xerxes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 in some warped poet when he works without a conscience or a name. You see, and this gentleman, he was looking at the friend of green, there's nothing so green as this country and all the flame, you know, and it was a beauty that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 lurked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 within him but - it - he'd no conscience or a name - it wasn't anything to further life in that point of view. He was intoxicated with something which was nothing. Unless it was used for some other purpose.
