\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And to services as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. I remember going on one - to Weymouth. That was quite an event because I - I remember losing my cap on the way going - we wore our caps in those days because of fear of sunstroke so we were instructed and eventually reached our destination and got a
 severe reprimand for - absenting myself, I was quite interested in a Punch and Judy show and - 'course I was called over the coals for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any other social activities organized by the church at Freeland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There was something in rega
rd to Freeland - following the service we were taken on to the lawn and played games - it was most interesting and I think it was quite a - a thing much appreciated at that time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 
Otherwise the service was really quite serious and deep, but the relief was - with the play afterwards. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And I think really that attracted us more than the service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any special activities connected with the choir like a treat or outing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the church there run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any temperance activities that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, I don't think - nothing what so ever in regard to that. As far as the church of England was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But in the chapel, yes, there was definitely - Band of Hope. I was a member of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have something to do with chapel activities as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I was much persuaded to - to take an active part
 in that - in the revival meetings such as they had at those days - in those days and - I was quite unattracted but it was quite a revelation to me as far as some of my friends were concerned, two in particular. There was - boisterous types of fellows you
 
know and they became - really sincere Christian. I was so amazed to see the transformation that I was deeply interested but not persuaded to take - because I'd taken a new line of thought. I never accepted a thing - as it was explained to me. It seemed su
ch a lie and truth really wasn't there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 I - I never question the sincerity of the people that was trying to persuade - going to accept this. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But in - under the - under the stress of emotional strain I think my friends followed that and - so it reacted on th
em that they became really quite sincere and very deep. In fact it coloured so far through in regard to one of my friends followed that and - so it reacted on them that they became really quite sincere and very deep. In fact it coloured so far through in 
regard to one of my friends, in the Army where it's most difficult to follow a - a life - a Christian life, I would say, in the accepted sense, that this friend of mine was quite sincere all the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever attend the revival meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were they held in the chapel or outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
In the chapel and out of doors. But - I was - I was unpersuaded because what had happened in the village was I knew of two men in particular they were aged and one was ill at the
 time but there - no one there that was taken - activities in revival meetings that attended. Either of these two people. I had a brother who - took no interest in religion in that sense, he used to - he used to visit this - one - one man in particular he
 
used to visit and take him a bit of tobacco and peppermints yes, and a Salvation Army man came to see him and he said, well, his name is - we called him Jappie I don't know why - now Jappie you've left in rather late you know. And my brother was present a
t the time, he used rather abusive words. He said, best thing you can do is to get out. You never bought this man a rice pudding or anything to help him in any way and now you're talking to him like that - get out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the church - were they good to the people - bringing them things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, because as I say the activity of the church at that time was under the - well couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  an influence of the Vicar such as he was - Mr Scott. So the - the church was practically dead. Everything -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This is the Vicar with the baby in the bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was the Freeland church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, Northleigh church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about at Freeland church - what was the vicar like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, he was 
a - at that time the vicar was a marvelous man. The one that - enjoyed life with children, to give you an example - on a Sunday as we were playing on the lawn previous to joining a choir - I was inspecting an apple tree and found one looking rather nice a
nd he just watched me take it and just patted me on the back and just laughed, you know, and I never forgot that because he accepted that sort of thing quite possible from - children. The contrast was, the vicar following was just the direct opposite. Ve}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 ry,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 very strict. Now I - I doubt if anyone could ever question that - this vicar's sincerity because he believed that that was the right way, and it seemed so contradictory to me from a sense of a Christian point of view.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you belong to any club organised to the church or the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, to be quite candid, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you as a child taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. The Lord's prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. He was Conservative. Very much so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why do you think he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 My father - accepted the idea that those - in a position of education were the authority and the people to - to govern. They knew best.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about your mother - do you know if she took an interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. My mother just I think automatically - followed my father in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember her giving evidence of her views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. I think mother was too obsessed with family life and everyday problems such as they were and therefore I never remember my mother giving utterance to any thoughts which I might express but so - so embodied with everyday life, I think it almost be
came impossible to - to take any other view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes. And being very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 persuasive}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  we followed suit along the same lines as him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - the Conservatives were supe - was the right people and the - the other party was - rowdies - not to be trusted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know if he went round in the village talking to people about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not necessarily so in that respect but in conversation he would quite emphasise the necessity of voting right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At that time many men felt they risked their homes or their jobs if they didn't vote a certain way - do y
ou think this was an influence on your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, I - I wouldn't think that way whatsoever. But it was I think on a majority of people they care - take great care not to divulge which way they would vote. But that followed a general trend in those days that - I use the word }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  circle not necessary that men were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  but - the art of - of - of existing was to be very - very shrewd and so in conversation, even in a public house men knew one another and conversation they would talk in 
a language which would be understood - between them and just a wink or a nod - accept what had already been said.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On what type of subjects?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 Well generally with regard to - to employment or about say - talking about - farming or any work which -
 they were getting a living from - he most careful not to say anything derogatory - to what might happen - someone might be eavesdropping pass the message on. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
A very guarded conversation. Yes. Very careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your father ever working for the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know if he was a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, no, I don't think in those days one - things went that far. No. Because just a minority - in power - used their influence and it was sufficient. In the - not an organization such as we have today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say that your parents took part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say your mother had any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, none whatever. It
 was much too difficult to - to even think of my mother - taking any other activity outside the home, she was obsessed - her whole life was obsessed with the - the family life and - renewing for the next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember her having any leisure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No - nothing whatever. No, continual toil from early morning 'til late at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your father have leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well not really. I suppose father's leisure would be - going for a drink you know. Quite a moderate man. Probably would 
say two pints a day would - suffice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He would go to the pub every day then would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes, that was a - I think that was a - possibly habit because he didn't drink that much but he must have a - a drink at night. He'd go quite a distance - the pub would be at least a mile and a half to two mile away. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember her going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, that - that wasn't thinkable at that time - for a woman to go into a public house
. She'd go for the bottle - to - for bottled beer or something like that, but not to sit in a public house. Utterly impossible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said he would get home in the evenings at irregular times owing to the nature of his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many evenings a week would he be at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh probably four or five. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And those evenings he would get home at approximately what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Five o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Then when would he have the drink in the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh that - that'd be half pa
st eight or - say, nine o'clock. Never in a hurry to get - really get away. He'd get away into a pub say at nine o'clock and of course pubs closed then at ten o'clock - be quite all right. Most contented man. If he could get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the evenings that he didn't get home at about five he would get home about when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - that - that'd be all night sitting up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He might not come back at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not 'til morning. Morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was he a member of any club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And your mother wasn't member of any club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. At that time you see things was - things was very much isolated. More an individual life or family life so that - insofar as - nothing was - at that time, organized. I can remember no social activity in the village ex
cept - the - the things such as the Ancient order of Forresters - Ancient Order of Buffaloes I think. That was a club where men paid - threepence or sixpence a week and at the end of the year they'd have a beano, you know. Met and - of course it was a sic
k benefit and of course Lloyd George - insurance came along and of course that - then it was disbanded. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your father belonged to that did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he didn't belong to it, no, he wasn't interested in that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Just darts in the pub you see, play darts. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he lay bets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. Nothing betting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he belong to any savings clubs, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 slate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  clubs or anything of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. I d
on't think at that time you see - that followed - in that time the clubs of that nature, no, there was no slate clubs or - I don't think there was a slate club then - in the village, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nor a doctor's club either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would you say you got on with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I think as a family we - we were very amiable and got on quite well. But even so - if - if there was trouble it was quick and there was a rough and tumble fight - because we could fight then - and we accepted that
. Yes, it was quite easy to - to drop into a storm of that nature, but the best of friends afterwards. I remember my - my brother with pigeons, I'd persuade him to try to come home, he'd been about - we've kept him about now for some little time but that 
- they went right away and immediately let mine out, so we lost all the pigeons.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did he let yours out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because - because he was so angry with me for persuading him to let his go. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was revenge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there one brother you think you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, my younger brother. Reg. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that - you see, the war came and - we went into the war which I - you know - got hard and settled down to but the moment 
I had a letter to say that Reg was in the Army I was quite distraught - distraught - or quite distressed about it. That was me to - I was really quite hurt - terrified what might happen to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get on with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course they were quite young and - devoted yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were a child did you play with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, we played games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you play with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 Well Ivy of course, she was too young - only two and a half I t
hink it was when she died and - we were always taking her out you know with the old pram. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
It was a - it was a pram that we used for carrying wood you know - we'd push round the fields and - and a dry stick in the hedge you know - take home. 'Cos it was a p
roblem in - during the death of the country you were without firewood and seeing that one used coal in those days, always got to get a continuous supply of dry wood for lighting the fire and it became very difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you play with anybody else as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - there were the boys next door. And the girls next door - used to play a sort of a - impromptu cricket you know, rough willow bat we used to make and cut out and shape out. With a wooden ball which we'd managed to get - save from the f
air - keeping a watchful eye and taken when it was convenient and it was quite a trill you see to get in possession of something like that. Then of course we spent a lot of our time - out in the fields just roaming around into say - oh I suppose all sorts
 of mischief. Bird catching. Spent a lot of time in the summer catching bullfinches and - and linnets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you catch them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well we caught them - what we called a trap cage. That was the bird in the - the bird that wouldn't - you'd already got
 tame in the lower part of the cage. The upper part was a - a - opened at the top with a spring with a thistle on a little trap thing and of course the - the wild birds was attracted to the one that was whistling in the cage, eventually they'd probably co
me along - look inside - have a - have a pick at the thistle, down'd go the trap cage and they were shut in. It was a barbarous thing to do I suppose - not at that time but now I realize it was quite wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do with the one you'd caught then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 We'd take it home. Take it home and put it in with the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't kill them or sell them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. Because you see you - a goldfinch is a beautiful bird to whistle. Yes. And the linnet to a lesser degree. And bullfinches -
 we'd catch bullfinch - you catch a bullfinch by -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 throwing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 - in the autumn time along the hedgerow and making all types of noises going that side - one that - eventually you startle and frighten the bird, you put your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  in and take it out. That's a terrible thing to do. But - you see at that time, question of cruelty, I don't think it entered our minds very much. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you play in your own garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, no - that would - no, we much preferred to get out into the fields, not in
 the garden because we were likely to be spotted and get into trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you play in the lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes, we played games there. We play with spinning tops - that was a great game that time. Peg tops, the one you used - wound round and round
 with string and threw it - continued - it spins for quite a long time. Then you had the humming top which you - you drew round, you had your string and round and round and round, you had your stick and just released it then you got it spinning, perhaps a
 bit of white paper with nice marks on the top and you - you use your whip, you now, you kept it going 'til you got a him, and it was quite a thrill - that was most interesting. And then there was the peg top. The one that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - you released and hit and oh you - that'd perhaps go for ten yards or more. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you make them yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, you'd buy them a ha'penny - a ha'penny a time. That was all the rage at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about playing indoors - did you ever play in your home or in other people's homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No, I - I can't think of any game that really had it indoors. It would be rather difficult to play indoors when we - were at home as a family we'd be - you know - some'd be going out and - no, I don't think we ever settled down to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about in really rough weather - bad weather - what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - rough weather - oh, we'd be out and about and - all types of weather, it made little difference to us. We were used to it you see and therefore - we a
ccepted anything that came along. Even going to school it could be just coming down in torrents, we'd just trudge off. Then to be - go to school and be wet through was a little concern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you free to play with whoever you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your parents didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. That - well, that wouldn't happen you see as far as parents was concerned. They wouldn't know.
 We were out, say from early morning especially holiday times to quite evening time. It was no concern - there's no qualms as to I wonder what's happened to that boy. It was accepted and taken for granted that we'd come back all right. Come back in a most
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 dishevelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  state. But - no, - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 qualms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - no punishment.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Not in a sense that you'd call organized but belonged to a cricket club and most enthusiastic about that. We had a cricket club and worked really 
hard. There was me and another lad, we - we got a formation of a cricket club and we got this going and that entailed endless - endless work because as you know the village is very, very scattered and - romping all over the village on an old bicycle and v
e
ry often that was almost unusable. I think I mentioned before where we used to let the tyre - where the inner tube was blown out the top, let the tyre down and put some very strong string round, keep it taut and close together, then blow the tyre up, to k
eep the string tight and it would keep the - inner tube in place say for a day or so. Well of course that was without using brakes when we wasn't concerned much about using brakes at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you organized this with this other chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you play teams from other villages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were the boys who belonged to this - were they all classes or what sort of type of boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I think mostly yes, much of the same working class you know. And then - course - 
the Eynsham Hall cricket club we then had the formation of a - of a second eleven and eventually few of us graduated to - the first eleven. And the first eleven was made up of - of - doctors - farmers - and people of that - came renown. And - personally I
 
- I became member of the first eleven - not at all happy in a select body, much preferring to remain with my second eleven team. It was very difficult to - to - and rather embarrassing too because I wasn't in a position to - to join the - expensive way of
 living then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you tell me what things you found about being with them embarrassing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well yes. When they went for a drink and - to - spend money. It was a question then of - of relying on charity. That's the most difficult thing of all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What exactly do you mean, relying on charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - you're not buying a drink and - you're - you're - people realize that you're not and - have a drink Bill, see. Yes. - But you can't return the compliment. And one doesn't feel like accepting in the 
first instance. One can do no less than just accept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This first eleven was at Eynsham Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Eynsham Hall, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But the second eleven was your own team was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, well, yes, in the first instance - yes. But then we were accepted - as
 a - a part of the first team. We were second eleven of the first team then, sort of thing. But in the early stages, yes, we did have what we called a - a - not in the sense it could be an organized thing but we made up a village team, we would play the g
a
me not with really good cricket bats but as I say home made bats and the best balls that we could get. We'd make up the stumps out of - out of nut tree you know which grows straight and you get that all right. We'd even make bails to fit along the top. An
d of course it was - it was the preliminary to having the idea of - getting an organized club. Which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the question of cricketing clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, that didn't - oh no. Well of course that was out of the question, one - at that time ther
e was not sufficient money to - pay for cricketing clothes. There's quite a number in that time if I remember never had cricketing clothes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the first eleven too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the first eleven too. I remember my brother Reg playing - and playing agains
t we played college teams, used to be Exeter College Busters, Christchurch Wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 rriors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
, I remember - yes, we played at these games and I remember my younger brother - great good bowler and - he was just playing in the ordinary clothes and the college people was most interested and wanted to buy him clothes, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he say to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He said, yes, all right. I think he had it too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was the Christchurch team called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Christchurch }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 Warriors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 . Warri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 rs. Yes. Then there was Ex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 
e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 ter College Busters. Yes, I remember, yes, that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Tell me how you found these people and how they talked to you when you met them socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - well seldom we ever got in conversation with them. I - that time I suppose one realized it was ra
ther difficult and under the situation - you realized your own capabilities and the position that you were in. It - it was always that inferior - inferior complex you know that - you didn't associate you just - normally played the game and you was - more 
or less felt that you was definitely on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you quite on your own socially then in the first eleven the time you were in there or were there other boys of a similar station?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well yes, to be fair, I think it was - one was accepted and -
 you realized that you really didn't belong to them and I'm not decrying the people I played with. Yes. Yes, but my point of view, I realized that there was - such an extreme that rather puzzled and bewildered about it all. Course it was quite unnecessary
. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 
I know to - two friends of mine I played cricket with quite a lot and they were in a good position, they were extraordinarily good and they realized the position I was in and they did everything to entice me to - to associate with 'em and to knock about w
ith them you know, but then again, I hadn't the willpower to meet the people that they were meeting.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What position were these two people in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - one was a farmer's son and - one belonged to a confidential clerk and secretary, you see. And the
y were really in reasonable positions and their acquaintances were of that make up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get to know them in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 By playing games. Cricket. And my general interest in - in life in the village. You see, and that led to lots of
 difficulties for me really because I remember this was following the war when it was a question of - I think of I may go on, previous to this memorial - there was - we had - we'd come back, we'd not been recognized in any way in the village and - a few o
f
 us got together and I suggested that we got something up on our own. For instance, we'd get a band from Witney to parade the village. Which we did. We subscribed - hard work to subscribe anything at that time of day, short of money - but even so we did. 
W
e collected enough money to pay for the band and we paraded the village. We went down past the vicarage and I'm sorry for the clergyman because he was quite honest good man but no one had done anything for us really so I suppose we did this. And possibly 
it was a preliminary to the question then of - having a memorial that they'd taken that into consideration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was after that that the question of the memorial came up was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any pets besides these birds you used to catch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What pets did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Rabbits. And pigeons. And an owl. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get the owl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - got the owl - it came about in this way. My father was in the woods - Eynsham Hall and there - what we would call 
a tread basket that time of day, weave sort of thing you know and - when my mother went to pick father's dinner for the next day, she opened the bag - found this owl was there. She was scared stiff over this. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 You know, someone had place it in mischief you know in father's bag and so we put it in a cage and kept it for - not for very long. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
You know what happened? Well we fed it on worms and - and of course it just simply devoured the worms almost Wholesale and it brought about the early demise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any collections of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say you had any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I think our chief hobby was - well in regard to sport, cricket and football you know. Tennis - ball - any ball we could get hold of - wooden ball it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you play tennis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - I can't say that we really - played tennis in a way - we'd play with this rough stick you know, bat - one that was more }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 flat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  you know but not in a way that you'd play tennis I suppose it was just a - t
aking a pattern - there was such a thing as tennis played and we did the next best thing to - to copy. We played another little game we called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid677048\charrsid5840491 tippet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 . That was with a - you get a - stick we say about - something about that long, taper it off at each end, y
ou have another stick of course - you'd have a little ring with this one in. You have another ring farther ahead and you just tip the end of it like that, chuck it over, you know what I mean, up in the air a little bit then you just - tap it along to wher
e you wanted it to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you would tap this stick which was about two to three inches long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 With another stick of the same length?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And of course the end of the little one you'd taper off - each end, so that wh
en you hit the end like you spring it up in the air and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And when it spun in the air you would hit it in the air?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And would you aim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, we'd aim at a particular place we'd make a little chalk mark, see you could drive it into that chalk mark - into the ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you compete against each other doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. Just a - 'course we'd play this and play pretty rough - well see how far we could knock it - and - that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes. We'd do - of course, yes, at that time. I remember always helping my father in the garden or on the allotment. I think I mentioned that to you before didn't I.
\par 
