 on the ground, you know, long streaky - one day he was - he did it up in a little bundle and I was very curious as to what - the reason for this and I said, what's that for d
ad? And he said, well, he says, you get me as much of it as you possibly can and I'll know what - I'll find use for this. Which I was foolish enough to do - later on I did collect the stuff. And - took it home. And then sometime afterwards I found out fro
m
 another man - he was collecting the stuff and just throwing it away. And I said but my daddy collected this. He was a rather a dry type of man you know but even so he says, for what reason? I said, he told me he'd got a good purpose and he told me to bri
ng it all home. But he was quite amused over this because he realized my father's idea was to get rid of all the s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
itch that was on the land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What exactly is squitch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It - it's a long type of grass you know that grows in the ground and spreads a
ll over the allotment eventually you know. But it's ease - really easy to extract because it's long streaky stuff you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was his sort of humour was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh his sense of humour - nice sense of humour, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any rivers near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Reverend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Evenlode but that would be about two mile away, but then that was a short distance as far as we were concerned in those days. 'Cos we'd - 'course - we'd go - a fair distance was nothi
ng really. We'd travel from early morning 'til night, even - impoverished conditions such as they were I suppose we got really hard and tough but - it was part of our life really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about going for walks for the sake of a walk - did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, we'd go into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Woodlands}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 , into - into parts I suppose was hardly ever used. Any - the rougher and tougher it was and - say thorns or into entanglements, yes. Out of curiosity - exploring - all sorts of places. We even - places too difficult 
- big walls or anything, we had - nails in the wall which we managed to put in, we'd know - locate the spot - we would climb up and get over quite - height places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. We - then at that time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Russian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Todd bicycles. Yes. But even so - yes, that was the question of the blown up tires then but then there was the hard tyres - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 solid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  tyres and sit on it was quite a bump bump bump. And the roads at that time of course you know, very, very rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What age were you when you started riding a bike?
