{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  bicycle. Wheels loose - I can't - I can't honestly say how I got it. But I know it was of very little use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had you started working by the time you got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When I was thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever go to anything like a theatre or a concert - did anything like that ever come to the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Oh no, I think there was on one or two occasions there was a - trying to think of the Chipperfields show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The - the - Chipperfields now they follow these St - St Giles's fair which they've grown into a big thing as you kno
w. Nothing is - everything becomes - becomes more life or more decadent. This apparently has become more life because as I say it was small concern. I remember it once visiting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - that would be about 19 - possibly 19 - about 19 - 1914 - 1912 I wo
uld think and - there was a cinema show and a bit of a variety and - competition - a prize of a pig eight weeks old. This was for a man that could sing a song and hold the pig under his arm at the same time. And one man from the village named - Bartley he
 was - he succeeded and he won a prize.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you compete?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, I was too young that time and this was a big bulky man - very powerful man. Yes, quite strong and capable. 'Course these songs at that time were very old - I remember quite a lot of 
songs then. Some of them are not very nice, some of them are quite good songs. Can't think of some of them now but - what - one was a sentimental one - what's the reason mother, I can't see that you, I often wonder what you're like, I know you're kind and
 
true. Father says God's will be done and if to him I pray will he give me sight and let me see your face and light of day. And - some of the village people could sing really quite good you know. And they - they'd sing these very old songs and some of them
 very old and some of them very nice, some of them not so nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What other occasions would they sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Not on any particular occasion but - just as - just as the situation warranted. Yes. And - without a sense of - priority which I say - might sin
g a nice sentimental song and another song not quite so good. I don't think we realized that time of day or sensed a thing in the way we would at the present time. We didn't sense a thing in those days as we would at the present moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Sense what sort of thing do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well such as a - it may be a sentimental song and be sung with great - feeling you know, but even so or another song would be just the opposite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were some of them rather improper crude songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes, very crude songs, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would they sing those in front of women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes. Because I think taste at that time was rather - not in the way we are at the present moment, we talk about things that it's necessary to talk about and openly which is 
I think quite proper but at that time - yes, but at that time it was done more in whispers. One didn't talk openly of things which was - I think are vital and tremendous importance, especially to youngsters starting out on life. I'll always remember my mo
t
her - talking to me to be very careful, and don't get mixed up with bad people. Because I - I wasn't really interested in girls at that time. For some reason that I shall never know they may possibly have been interested in me but instead of - mother's ta
l
king quite openly and frankly - 'course it was undreamt of. I always remember in conversation my mother would be talking probably to the next door neighbour - now it's time you boys went out to play. And I rather ascertained that time the subject was some
thing not to be known by me. In the - the contrast with parents and youngsters at that day was - so extreme that the mothers not realizing or understanding their children, never giving them credit that they were thinking, and thinking deeply and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 puzzled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and bewildered over things, it was an accepted thing to do - you mustn't talk about these things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When your two younger sisters were born did you know then were babies came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I - I - I - I questioned then, no. I - of course - under a goose
berry bush and all this sort of - thing, became absolutely taboo to me when I was about - twelve, yes, that time I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You knew when you were about twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, because I read papers - I read the News of the World which war rather a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Revealing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were about seven or eight when Ivy and Winifred were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't know then how they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. I certainly - no, oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What happened then at the confinement - where were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That is rather hard to sort of work out. Well surely I was around about at that time - we never went - what happened I wouldn't know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know if perhaps you went to a relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so. No. Oh n
o, because you see - you never had a nurse at that time of day, you had a midwife. It was - someone local in the village. 'Course the doctor - if there was a question of a doctor we had one at Hensham, that was about three and a half mile away. So the - n
o, it wasn't a question of having a doctor. The midwife - midwifery at that time of day was question of - of a local - someone that you knew in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who was experienced?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well not necessarily experienced - but had had experience but not anything in the way of being a - an accomplished person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On this question of taboo subjects, do you remember girls getting into trouble and this being talked about when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. I remember a friend of mine - who - girl cam
e into service in the village. She was about fifteen. She got into trouble. But - they married. And they lived quite a happy life I think - quite satisfactory. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 
Anyhow I know it happened with another friend of mine - a girl from another village, she got into trouble and I know this friend of mine he was - he was quite worried how he could avoid - the expense or the worry. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Then the mother of the girl paid him a visit. But that was his great concern - how he could avoid all the - things he was involving in. Bu
t eventually he got into the Army and - this girl got married - wrote him a very nice letter which he showed me and he was highly amused - delighted the thing was over. He wasn't the slightest bit concerned. About the girl.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the problem at 
the time of the very large families - did people talk about they wished they didn't have children do you think or planning their families at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, they - it wasn't a question of talking about that, it was - the only thing then was - what are we
 going to do to provide for them. Of course that was recognized and so obvious that we were - that we were unwanted in the first instance. It thought - it didn't occur to say oh I wish we could have avoided this. It was just a question of - of carrying on
. Yes. That was the tragedy I think was that so many of us of my age came into this world unwanted. But - the great -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember people actually talking about that when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No, you see, because people never - it's only 
few people ever came to realization of - that big families could be avoided - their education and knowledge - was beyond their comprehension. Of a period that was safe or anything like that it - even to most intelligent women even so didn't occur to them.
 
We lived in an age then of - almost unbelievable ignorance. In the things that one did believe in - believe in to such an extent that it became - an obsession, say in regard to religion, Christianity. People were obsessed with a - a certain form of religi
o
n. I remember - being with my grandmother at a very early age when the sisters of Mercy at Freeland paid her a visit, perhaps - possibly brought a little soup or something midday and my mother - my grandmother, being a chapel woman, that time - and the - 
a great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 persuasion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 to persuade granny to come and accept the Church of England faith and I remember my granny telling this sister of Mercy - I can enter on my own closet and pray to my Father in heaven. And the sister telling grandmother that if she didn't 
come to church she'd be - she'd be shut out of heaven. And that - and - no - unquestionably was said with the greatest sincerity and the greatest belief. Yes. It's so true those days you see. And I was - as a youngster the question of hell fire was terrif
ied. I - I - I believed that - sincerely believed it that we'd be burnt in hell fire and a continual - continuous process of torture and I think quite a - many of my age believed in that. Yes. Horrified and terrified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember people being turned out of doors because and unmarried girl had a child in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. I don't think that happened so much as it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 does}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  in this present day and age because they were very, very strict parents were then in the guidance of their - of the children. 
And - I think the conversation I think on sex was rarely spoken about. I say, at school - thirteen, fourteen or so on but in factory life yes. At an early age girls going to Witney factories for a number - of course I knew quite a lot of them - and - at t
h
at - strenuous work - say, I think it was from eight o'clock in the morning 'til six at night, and of course the very nature of the work and the long hours they developed at a very early stage - factory girls did - and of course the conversation then used
 
to run more or less on a looser line so that was ; that was one thing I believe that - but then - the older women in the factory brought up in a staid way and accepting certain principles in life that I believe held - held the younger ones more or less to
gether. I know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean they imposed their views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Their - ideas, and their ideas on - on the younger ones you know. But - so that it became more or less a craft and a cunning you know, in the factory. That was a thing as I think about today tha
t I don't like. It wasn't really a craft I think as a - a wonderful thing if it's used to the right sense, you see, but then at that time there was a craft in existence. A craft that you outwitted the other person for something that you wanted and was nec
essary that you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say these girls in the factory developed a craft and a cunning, can you give me an example of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, yes, it was the way - only example I can give is to say that they knew they knew in a shrewd type of way - wha
t could possibly happen to them - and the great - the plan for discipline probably over awed them. That they - they maintained a - a - a way of life which - which - was more or less held in a groove I not as it is today where elasticity can - principles o
r things are allowed and people - they have something where they can go I mean, if a girl gets into trouble today they - they're provided for and they're looked after, if not by the parents - by society. But at that time of course you became an outcast.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you think these girls realized it wasn't worthwhile taking the risk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's what happened I think at that time, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember anybody at that time playing rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Mouth organs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I mean rough music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh 
yes. Yes. Oh yes, that has happened - I do remember it 'cos that was - yes - 'cos that was with old kettles and drums or old tins, anything - yes. Do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What occasion do you remember this happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I can't remember any one 
per - I do remember this has happened in the village but I wouldn't like to say I remember anyone in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You don't remember what the offence was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember an effigy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Sometimes an effigy was made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, of course, yes. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your father's mother would sometimes give you a penny or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 tuppence}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your own parents ever give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. It was a question more or less of father'd want to borrow a penny o
r an ha'penny to make up something you know. So - oh no, never a question of saving - if - to run an errand for father or mother - and bless mother - no, it was never a question of having anything back. That was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He actually used to borrow from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, he - yes, if it was a question of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it borrowing or was he just asking for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, it was borrowing but - the question of whether you got it back was another - never happened, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that before you were earning regular money that he'd take a penny from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes. Yes. Of course a schoolboy I mean, you'd pick up a ha'penny here and a ha'penny there for doing an errand - at school - go for an errand for the school - master - get a ha'penny. Not always, but you we
re pleased when you got a ha'penny. Oh yes, that happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember anybody helping your mother with her house and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about your grandparents - did they help her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - yes - on - father's side. But
 - not on mother's side because - it was - no, she was in poverty street too. But father's - my grandmother, father's mother used to - she - no help - she'd help father, you know, a little I suppose. In extremities but - you know - but not - I don't think
 
that - very seldom because I know we were always in difficulties and in regard to finance - in regard to paying the - the grocer which he came - I told you before - once a month. There was - kind of settle up with him. I - quite a routine of forty pound o
f sugar and so much tea and so on automatically went down you know and mother'd check and say, no, oh he said, that's all right. And - always believing that he'd get his money some time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean she often couldn't pay the whole bill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Often could
n't pay. Or it's a question of the baker - not paying the baker. Baker'd come up on the - on the Tuesday with the eight small loaves - we used to have cottage loaves you know those days, you know, with the tops, yes. A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Cheltenham's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  a large one, that was a 
big one you know, but more or less a cottage - when I was round eight and nine, you know, that'd do for a couple of days. Then there was the question of paying the baker and that was a - always a debateable point as to when he would be paid and mother and
 father'd be - you know - so mother would say, I've got this to pay and this and that to pay. And the baker to pay for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 barley meal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  for the pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She wasn't ever called up by anybody for debt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did anybody come in and actually help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. No. No question of any help whatsoever - it was a just a question of - of carrying on to best of one's ability. I think that followed with our family or with people in the village. No one knew what was happening in a 
village of the size of Northleigh at that time one could sit down and imagine all the way through the village what was going on in that village in regard to - to poverty and distress. And the stresses of life was very severe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So when Ivy and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Winifred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  were born how did she manage - you said she'd have a local woman in to come and help with the birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's true - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she stay in bed after that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, yes, just for the time that was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would she manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - of course - we had a neighbour - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  neighbour - and the next door neighbours would be, what - well there was another house about two hundred yards away and the next house }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 would}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  be a quarter of a mile away. But the one two hundred yards away was the woman that was getting on in years and wouldn't be - able to come, but the next door neighbour, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she used to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She used to help, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know if your mother paid her anything for helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh was bound to be - question of paying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Be a business proposition.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother go and help anybody herself at a birth do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, I can never remember mother going. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 she saw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  her own mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
That would be about - once in say - a month. I do remember granny Merry from Freeland which would be say two and a half mile away, would pay a visit to my mother. And that would be perhaps once in six months. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was your mother's mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Mother - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She would come about once in six months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Remember the time when they were the widow's bonnet at that time. And dear old lady, she - she come gasping up the - and tumble into a chair and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Polly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  s
he said, I'll never be able to get up there again and I shall have to stop the night you know. And mother - oh that's quite all right mum. Mother'd already told us, when granny comes she'll want to stop the night but she'll go back. And so - and it was qu
ite true. After a rest granny says, shall have to get back. And she would go back that night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why would she always say that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - well - well because she would be tired when she got - arrived - in those days you see, and feel quite
 exhausted and quite incapable of getting back but - revival you know following after a sit down for some time and then the - question of - of getting back to - probably get her butter or something the next day, as people - strode up with all sorts of ide
a
s. Granny would be of that make-up you see, and therefore she'd have to get back because her mind as so filled with the stress and strain of life - of living you know and the continuation of it and being with her in a talkative way - retiring to the littl
e - little kitchen, oh yes, but then I must go down and get my butter tonight. If I leave it later on it'll be too hot. If I go down early in the morning and so and so on. That was the question of life you see such as it was lived at that time
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then the other times would your mother go to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, pay a visit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When your granny came would she be offered anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would she have a meal with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, no, just - it would be 
question of say - cup of tea or a - butter - bread and butter or cake or maybe a homemade cake, mother'd make a homemade cake. You see, just a little of this. Oh no, it'd be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When your mother went to her would she have similar food and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Just a - just something that was - available at the time. But you see, nothing organized in those days. In the sense of organization.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there other relatives who would call round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - yes, I think as relatives we met more often then in those days than we do at the present time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were the other relatives who lived near you who you used to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well there's aunties and uncles you know. And - they - you see, they'd naturally call, not in a sense that they'd call to see you or pay 
you a visit but it was an accepted thing that relatives just met in that way. Well I - I called to see how you're getting on. No, no, it wouldn't be a question of that. It was just a question that they'd just call in. Wasn't done in that sense as we - you
 know, it's nice for someone to say, well must come and see you - I'm so glad that I've come to see you and seen that you're al right. I don't think we met in those days in that sense.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many aunts did you have round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had - two aunts and - on father's side - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And any uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well, uncles, yes. They were on - on mother's side. Yes. I think - yes, they were rather nice uncles you know. Quite - good. Genteel, amiable - loveable sort of characters you know. Those that woul
d have a little packet of sweets and with a childish delight just one here and one there sort of - so that I had one sprinkled out in that way. You'd get a real kick out of it. There was something lovely I think at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. No. No, I don't think that was an associ - everyone was more or less - someone that you knew. You knew everyone in the village. You either just mixed with them or passed the time of day but - as to have friends, I don't th
ink you could everyone more or less a - a neighbour or you were associated with certain people or you didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was the term friend used at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Friends? Well - no, I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the neighbours come into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Well we had a neighbour then at that time - our next door neighbour then, I wasn't showed enough but - the boy, we played cricket before we went to school. And - if the ball was knocked under the back window he'd say get it. Well I'm sorry to say tha
t things went on very wrong you know. Things was pilfered out of - doors. Things were pilfered out of doors. Yes. Yes. Get me out of the way you see and mother wouldn't be up and I was up rather early, say - about quarter past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What things would he take then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - sugar. We had a twenty pound packet of sugar you know - sink a cup in - slip out of doors with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother find out about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, she knew. Because the - see this woman looking out of the corner of the window one morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean the woman connived at this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That wasn't a neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, she - yes, that was the neighbour -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that the neighbour who helped your mother at the birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Same one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. 
Yes. Now she was a very strict disciplinarian with the children and - extraordinarily clean woman, very tall - and - athletic type I should imagine, but - I think the children's fed properly, looked after well, but in regard to discipline it went to the e
x
treme. Unmercifully thrashed for any - any demeanour whatsoever - a friend - from the boy was about my age, a friend from him would solicit punishment but you'll go and do whatever I've told you and then I'll deal with you when you come back. He would be 
punished when he came back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But he wouldn't be punished for taking the sugar would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh he wouldn't take the sugar - his mother would take the sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When your mother found out about this what steps did she take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well she would do nothing about it - only to be careful and not leave things about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She didn't say anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Be useless to say anything. You couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why, you couldn't take action, you couldn't summons the woman for doing it, you wouldn't be 
in a position to do it. To raise an argument about it wouldn't help. So the thing was best left, knowing what had happened, to be very careful, to try to avoid it in future.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she have any neighbour that she could confide in or be close to in a friendly way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I think that was - no. No, there was no one really that one could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Did neighbours ever come in a way like relatives did and have a cup of tea and cake?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. You see, if - living in a - in a - in a lane such as we lived
 in there was only just two or three close at hand and the next was a quarter of a mile away, a little small farm, you know, that were - so you wouldn't have any neighbour that you could confide in and mother's problems was her own problems which she cont
i
nually ploughed over I suppose in her mind - tragedy of it all was you see that there was no one she could confide in or talk to. I - there was one - clergyman from Freeland that pay visits from Freeland into the Northleigh village. Mother'd attend Freela
n
d church and he was most helpful I think, I do remember him quite as a youngster, I expect I'd be about ten - paying visits. I remember this very clearly opening the cape when he was leaving and putting a shilling in my hand, you imagine a shilling at tha
t
 time was tremendous thing and - patting me on the head and going away and of course a shilling - you know what I done with that? Took it to mother because that's where he - it was intended that way, I know that. Of course I give it to mother. Things I al
ways remember because it so stands out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that the same clergyman who laughed when you took an apple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, it wasn't the same man. Very - typical of a type of man - such a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Your mother herself didn't call in on neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember her getting together with a group of relatives or neighbours for any kind of entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. I don't - nothing in that light whatsoever. There was no question of a - of doing anything other than was - on the spur
 of the moment - something had happened. Nothing deeply set out or organized. Life was - on - on such a level then that it was - come day, go day, and what happened just happened. You never had anything that was - ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would a social get together take places?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No. You see, I - I remember the - I remember the women or men getting together - with never any sustained debate or - or questions you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What would they do when they did get together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - all the conversation'd ru
n at random in utter confusion you know. There's no sustained - argument of anything. It was - it's surprising really - I remember as a boy working with a group of men the conversation they got onto gardening onto anything then in two minutes it'd be leap
t from one subject to another. And then of course - one fellow would raise an argument, the other fellow raise one and the conversation would just simply drift into no mans land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think that your mother talked over with your father her worries about the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Yes, of course that was - that was always a - a bone of}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 contention because father wouldn't particularly want to listen - he'd know already. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But then of course one must spill their - feelings and - and that - and mother would d
o that you see. Then she would do that with us. Try to explain - what would happen and what - and what she - what could be done about it. 'Course I'd always end up more or less in despair and I don't know. See? That was - you see, I - I apply this to my f
a
mily, this must be going on with countless families in the village at that time. One can only get an idea from the - the - the children that went to school with you that they were more or less in the same level as you - they were dressed more or less like
 you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They were very much the same were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any families that you felt were worse off than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Possibly, yes, there were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And some were better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Some - some were not - perhaps not quite even s
o - might have been slightly better off but not perhaps looked after quite so well as we were - we were always - apparently clean you know, clean and very careful haircuts and being kept tidy in that sense - tidy as it was possible to make us. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother cut your hair herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes, oh yes. Quite true. And that was - that was rough because the scissors never always cut properly and the comb got tangled up sometimes you know because you - I mean one could comb - comb your hair out an
d all the rest of it but of course we play with all sorts of mud pies and anything could happen you see. Your hair got sticky. Rough and tumble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At that time how would you divide the society where you lived into social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Of course the soc
ial classes then - there was only two classes. Those that had and those who - had not. And so of course the greatest homage and respect was paid to those people that had and to the ones that you belonged to or thought you belonged to you just accept them 
a
s they were and you just mixed with them. But the - there - there was the two extremes - there was the two worlds. You were in a world that was separated from the other world. Puzzled and bewildered perhaps often realizing the fruits of the earth was ther
e
 but not for you to pick. But that was accepted because the other people had control of it and you couldn't visualize that that was part and parcel of your heritage. If one could only have organized it - we've already talked about organization - if we cou
ld have organized at that time of day - we would have - had explanations and had sufficient intelligence to see that that this was a part of our inheritance. But, no, we didn't know and realize that that could be. We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the group of those that had were there divisions among them - who were the sort of people that belonged to that group?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. Yes. With those people - with the upper classes and the middle classes and the middle classes was - was moving always towards that time that's where t
hey could reach that height if possibly, but quite - the upper classes who accepted with the middle classes - and the lower classes was accepted as the slaves into a system that evolved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did the upper classes think of the middle classes in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh well that was part of the heritage they were accepted - quite easily, yes, but - with the upper classes. As a party holding - holding allegiance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Squire Mason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was at Eynsham Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who were the other people in the upper class round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - I - I don't think of anyone really at that time. He was the Squire and of course Woodstock was the Duke of Marlborough. There was the power and the influence. Such an influence - that was accepted a
s a - as a law. If I give you an instance, I remember Northleigh common one morning being set ablaze. I knew who done it but me and my young brother - we were attracted to the fire and making our way close to it when who should jump out of a car but the }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Honourable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 Parker, he was a - a friend of Mason's and lived at Eynsham Hall. Why did you set fire to this. We didn't set fire to it. Now then, come along, you set fire to this common. No. We didn't set fire to it. And I - so we went on. Eventually he left us
 but next day a policeman called at our place. Now, we did not set fire to this common but our name - policeman took our names and I suppose it was taken to Woodstock. We were not summoned but the powers that be assumed that we'd set fire to it. We'd no s
ay in the matter whatsoever, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Is this before you went into the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. You see, that - that's what happened in those days. You were - you were assumed to be guilty of something - you was never - never investigated to prove it was right. They'd taken the - so - they take - they took the law into their hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of people belonged to the middle class at Northleigh and round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - farmers, baker, butcher, such people as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What class was the clergyman in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well clergyman is - you remember at that time he was a class of his own - he was living - living as a recluse more or less. He never took any active part in the social life of the village. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the doctor what about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well the doctor 
he - he was two and half mile away - he was a doctor but - of course he'd pay his visits if you sent for him, otherwise he - you never see a doctor. If you was - if you had an ailment - of course you never - you never went to his surgery, that was too far
 away. But serious illness, yes of course, he was called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you brought up to treat some people differently from others then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well in - in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh 
yes, that was quite so. We did that sort of thing - that was more or less and understood - we realized or - yes, we did realize that - was such things as classes. And - and - in our own order it was quite easy to go about light but in meeting people of - 
what were considered then as the upper classes and middle classed is was very distinctive.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How were you supposed to behave to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well with - that due respect which they expected and - we accepted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember for example what forms this respect took - anything in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I suppose it was a question of - obedience and accepting what they said was - a - a thing could be done. In other words it was generally thought that - they knew best. Personally of course I didn't nev
er accept that sort of thing but it was the generally accepted - idea of village life - to the - to - to the - Squire and to the middle class, even on Sundays the working class would never been seen about at church time when the people of that order were 
attending church. Especially it was a wrong thing to be at work on the allotments. People -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say they wouldn't be seen around when those people were attending church, what exactly do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that I suppose was a respect to the people in - in power and authority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But wouldn\rquote t they go to church at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, those people that would go to church, yes, oh yes. The others wouldn't be hanging about in the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember your mother or other ladies curtseying to these people or was that not in your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I don't think my mother would do that sort of thing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you taught to touch your cap to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anyone you called Master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well no, of course the schoolmaster, that's the only thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You called him master did you or sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No - Sir - always Sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who else would you call Sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I think that would - no - generally I suppose 'd be the - the clergyman and - someone of higher aut
hority, such as - of course, Manson's, the people - what were considered authority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember anybody you would call madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anybody in the village who showed respect to your parents in the way you've been describing you showed respect to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I think 'course - from the business point of view, business people naturally, they would do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To - my parents. I think generally people would - with an ordinary order of respect yes, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 By business people do you mean the baker and people like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The butcher, the baker, and people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they show respect to your parents in that way - did they show respect to other people of your parent's s
tation in the same way as they did to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, I think so, yes. Yes. I think there was quite a - a good deal of understanding and sympathy with business people because there's always the question of - of debt - being indebted to the - to
 butcher and to the baker. And it was always a great problem with the butcher and the baker in regard to their money. But, as business - as business men they had to - keep an eye on the business and appear to be quite artless at times but - it was always 
a problematical thing in - in regard to business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It wasn't because your father had his own business that they treated him with respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. No. Wouldn't happen that way, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you come into contact before the end of the first world war with Squire Mason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, not actually, no, but indirectly I suppose I - I knew quite - quite a lot about them. As my - my wife, she was a guide at that time and - my interest and activities in the village were such that they became aware of my - my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 presence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
. In a discreet type of way - I remember working on Eynsham Hall Estate - it was breaking stones ready for the - the roadwork and - Lady - Lady - Lady - Evelyn Mason apparently knew of me because someone - was interested in what was happening in 
the village in regard to - a memorial. She sent someone out from the house to see me, would I take this gentleman - round the building in the afternoon. 'Course which I did but - and - that was one instance you see. And after that - Lady Evelyn Mason - se
nt a private - confidential clerk and secretary to see me with a view to learning the art of book keeping and to further my education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that before the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was - that was the end of the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you'd just got back from the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. But - that - I could not possibly accept because - I'd suffered from shell shock and I was in a state at that time - coo, it was inconceivable that I could carry on with anything to do - I just - idled around so that it really never happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you on the parish council at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was I? No. Not 'til later on - I went - I got on the parish council then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why do you think she sent that clerk round - what was if particularly about you that made her think - know about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I think my association with - things that was moving at that time - the memorial probably had quite a lot to do with it. Then there was the fellow - the agent for the land - for the land worker - for agricultural work
ers - I got in contact with and I was going round the village with the - with the land worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was this a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was a trade union, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was the name of the union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The agricultural trade union. A man named Mr Bond, he 
was a very, very sincere man, he was the - conscientious objector during the war but I learnt that he had life saving medals but he - I remember him with tears in his eyes when he was telling me about this sort of thing but - I remember it was a wt and ve
ry - very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 wintry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 night and - could I tell him where the Mason's Arms was. I said, yes, as a matter of fact, I'll take you there. And he told me his mission and it was to promote agricultural trade - union in the village and I remember the gathering in the p
ublic house. Then - the fellows there were quite sympathetic and - I tried to encourage him by - I would help and all the - any possible way I could. As I say I gave in regard to the distribution of the land worker. And I think from that that - Lady }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Evelyn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Mason}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 was interested in me - I suppose I must think that she was - possibly - trying to get me interested in other side of things. Perhaps from the Conservative point of view. I think so because - this gentleman - this - a man named Mr Gardner who was ver
y keen that I should drop certain ideas which I wasn't inclined to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was the clerk - Mr Gardner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Yes. Which I wasn't inclined to do and I - I - and I - mater of fact - I really do think that I was ostracized after that because I - life in the village then was very difficult for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After the memorial you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After the memorial. And then I got in contact with a gentleman of independent means from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 South Leigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and he examined me and tested me on different things and he stro
ngly recommended me then for the - what was going at that time, the Buxton Scholarship - Ruskin College. And - this was after the first world war - and - so I had this recommendation and I came to Oxford with a view to going to - to Ruskin to see Mr Smith
, I think he was the man then. And - he was a personal friend of - this gentleman. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 McGee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 I think the name was. Anyway - I came to Oxford, my brother was at carpenter on the corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Which brother was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Walter. And - he said, oh Bill, he s
ays, if I were you, he says, I wouldn't think about it. Why don't - I could get you a job on the corporation. And I hesitated in a very nervous state at that time, and that's what happened. I never went to Ruskin college to make this application. But -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He got you a job on the corporation you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. But I'm pretty positive that I would have got through because - this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 McGee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  was the name of this gentleman from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 South Leigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - Mr Smith then was great personal friend of his. And he'd already used his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 info}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 - his influence but I certainly never went and probably - on that ground I - I ought not to have went because it might have been influence at work that would possibly have got me - into this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Have you ever regretted that you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I - in many ways yes but - I don't think I was worthy of it at that time because I was in such an agitated state.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You might not have been able to take advantage of the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I doubt whether I could possibly have took advantage at tha
t time. I was completely broke down you see because - in the meantime, previous to coming to Oxford I'd - had a job on the estate with another friend - pal of mine, cutting a big hedge down on the estate and we were both near exhaustion. And I remember co
m
ing home one day when I collapsed and he said, what's the matter Bill? 'Cos he'd already missed me and he came back and - got me up and I said, what's the matter George? And he said, hah, he says, you - he says, you fell out. I said, ah well, perhaps it's
 
starvation George. Any rate, I says, when we gets home I must think about something. - So - following - the next day I never went to work, I went to see my doctor which was that two and a half mile away. He examined me thoroughly and he said, well Breaksp
e
are, he says, you're all to pieces - you're starved. He says, you'll have to pull yourself together. And - following that I - my brother took my job on for the time being. As time went on I suppose I - recovered in a way but - eventually I came to Oxford 
and - I suppose life got a little different then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After you got that job in oxford then you never went back to Northleigh?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I never went back to Northleigh. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That time when the doctor said you were starved - you were having to look after yourself were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Living with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I - I was - of course as I - I was at home and - my younger brother came out of the Army - believe I told you about him, and the one that was a prisoner of war. 'Cos he told m
e, he said - life - like that Bill, he says, you'll have to pull yourself together. I said, that's O.K. I said, we'll do that. This brother would talk in that way. Well then of course my younger brother came home and - I believe I told you I didn't recogn
i
ze him - I certainly didn't - but - we got moving on together and - existed, I can't say we lived because it was too difficult at that time. And father you see was earning no wage. He said, here you are, you boys, there's the house. He says, you must mana
ge the best you can. Fortunately for him as I say he could always - visit his sister at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 and he was - regards that he was comfortable in that respect. But life - life at home was - well - in such a way - state that - as boys I suppose we'd no sense of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 manoeuvring}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 for ourselves.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  We felt quite incapable you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Before the end of the war in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Northleigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  now, can you remember who the schoolmaster associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think he - 'course his association was more with the - with farmers an
d - an old man - in business - Turners - at Oxford they were - they were friends you see. Of course - in - I - I can imagine he was a man whose time was limited you know, but naturally enough his association was with people - over the same make-up as hims
elf. Highly difficult to be otherwise because association with - he - he'd mix - he mixed - he was associated with the school children, he knew the make-up of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 parent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - parental life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say he associated with the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who else did the farmers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well more or less with their own - brand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Other farmers you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I don't think they shifted very far away from their own - make-up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean other shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, well of course there was only - at that time in that - in the village was a small shop - only one shop. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were talking earlier about the butcher and the baker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where were you thinking of then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - well the butcher and the baker they were - associated with people of their own make-up. I - I think it - you know - it's just - it can never be otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In Northleigh there was a chapel wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. There was a chapel.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of people from the point of view of social class would you say went to the church and what to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh they assoc - the people that went to the chapel was quite in - working class people, very devout people, very ke
en - on revival meetings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any middle class people who went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No. Of course - yes - people from Witney - Erley's - blanket people, yes, they would - and of course then they didn't belong to the village but I think they assisted in the work of the - chapel, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Where you lived in Northleigh did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think so, i
n regard to - yes - the standard of living, yes. That was just a question of - as dependent on the work they did. But the agricultural workers where his wages was twelve shillings - even on Eynsham Hall Estate was eleven shillings a week. They were paid o
n
ce a fortnight - the magnificent sum of twenty-two shillings. And even so - I well remember as a boy watching big able bodied men waiting for the farm bailiff to come along with a pony and trap and shaking his head before he go to them - to say there was 
nothing doing. So that - as regards - living - of standard of living was desperately low.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there some working class people in Northleigh who weren't in agricultural work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were they better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, they were better off. Yes, they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of jobs would they be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well they - they would be probably stonemasons and people of that - work of course, or carter, you know. Yes, well they was slightly in a better position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember a distinction made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no, I don't think so. No. Much of the same order - 'because they were more inclined - as - like a magnet to be drawn to - in association with the - with that order. One was pulled by a string al
most - that you belonged to a - a certain order or you belonged to that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say that they were pulled together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But do you think in the working class in Northleigh one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The craftsmen didn't feel themselves superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I don't think that happened that way, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you think that some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, yes, I think that was the case. Th
ere was that rough edge to - to life, to certain people more so than it was to us - others. There was others that was considered quite - respectable people, but - personally myself I accepted the majority of people in the village as - of one order. That's
 
slightly gone astray over owing to difficulties or more - some more - illiterate than others but generally I think all had a - a standard of life which - was - which was forced upon them. If there were difficulties in regard to petty thefts there was a di
re necessity such as probably - robbing a farmer of a - a - of wood from the hedges you know and that sort of thing. It was a struggle - then of course - struggle for existence was very, very severe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say that your mother and your father had the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, I think so. Father was very - very much up against anything that was - outside the law. He accepted the law as a - basic facto of - of life which I think was such a damnable lie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you t
hink your mother saw herself as belonging to a certain social class - did she think of herself as a working class woman do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, quite a - a - a person of - of a respectable - understanding, brought up in a - in a Christian way of life, 
always moving towards - a purposeful thing but never realizing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But do you think she thought of herself as a working class woman - a member of a class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I think my mother was exactly - a domesticated motherly type of person with - only one
 understanding - the struggle to make - maintain life in the home and everything else - was secondary importance and - and really truly never ever having any - awakening to - to the social disorders, this was a thing my mother was centralized on, keeping 
life moving within the family. Always struggling to get this and that. To maintenance of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think at that time it was possible, round where you lived, to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. I think that was - utterly impossible. You 
see, you were - you was in the mire and there was no such a thing as - as any organized method of - of eradicating yourself away from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember at that time any one being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I do remember it - in the village itself do you mean or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 If people at that time used that phrase what did they mean by it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, well - at that time I - I remember my mother often speaking of the Duchess of Marlborough - paying visits in a carriage round the 
district and - and trying to help people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 I only got a glimpse of that but I do remember - my mother telling me about the Duchess of Marlborough - at that time.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did she say about her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She thought she was a real good lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why do you think that was - because she helped people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because she was helping people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about real gentlemen - do you remember people using that term?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well yes, of course it - I do remember my mother talking about a clergyman at - Freeland. Because
 he was a - a - a real gentleman, I think I mentioned it to you, the man that always got that genial type of smile, that understood children, after Sunday school you played on the lawn and you just simply got a kick out of it with him. He - he really enjo
y
ed doing the things that was necessary. I think I mentioned that he came out of the parish to visit my mother when we lived at Northleigh which was rather infra dig to visit another village. But - and leaving the shilling when I opened the gate for him - 
and knew it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you gave it straight to your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes. Yes, and - you know, that - that was a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I remember you saying the police would give the boys a knock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you see the policeman around where you lived as a child a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, quite, yes. Yes he, especially at night time when we were out in the streets at night window tapping was a great game with us you know - you've heard of that. You get a needle - get a pin and a button and let
 it hang down and you get a piece of thread and move away to the road and then - backwards and forwards and it taps the window you know. And very often you'd get a severe rap across the backside and if you made enquiries, who was that, you'd get a second 
one. You didn't realize it was a policeman. We really did get hit hard you know. Oh yes. A box at the side of the ear, I've had that before now. You didn't go home and tell your parents because you'd probably get into more trouble at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother ever say to you, I'll call a policeman when you were a little boy when you were naughty or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No, we wouldn't be worried about that because we already - had come in contact with police so we knew quite a bit about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How do you think the policeman treated people in your village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They were always on the watch for - poachers, that sort of thing. They were very clever at that - game. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There was actually a Northleigh policeman was there - did he live in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he - I think that time he lived at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  but of course he paid a visit round the village. No, always trying to solicit information - you know - indirectly through youngsters such as myself probably but - being very wary I could - outwit the
m in regard to giving information. About the certain movements of men in the village. And of course the indirect approach could easily lead one to - give information against some fellow, you know, that you'd no intention - no intention of giving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 These men they were interested in - were these men engaged in petty crime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you actually knew about people in the village thieving and you would shelter then from the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I wouldn't say that - it was thieving - this was men in the village that - desperately - having to - to get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You felt sympathy for these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you would protect them form the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, I would help - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It's not like that now is it - nobody's driven to thieving now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was your home rented?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, we paid rent for that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was to the Duke of Marlborough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's - duke of Marlborough, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was his agent who called round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever see him himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I see him - when there was repairs being made at one time. I remember - back of the house was huge field and the cattle used to come right up to the window and - you know - how th
e cattle, shall I say blow, when they get interested or curious they used to smother the window you know and then at night my mother got rather concerned because they'd come - with the - with the - oil lamp you know, not very strong light but }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 flickered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  thr
ough the window, they'd be curious and come and make a noise and - my mother was - got rather concerned about it so the - eventually put up a fence, you know, protecting the back windows so they - couldn't come right - too close. 'Cos it was a bit -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the Duke put that up did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because your mother asked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you think about him then as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 landlord}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh we never had - came in contact with him really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But his general policy towards his tenants - what did you think of him as a landlord in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I don't think he was very, very interested - except if repairs were necessary they were done as in - in the case of - our house, were done. But I - apart from that I don't think he was interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was your father ever ill or out of work during your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, he was always a toiler, always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Always working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever get help up to end of the first world war - did your family ever get help from any charity
 - the guardians of the parish or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Could I ask you a bit about your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You weren't ever given lessons by your parents were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I was five when I first went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that the whole day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Be church school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And it was mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 We walked - yes, got to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well about quarter of an hour. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who went with you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I - I remember my two brothers at first day I went to school - I remember them
 taking me and I think I told you they - robbed me of my buttons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And after that did you go alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I went alone then. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They didn't go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, because you see before going to school at four years of age I would just simply get out in the fields and wander anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't set off from the home to school you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. The first day - they took me. But after that I was on - matter of indifference, I'd just simply go myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You went home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Very curious - very, very strange to me it was. I remember the little marbles that you moved backward - and forwards on a string you know - on a thing and counting and that sort of thing. I was ve
ry interested in that sort of business and - but I - I - I can't really remember too much about that. That - learning to count and to - to make letters and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Later on as you got older what did you think as school then? I think you mentioned to me you were always rather worried in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh I was always worried and perplexed in school I can - and I was always - very embarrassed because I seemed so stupid, I could never - sort of understand what was going on. I could never - I co
uld read - I could read very, very early - very - I think I - yes - I was very interested in things that I actually read and I - I could understand them, but I could never understand arithmetic. Very backward in all sorts of things. And yet within my own 
mind I was always struggling and puzzling things out, no one could tell me what - what I was thinking - I could never explain to people what I was trying to think about. But it all seemed so contradictory. I wanted to learn at school yet I couldn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Perhaps it was because you were so worried all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I was extremely worried about things. And I could - you can never - when you're young like that you can never tell people what you're thinking because they would laugh at you and that sort of thi
ng, my parents, I would never tell them - what I thought. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you feel about the teachers there - was there just the schoolmaster or did he have an assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The schoolmaster and his wife. And of course - other teachers. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you feel about them - do you remember whether you liked or disliked them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I - well I disliked the school master - I disliked his wife. But the - later on I realized that they were people that was extremely busy and - and worried. At the time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At the time you had no feeling of affection or liking for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. Not at all, no, no. No. Because of punishment re received you know, the cane. I mean you got to school and you was a bit late and - wintry weather, you know what can happen, 
you're hands are cold and - of course we didn't have gloves then, sometimes mittens, we called them mittens but they wasn't much use to us. Then you got the cane at school and your fingers was numbed and it was very painful business you see but - the scho
olmaster's law you see - he - it must be very, very hard for the schoolmaster to - I suppose it was things like - almost must become unbearable for him at times and for his wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In that way because - I suppose they'd - they'd used the cane - they'd use a cane for trivial things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Girls the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What other things besides being late would they used the cane for do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh for - of course disobedience and
 not paying attention. Yes. Go out and get the cane. I always remember we used to hold our fingers so as the cane would glide off you know sort of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any other punishments they gave besides the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes - lines. We called it - yes - fifty lines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, standing to the chalk mark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Having to stand up you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long were you kept standing for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, perhaps for five minutes. I remember on one occasion I got very angry about t
his and I shifted off and the master pushed me in the back and - I wouldn't stand at the line again. And so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I got the cane again for that. So many more lines to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that unusual for a boy to be defiant like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes. I think I got - when one got into a temper you know - some of the boys would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It sounds awful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It sounds as if he was very harsh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he wasn't - I don't think he was really. No, I don't think so really. 
And - his wife - I don't think she was really - but - it was for - I think now it was very, very difficult for them. You - and you as a family woman realize with children that it's - you've got your problems.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say you'd sit beside a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
 Who - who could readily do his work easily and I - I was trying desperately hard to do mine, working much harder than him, but just simply making - no success of it. Here was a question of a some - a teacher - trying to understand me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, I this - definitely yes. There's some children, yes, have much - better treatment. But possibly because they were more easy - easy to learn and the children that was backward got less attention - the very children that needed help had less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Which just reinforced their difficulties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, but I think that was the desperation of - of the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your parents }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 show}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  an interest in your work at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Very little time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did your mother or your father ever ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. I don't think my dad was a bit interested in - what we did at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you ever remember them visiting the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That wasn't so much the thing in those days was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. They never do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they ever meet the teachers on any occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course the village such as our
s was a - divided village - east end and north end and so there was always rivalry - always fights, and they were always between - the two halves of the village, you see, because we were separate, in that sense, separated, so much that - you see one - the
 Northleigh end would go and the East'd separate you see and then that was fight with stones. We'd throw stones and - yes. That would have a terrific bash at one another you know. And a stand up fight, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any children who were left out of things - isolated children at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. No. They generally find their own clan you know. With in school I suppose we mixed up with - it depends on age and - football - yes, we all mixed up together. There's always a question o
f - of playtime football with tennis ball, hard ball such as the fair people have you know for throwing coconuts. If we couldn't get that we'd get a tin and bash it up and make it as near - we - of course we - we'd kick our boots out in no time you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you go to another school after you left the Northleigh school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I went to the Freeland school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At what age was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I would be about - eleven - eleven - possibly eleven and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was when you went to live with your granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When I went to live with granny - that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was a church school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were living with your granny how did you get to school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I had only short distance to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And it took you about how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh - about three minutes. Of course I - I think I told you about that, I went to work in the early mornings to clean knives and forks at the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 home, supplementing my - and I had eighteenpence a week for that. And I had to go Saturday mornings - to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So From Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
you'd go to school would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I'd go to school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you go home to your granny for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - you see that was a completely new world to me because the children there was - was nurtured in the very devout - high church way of life and - I never been accustomed to that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why were the children different there do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Because it was more - hamlet at that time, very compact little place and the whole environment was - as I say - saturated with a - with a deep - persuasive Christian belief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was this the influence partly of the vicar do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, it would be and the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 and the Sunday schools and - everything appertaining to - to - jolly affair on Sunday afternoon with - with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 scrambling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  sweets and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It must have been a real change for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was a terrific chang
e, it was - so overwhelming I can never really understand - and I suppose the teacher found me rather a backward type of pupil because - I was very backward in most things I suppose. One think I - they were interested in was my - we'd call it then composi
tion. Writing you know. And - she showed it to the - to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 clergyman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 you know, what I used to write, and she asked me a good many questions, why I wrote that there - but I could give no explanation, it was just the way - and by the way, Northleigh, that wa
s sort of thing. I was very interested in anything - say writing about a horse - or what I met coming to school you see. Well, apparently I must have wrote completely different to other children. Why I don't know but I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You haven't got any of them still I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. And - and they were always - you know, I remember Mrs Pearson always take it home to her husband I wrote you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Mrs Pearson was the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Schoolmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Northleigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At the school at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Northleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, the next school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, Freeland. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you like that school or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - I disliked it really. I disliked it because it was - way of life that I wasn't accustomed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you feel about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well there was only one teacher. Well there was - yes, one. Mrs Gardner I always remember - she was the lady - when I left there, as I say I left when I was about twelve and a half, and she took me to the station, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  station. I
 always remember putting a carnation in my buttonhole so that the ladies at Reading platform would recognize me that I was the boy for - Helpses. That was the name of the people that I was going to at Sandhurst. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was to be the recognition was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was to be the recognition, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
At the schools that you went to did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life - thinking of Northleigh - things like manners, tidiness, punctuality, how you spoke - did they consider those things important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. Oh no. No, that - that - I don't think I can ever remember - anything of that sort. It was just a question of con - of carrying on their duties such as learning one to read and write and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They didn't pay attention to tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Punctuality they considered important didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well that was a - a - that was a - a necessity I suppose of their organization, such as being late for school, yes, was subjected to punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about how you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That - no. Not - no - not the slightest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At the Freeland school, did they care there about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, they were quite concerned at Freeland. I remember that quite well. General mannerisms was a - a thing that was to be obey
ed and - accepted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the way you spoke - did they consider that important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. Because habit then was so - conformed there was no question of - what shall I use, the word obliterate - you couldn't - transform - my way of spe
aking then back in the village was very, very broad and - of course we I - was different at school. You'd say you for there, all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You'd say thee at home would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh when I was going on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you talk like that still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, I - when I go back in the village - down in the old part I'd say, hello George, how's it going on. I don't know how last time I ever see thee, must have been forty years ago I haven't seen thee Bill, not for ages. See that was the general way of -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It's a very old fashioned way isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - if - if you assume to - to use a proper way of speech then - well it - you were laughed at because you was - considered you was trying to be uppish. So you deliberately drop into the - common vogue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
At the Freeland school - you said there weren't gangs or - groups in that school and that there were no children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not at Freeland school, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The teachers didn't single out some children for different treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You left when you were twelve and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you have stayed longer if you'd have had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I suppose I would. But at that time you see - my line of thought was more or less contro
lled by those people that had the power to wield their will so that - probably I would be in a state of confusion about things and what was said that I must go away, that was a question of I just simply accepted it as a fact. Of course my mother and fathe
r had that in - in this question of me going away for my good, it was considered, and - I just simply went. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did your parents feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They thought possibly it was right I should imagine. But not my granny 'cos I remember on my le
aving the little - very small little cottage it was and she was rather poorly that afternoon, I remember she was laid on - on her bed and as I say the room was partitioned off and she drew curtain - broken hearted poor old lady was, she says, ah well, goo
d
bye will, I shall never see you again. I said, well granny, I'll see you. And I - I wasn't very emotional at that time about that sort of thing. Since I have you see because I - what a terrific thing it was for dear old granny then, she never - she knew t
hat she'd never see me again and I - I wasn't really concerned. I said, oh I'll see you again granny. So away I went. And as I say, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And did you see her again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no. No, I didn't see poor old granny again. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you tell me what led up to your having to leave the school - it was some - thing to do with not attending choir practice wasn't it?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. It - it so happened that the clergyman was away on holidays - and his daughter - his sister was taking the choir but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was at Freeland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, this was at Freeland. But I was very keen on football and it happened to be moonlight nights and I persuaded the boys that we'd pack up choir practice for the time being and indulge in - engage in football - which we did. But of 
course when the clergyman came back it was questioned to what had happened to us and why had we done this sort of thing. And - said we played football and of course - an apology was required. I wasn't prepared to give and refused. And I remember him telli
ng - saying, well you can go - you're a Northleigh boy. And I left. And what followed was the question then of me - going away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When he said you can go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He meant it - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Go from where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Go from - go out from the meeting - I - I wouldn
't apologize and not only that, you're not a Freeland boy, you're a Northleigh boy. Well you can go - you're a Northleigh boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But did he mean he was expelling you from the school too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That - really and truly at that moment it meant that I was e
x - excommunicated from - from church - from activity of the church. I was finished with the choir and then of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then the next step was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The next step was - what should happen to a boy like me - I was a bad influence in the - in 
the village and possibly would be the best thing for me to - to go. And to that extent the seeing I had not finished my schooldays it was still expedient that I should be out of the - out of the village for the good of the others. And I - I questioned - I
 can possibly - I don't question parson he - he thoroughly believed it was necessary and poss - and possibly explained to my parents why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He went to see them did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I can't remember that he did, he must have done so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said they sent to Northleigh for information about your attendance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had you enough attendances then for them to be able to let you leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I don't think so. But I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So in a way they were breaking the law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well they - they made that possible to - the law at that time was their law which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They were able to break it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. With impunity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have any part time education after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, no. Only - book of life sort of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes I - yes, I - yes I do. Yes I think that - at that early stage I could have had an education - I could have been of some use. I was always lost in the work - in manual work, in physical work you know. Never really concen
trate properly on it - only as a pure necessity.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. I - because I never really learnt anything at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did he find this job for you in Sandhurst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - the immediate pros
pect looked very dim because I - the lady - of course had already heard from the clergyman as to what type of boy I was and - I always remember going into the kitchen, housekeeper telling me to sit down and the lady - coming through the kitchen with these
 - what do you call them, bisnoys or - little glass on - wiping them and - and I was in - quite a state of nerves I suppose and - always stand up when you're speaking to a lady. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 I\rquote d}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  forgotten my manners - which I did immediately. And - oh Nanna - that was h
ousekeeper - take those horrid things away - Comic Cuts protruding out of my pocket, you know. So they were taken away and - I suppose, conversed with me for a short time and - said, that'll do, see you tomorrow, with a smile which wasn't a very nice smil
e. And - and that's what happened. I'll always remember two -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you were sent there from the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You'd never met her before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no. No, that's the first meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But how did the vicar know this person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh through contact with the - with the - church. That was a clergyman's household.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And this lady with the glasses - what relation was she to the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To the vicar at Freeland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To the vicar in Sandhurst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh they were - that was the - the
 vicar - the - aye, no relation to the actual vicar but this - her husband was a retired clergyman - as a matter of fact, invalided out of the - out of the - he was - he was an invalid. I think I told you where he used to read in different languages the B
ible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 While you were still at school you used to go from your granny's to work for the Miss ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have a job when you were at the Northleigh school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Only in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was your first job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. That was - that was early in the morning just, as I say, to clean knives and forks - clean the boots and - do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well it - that was arranged when I went to granny's because you see the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 were devout church people so it was all part and parcel of church work. Right from the very moment I went to Freeland. I had to supplement poor granny Merry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I thought she was chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, yes, she was chapel person - yes. But there was always that terrific persuasive power to get granny over to the church of England.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was part of the campaign?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was at one time when one of the sisters - Sisters of Mercy they called them I think at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They came and threatened her didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - yes. Said - informed granny that she'd be shut out of heaven because she never attended church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What time did you go to the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About half past seven. 'Til about half past eight - you see, about an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you go again later in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What exactly did you have to do - you had to clean knives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 knives and forks - and I boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You went on Saturday morning too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not on Sundays. No, because I - took up with church work then - choir. For the early service and - and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What - for choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No for the cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Eighteenpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you feel that was a fair wage for the job or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I'd no - that time you see - to think deeply on things of that sort was - out of the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't think about it one way or another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do with the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Gave it to granny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Every bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She didn't give you any back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - it was impossible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She needed it for your keep didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get on with the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 - did you have any contact with them when you'd go their in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, because they would probably be - getting ready to go to church - they went to church very early in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Every day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who did you meet then - who gave you your work and spoke to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well the housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - quite - amenable - just a question of going there and coming away was always - just accepted that I would come there to do the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have much conversation with anybody there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How would you say the Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
treated you in that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Oh I think Miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 
they did what they did was done out of a - kindness to granny to supplement her, I think they were rather - they lost a huge fortune I think - the Miss - they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 had in some undertaking and they were more or less - very poor. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Very genteel ladies of high standing at some time because - the father I suppose was Judge Taunton - so they did everything they possibly could to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There's a picture in Christchurch Hall of one of the .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, it may well be one - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Have you seen it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I haven't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I don't think so - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This job you went to at Sandhurst when you left school - did they tell you much about the job before you got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were you told?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course I was just simply told that I - I was going to this place and that's all I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you say anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No - I just - accepted it as a - one of those things that I had to do, I had no choice in the matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they tell you how long you had to be there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And when you could come home again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't know anything about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. I wasn't - I wasn't really concerned. The only time I was concerned when I got there and the first day - of - doing a little job in the garden - probably, I was put in the garden to just - to be released from - more thoughts - 
you know, to be free. But that was very disturbing thing because after you was always in the garden - school was not far away and the children were out at play you see and I was out at play with 'em because you see really and truly I was still a - or shou
l
d have been - at school and that would - was a thing that I should possibly have overcome because I'd keep a pretty stiff upper lip but suddenly a pat on the back and I'd look round and it was a - housekeeper and of course the last straw breaks the camels
 back. I'm sorry to say I suppose I must have - shed a tear or two - I'm sure I did but - that was one of those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you go and join the children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, because - no, no, I just simply - worked at the house you see and therefore I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did the housekeeper come and pat you on the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I - I - you know, she was - she was a woman that brought up the - the Miss Phelps's and understood - understood people - understood children - I suppose was still a child in that sense 
really. And - of course I wished she'd never done that because - it - it just upset me, you know, and - she said - you - you'll be all right, William. And - I suppose, yes. Well I didn't think so at the time because homesickness is a terrible thing I beli
e
ve 'cos that was the first time I'd ever experienced that. But you see, it only needed about two days after that and - I - I cared for nothing then. I was hardened into things. The - the thought of going back home - no, I - No, I - no, I was settling down
. I accepted it - it was that sort of thing. I didn't like the - I was always afraid of the - of the lady of the house. She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She was Miss Phelps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Mrs Phelps. She - was strict and austere you know, sort of - the - the young ladies, yes, they - I 
- I - they - I could accept them more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were they at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well one was about - eighteen, Miss Agatha I remember. And the other one was - they were out and doing - possibly doing good work. I know there was one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old was the younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was Miss Agatha. She was quite young. She was about seventeen or eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anyone younger than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. The rest was older. The eldest, she was working in the mission works at Liverpool. Used to come home occasionally you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many servants were there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There were - there was only the one, the housekeeper and that'd been their old nursemaid all the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then there was you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There was me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nobody else at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nobody came in to do rough work or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Only the housekeeper. She did the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I used to sleep in a - a house about a hundred yards away. Cottage. In a - Scho - named Schofields -
 I always remember the first night because a room wasn't available for me in the house so I was taken over to this place and being a village you know, across a little pathway into a little field and - it was a - bungalow, you know. And - big sheepdog - ra
t
her fierce ferocious thing you know and of course it was kept under control. We went into the house and the lady, I suppose she was about seventy - somewhere of that at the time - and - of course the dog was kept under control while I was there and - the 
housekeeper let me and the lady said, well - what's your name? And I told her that. All right then Bill, you come here. Took me into this little room you know - that was my little room and that's where I slept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why didn't you sleep in the Phelps's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There wasn't the accommodation at that time. Only when one of the daughter's was away - you know, that I could have a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you sleep there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the kitchen with the housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 All your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't have anything with these other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there a servants hall at that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the housekeeper or the mistress supervise your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The housekeeper. But with a very diligent eye from the lady of the house to - see that I was doing the things that I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 ought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was the work you were supposed to do - could you describe a typical day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. That would be in early morning -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What time would you rise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Seven o'clock. And then clean the knives and forks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You'd come straight over to the house would you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. First think - I always remember that the housekeeper was quite good. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Always a sense of - humour shall I say, sweeping the kitchen she would - I would sweep round - she'd get me to sweep round all the corners first and - oh don't trouble about the middle, Bill - that'll be all right. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I said, but I've got to - oh well, you can yes, but as long as you've done all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 outside}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
. And - I - I was puzzled about this and I made enquires and she assured me that if all the corners was done - all the awkward places - it was so easy to do the middle. You see. That - that was a thing that interested me. But apart from that, yes, 
I'd clean the kitchen and then clean the knives and forks and then the boots, shoes all that sort of thing. Then, of course, breakfast. And then -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you help at all with cooking the breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, help - I never done anything like that
. 'Course - oh by the way, I had to clean the - the gentleman's room, drawing room. Because that was a - rather - not a very pleasant thing for a youngster - for me to do because I didn't expect that. As I told you, he suffered with asthma and he smoked a
 
matter of - best cigars, six, seven and eight a day - always knew because of the stubs in the - that was of necessity. That was doctor's orders. And - the - the spittoon - we expect during the course of the day was - well - it's hardly nice to speak about
 
but quite a lot to - I had to clean that out with hot water and that was - it was a ghastly thing now and I could - you see, I was - suppose I didn't realize it then anything could happen like that there. But you see that - had to clean that out then when
 
I'd done that, clean the drawing room out. And there's a question of going to post. Go down the village. Always took the dog with me, you know, and it was great fun with the dog. That was about a mile - about a mile and a half to post office. And perhaps 
to get stamps and post letters, that sort of thing. I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you do shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I'd do shopping. And take the laundry. I remember taking the laundry - the first time taking the laundry when the boys coming out of school. Are you the bo
y at Phelps's? I said, yes. In a wheelbarrow you know and cloth over - tied neatly and big clothes basket - got about a mile to this village with this wheelbarrow you know. And then one pushed one so one pushed the other and eventually they pushed it over
.
 Then I was in a predicament and I didn't know what to do because there were too many of them. And why I had a fight with one - which I readily done because I was so used to it at school you see - had a - a complete bash up for me because I had the roughe
r
 - I had two or three on top of me. But I was lucky because a man came along and jumped off his bike and helped me to gather up the - things that was on the floor and of course lots of it was - small stuff belonging to the ladies, you know, that sort of t
h
ing - collect it and put it in the basket. And when I went round the laundry - the laundry - it was two ladies used to do the wash and I told them what had happened to me, of course my face was bruised a bit. And they told me it'd be all right, they'd put
 
it - you know - and all nicely done up. So when I got back - housekeeper asked me what had happened to me. I said, well I fell down. Well you couldn't fall down and hurt yourself like that. Well I said, did you see. But whether she believed it or not she 
a
ccepted it and that was that. That was the start of things as that happened then to me in they early stages - but you see as I - I'd already got accustomed to rough and hard times. Almost unbelievable that I could accept it within two or three days and so
 - that was my state and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Potter about in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were supposed to do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, I did gardening - yes - for - just - and now the lawn, clip round the hedges you know - did all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That incident of being beaten by the boys - did that happen other times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, that would just - see - 'course I grew up with that at Northleigh school just simply did that. In fact, a boy I used to knock about with qui
te a lot - we - we'd entice others to - have a fight and we'd make a chalk mark and the first one that stands up to there is the best man. Well - there'd be - perhaps perfectly good friends and they didn't want to fight but we'd persuade them into it. Suc
h
 was our make-up at that time. Then we'd say, we'll show you how to fight in - this pas of mine, we used to really have a stand up fight as though we were actually - and we wasn't at enmity one with another - oh and we used to have bruised faces like and 
a
ll that but we accepted all that. It was extraordinary sort of thing that we did that sort of thing. What we - what we did heaven only knows, and why we did it - I don't know. I remember - at school - out of school - the place was infected with lizard fro
g
s. These frogs hopped about - little yellow frogs - frogs in the - in the grass you know and - horror of horrors - we would use straws and blow them up. Well it was done you see and - my mate, he'd swallow these little frogs. He'd say, here, and he'd have
 
this with the little legs and - open his mouth and it'd go - I said, they'll kill you. No, he said, my mum says they're good things for the liver. I suppose it was more coincidence but he was very fleet of foot, he was very active - he could just about ru
n, but he would swallow these little frogs. I can't think of others doing it. I often thought about doing it but I never quite accomplished that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At that household did you feel at ease with the housekeeper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, I felt - yes, she was quite - she was quite a good person. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 
She would she brought up this family in the better times - they'd lost money evidently on a big railway thing I believe - and - they - they knew her as Nanna, you know, and the - I always remember the Miss Agatha sometimes sh
e'd come home, Nanna, and fling her arms round - you know - it's a lovely thing it was. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Thing I'd never been used to you see but - I thought what a nice thing that was to do. And so she was part and parcel of the household. Miss Simpson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think she would have flung her arms round her own mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - oh yes. Yes. Should - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She was that sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - yes, I think Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9194455\charrsid5840491 Agatha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  was a - was very - keen - and lovable }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 type}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  of person and in - in a way that she'd been brou
ght up. You see, the whole make-up of life was a Christian type of life - in a very strict sense - as - her mother, Mrs Phelps was severe with me that - that was quite a necessary thing so it was thought I suppose at that time. I was a bad boy, yes, and n
eeded discipline and training.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you feel at ease with Mrs Phelps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about with Mr Phelps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well you see, I seldom came in contact with him. He was a man of - angelic type of man - I can - you see - I'm always haunted wi
th the thought of that man, you know, so - saintly like, in his drawing room - he was confined to the drawing room all day long yet - with his asthma complaint - in his breathing, you could hear him long distance off - you could always hear him quite a di
s
tance off - must have been very difficult and - the way he used to talk sometimes - if he went upstairs to the toilet he'd come - come up with you to some - inquest of something at some meeting you know and he - his voice would reach a high crescendo some
times, you know. He was always - and then religious services, he went through religious services.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Out loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 A conversation - congregation. He'd got a little - thing in his room, you know - pulpit or a - call it pulpit 
- what you read your lessons from, but quite a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 sane}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 man because if I had to go into his room he'd always - want anybody - you know, just a few works and - and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have a long conversation with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. It was impossible because of his illness. He - I always remember -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
His illness - it would be impossible for him to - to converse. His - wife only just occasionally went into his room - only for a minute or so. His illness was such - that - it was impossible for him t
o - he never went out on the lawn, only for I only remember - eighteen months I was there - seeing him outside twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why did his illness stop him from having conversation - because of his breathing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. I can't now - I wouldn't attempt 
to do it. You know, it was gasping all the time you see. So that I don't think it was very easy for him to converse - only in short spasms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did people come to see him, did he have company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think the clergyman of the village very seldom came. He did come just occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But he never went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He never went out - oh no, he never left -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you say he was imagining an inquest, do you mean from the past?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, from the past, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Reliving it in his mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, yes
. Yes. That was - you see - and birds - he used to come to his window and come into his room, they always - outside - see the little birds come into his window and he used to chuck little crumbs and that out. You see, now, they'd flutter up because we had
 
the dog and I trained this dog - very amusing - cat you know - he loved to go for this cat well there was a fir tree opposite and low branches and cat used to shoot up the tree and the dog'd - scuttle away and he'd climb up a branch or two you know, then 
wait at the bottom. But I think this man must realize that I was into mischief because - the housekeeper told me that I wasn't to send the dog after the cat - you upset Mr Phelps you see. I believe he realized what was happening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you feel that anyone in the family was interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so. No, I don't think they - no, I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the housekeeper - was she interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think the housekeeper was. She was in
terested in - in - in things I used to talk about and she often used to wonder why I was interested in such things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of things for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that was a - question of what we did in the - in the village and - and things that that I t
hought we ought to do - do better. But that was a passing interest I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She called you Bill did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 William or Bill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Bill - generally Bill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the other members of the family - what did they call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 William. William.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Called Miss Agatha - ma'am you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Ma'am you'd call?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, Mrs Phelps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And Mr Phelps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course as I say my contact with him was so rare that just Sir, you know. I remember
 - leaving - leaving - the place for the last time he came to the door - and - goodbye William, God bless you. Get on well. And he stumbled back into his room, you know, it was his - it was an effort for the man to reach the door. This was a chronic illne
s
s wasn't it in those - some people call it religious mania - well I - people call it what they like, he was a perfectly sane gentleman who was so afflicted that he - he carried on this ceremonial work of - with an imaginary audience and all that but that 
wasn't - no question of sanity, it was something that had - the man had suffered so much that really - I can't say that there was anything wrong with him in carrying out the work he did. Be certain - but perhaps putting the surplus on and through the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Put the surplice on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Lovely character. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long had he been retired to you think when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I wouldn't know. Some time I should imagine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did Mrs Phelps or the Miss Phelps's give you any moral guidance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. None - none whatsoever except that they got me to go to church certainly. Oh yes, I went to church and - I remember going to the Sunday school - that was a thing that pleased me because - Bible class on the Sunday afternoons - the clergyman would 
give a very short - scripture reading and then a story book. Lively story too it was, you know, and - that was controlled by the - this. This was outside of - of - religion, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you allowed any time in which to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, of course I did get leisure time. Sometimes in the evenings and - cricket, football for example.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you manage to play the cricket and football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - that was in connection with the church - organized by the church you see, and so I played cricket with 'em and football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What day of the week would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That'd be on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Generally - no, generally in the - Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you went out did they always want to know where you were and what you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think they were so inquisitive about that. 'Cos I think they really got to know and understand me - of - that I was - could be accepted to do what I was told. And as regards honesty I think they - that was - t
hey accepted that I was quite honest type of person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have a regular time off that was your own?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, could be most irregular. I never knew - when I had to go down to the Post Office or go down in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 wintry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you say you might have to go to the post at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I did. But that was if - if I went late at night I took the - the bulldog. That was put - a lot to me. He was a terrific and now be all right for me because it's too str - it was really too strong you know, u
sed to pull me along. Heaven help anyone that come to - interfere with me in any way - been - oh too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The Saturday afternoons playing sport - were they irregular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I was never sure whether I could - sometimes I was very disappointed because I wouldn't be - I couldn't go. I had something to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you lonely or did you have enough companionship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I suppose I was - I suppose I was lonely, yes. Off times I was lonely because I'd got no one to - mix with you see, I wasn't allowed to mi
x with anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't get to know any local boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I did yes but then they were far away and I couldn't always go - wandering off and pick them up and then say we'll go for a leisurely walk because I had to be back at certain time. And their time was unlimited, they could do as they liked, I couldn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When did you have to be in by in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - well of course at winter time I wasn't out at all - not at nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You weren't allowed out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Ad in summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In summer yes - with reasonable - hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 'Til about when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, I suppose about half past eight. That you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did these boys ever call round on you - could they cal on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No, that wouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there anything you particularly disliked about being there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 
Well, yes, you see 'cos things was - even there - so far as they were concerned they had their - they had their sanitary accommodation was good. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
But - mine was only a - a - just a bucket arrangement you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This is where you were lodging you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, that was in the - in their house you see, and that was a thing which I had to do - see to every week, you know. And - I didn't care much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, every week. To -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You mean you had one outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, had to clean it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You weren't able to use theirs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, no, not at all. No, 'cos theirs was - they wouldn't let you use that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you disliked that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I disliked that job. And I disliked the -
 what you call segregation - I didn't like to be - you know - isolated as a - as someone outside of - humanity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At your home what would your sanitary arrangements have been there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Well at - the - they - they were very primitive - of course - tha
t was a deep recess dug, you see, and - I remember one big seat for the grown ups and a smaller one for the children, you see, and - 'course there was no such thing as - toilet paper and used it - I can't remember such a thing as - newspapers hung up and 
that was a thing that was emptied about say every six months.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have to do that job at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 We used lime. Used lime you see. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You hadn't had to concern yourself with that then at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not at home, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who did that job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh my elder brothers. They did that at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 night time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  you see. But you - in - in the village generally as regards sanitary arrangements - if there were buckets - generally - some place you know, where it was used given time, some people - possible
 used lime but others no - it was left and flies infested places always - the lavatories and round about - yes, it was. Often wonder there's not more disease than what there was in - in the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 Was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  there anything about your job that you particularly liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was the washing sent out there - I think you said it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I took it to the laundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were any clothes made in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who mended the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the housekeeper do all the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she do all the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She did all the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she have regular time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I - you see, she was part and parcel of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Like a mother really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Like a mothe
r. She brought up the family and they accepted her as part and parcel of the family only on a - a - formal occasions was she Miss Simpson to the ladies. You see. But otherwise - in - in - part and parcel of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But she wouldn't eat with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well - no. No, because I - I suppose it was just a mere for - from of habit, always been used to having it in the kitchen and - getting their meals ready. It wasn't a question that - that she wouldn't be acceptable but it was just a normal - way of 
life. And there was me you see there, to - be in the kitchen, for me to be absolutely alone would - wouldn't be quite right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who was responsible for any repairs or improvements to that house while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I can't remember anyone really - except the neighbour - a Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Schofield}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - would do odd jobs about the house in regard to - window cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He was paid for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, suppose he was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And the adults ate their meals where - in the dining room would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the dining room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There were no children in that household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The children - only Miss Agatha at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But they weren't children when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, they were grown up - they were all grown up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What cooking equipment did the housekeeper have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh well I couldn't - no, you see, I wouldn't be too interested in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember if it was a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think it was - best of my memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Not a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 There were a few gas cookers round then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I don't know - I think it was a sort of a range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They'd have their breakfast about half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh mine would be earlier than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What members of the family had breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - the Mrs Phelps and daughter - and - oh the other daughter - they were at home
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But not Mr Phelps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh Mr Phelps always in his room. Oh never out - never went in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What food did they have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I can't remember much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you remember what you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I - yes, generally toast and porridge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. It could be - I think mostly tea at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about dinner - midday dinner - did you have it midday or in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - yes, midday meal - always good - plenty of food. Well satisfied as regards food. Yes. I never had so much in my life before. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think it did you good in that way - physically?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes, I t
hink I picked up you know, 'cos I had quite good food. Previously you see that was - well - earning eighteenpence a week, it wasn't much. But - poor granny, I suppose what she had - was too small to - I had potatoes and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 green stuff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and - oh yes - pretty rough you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were at the Phelps's did you have the same food as they had or different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think I had the same food as they had. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of food did you have for a midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not very easily - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have a joint for example sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's right, we'd be - I can remember cutting off you know for me, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who would cut off for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The housekeeper. Yes. Cooked vegetables and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Always a pudding, yes, delicious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You liked that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about in the evening, was there tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had a bit of - biscuits. I generally had if I remember about six biscuits. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That'd be about - eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you have between dinner and tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - oh - well dinner - you call dinner - what we call -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Midday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, midday dinner, then teatime - say about half past four or five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well, cake and bread and butter - anything - jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did the family's meals go - did they have a tea or did they have a meal at night
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They had a meal at night. Yes. Always had a meal at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have that too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, only just the - as I say - hot drink and few biscuits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What time was their meal at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About half past eight. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of food did they have at night - can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would it be meat and vegetables or would it be something lighter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I think it'd be some - something more light. Possibly be cheese something - you know, it was - more or less that nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In that household you did the garden - did anybody else do the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Except the ladies - they were - she would - she was very, very keen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 .}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5840491  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 She}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  was so keen in regard to gardening that she - she got me a book - amateur }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 gard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - Amateur Gardener. It was brought out by the News of the World. I've still got part of it now - 
in the - different marks that she'd made in this book the time to do different types of jobs and that respect. She's corrected the Amateur Gardeners and one thing amuses me - tells you - shoot all bullfinches. And she's crossed that out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did she put?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not - just a few potatoes and things of that sort but flowers, they quite went in for lots of flowers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And fruit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So vegetables and fruit were bought for the household were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember them having tinned vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I can't remember - no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they keep anything like hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no animals. They encouraged squirrels and - any - anything of - could move about. They had a great love for animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How many times a week did you eat meat there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I think most meals. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have fish on Fridays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - they - they're almost sure to have done with their - high church, yes, and festivals you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You say the daughters weren't very kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so, not really. They may - their intentions may have been that way by being - pretty firm with me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Can you think of an example of their unkindness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. In - just to - family that the boots were not quite clean properly by making a mark - you see, if that was properly clean the polish would come back again - wouldn't leave a mark there. That wax - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They criticized you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. Come out you see - you know, imagine I was polishing your boots and - well, 'cos I didn't know anything about it, I'd sort of think - you see that. Well you see the polish hasn't come back again, if you'd cleaned it properly the pol
ish would come back, you must see to that in future.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they often make remarks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, very - very often you see. I didn't mind because you see that didn't worry me, I was hardened into that sort of thing. I accepted that as part and parcel of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 On Christmas Day when you were there did you join in with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not in their house, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I - if I remember rightly I was just in the kitchen and - then had the - the sort of things that wa
s going at Christmastime. Probably much more than I had before anywhere else. That was all right - I never thought no more about it. But I can't remember too much about it. But I can't remember too much about it. I can't remember that - the lady of the ho
use wished me all the best things in life and happiness and prosperity or - entered into my life. Not at all - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were they a musical family - were there musical instruments in their home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes I think there were - they were interested in music. And I remember Miss Agatha - lovely voice. She used to sing quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember them singing or playing music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - piano'd go - yes, only Miss Agatha - with piano going, you know, that sort of thing. I remember telling the ho
usekeeper - I told - she was beautiful young lady wonderful good looks and I said, well, she would have done well for the stage. And that was a - horrible thought. 'Cos even housekeeper - that was terrible - no, not the stage life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you didn't realize that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I didn't realize that, oh no, no. Not until I - remember - a boy coming there - errand boy and - I was telling this errand boy I said, well if you listen to me you'll be as crafty as what I am - you want to be up to these sort of things - I
'll learn you how to be crafty. Well now you see - we always used that word crafty - we meant, I suppose, then - to - be - pretty fly and to be able to do this, that and the other and - the housekeeper, she was shocked at me over this. She says, horrible,
 you mustn't talk like that. Crafty - what do you mean by being crafty? I says, well, how to get about the world. Well she - she give }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 me a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  lesson on this, I always remember. She says, you see, only craft - that you can do is craftiness trade. The craft that
 you mean is to outwit someone - to be nasty. That is a term I did not understand but - always having a memory I remembered it later on and what she really meant but that you see. But you see, the craft that I learnt was the craft of subsistence - how to 
linger on - how to move - the wink of the eye, the you see, and that grew with me and putting it to this boy to be crafty didn't mean that he - to be malicious or do someone some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The sort of background you'd come from made it a necessity didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there a lot of books in that house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you able to read them at all or look at them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes - not - only two or three books I can remember. I remember one books - that was a rescue - adventurous type of s
tory of - Robinson Crusoe, of course that was - Man Friday and Masterman Ready was one that stands out. This was the type of book that was - was - given to me to read because that was a - a very necessary sort of thing that I should have so they thought.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you read them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I read one or two of them, but a lot of - most of the books I didn't read that they give me - pretended to read them but I didn't read them because I didn't accept them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were you paid in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Half a crown a week. And living you see. Half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do with the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I guessed you was going to ask me that. Woodbines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The whole lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I wouldn't say - oh no, no, no, no. No, was sweets and different things you see but - cigarettes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't send any home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No. I don't think I did because you see it wasn't very much was it, half a crown. If I remember right I must have saved some of it, then I had to buy - I had to buy little things but - I d
o - 'course I do remember buying the Woodbines. Because that was a thing - I don't know - I just - they were cheap then you see. Of course - I couldn't smoke them about the house. Oh no. That - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that before you smoked a clay pipe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's before I smoked a pipe, yes. Yes. But there you see I couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What age were you when you first started smoking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I smoked - when I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, no. No. About ten. Oh yes - this stuff you grow - pick from th
e hedges that'll smoke - honesty we used to call it. Yes. It used to burn the tongue. Then we used to make that little hollow hole in a - pithy sort of sticks and - push tea leaves up - dry tea leaves and a bit of tobacco if we could get it mixed up with 
- if we pinch a bit you know and - try to smoke that. Oh, it - terrible that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you dry this honesty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. But it burn you know - it was - 'course matches, we always pinch matches and - you could get matches you see - four boxes for a 
penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the cook know that you smoked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no fear. Oh no, she wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you have a smoke then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the toilet. 'Cos no one else visit there except me you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was your only privacy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't smoke in your lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not on your life - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the people there take any interest in you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where I lodged at - only interest I can imagine the lady taking was getting me up in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. She would - yes - because - I used to say, you're on - all right Mrs Schofield - make a noise you see and bump something on the floor, see, ah but you're not getting up. Which she knew that - when I was getting out. Then she'd threaten me, i
f you don't get out I'll come and pull you out of bed. Then I used to get up then. I used to lay in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she check up if you were reading in bed at night or awake in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I didn't often - at night - no, 'cos I used to get off - you see, I suppose -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What time did you get back to your lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In the night after you'd finished work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, about nine o'clock. In the wintertime I was up - no, I wasn't too early getting over you see 'cos I was pretty busy day, tim
e I'd had my meals and that and time I walk - when I get over there - how - of course it - it was a concrete place and with the wind and the snow and wintertime it was a footpath, oh, almost as far from here up to say the corner, the pub, going through th
e latch - latch gage and back kitchen you know - ash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 footpath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 then of course a little path you know, to - to the ld ladies place and - well of course I'd been used to the country so it didn't make any difference but - it was a bit ghastly going down there -
 dark and clammy you know. Open the back kitchen door then - oh, a big dog it - but of course he knew it was me and that was all right you see after he - 'course step in, Mrs Schofield perhaps be sitting close to her old fireplace, she never went to bed v
e
ry early. But - I thought that was you Bill. Oh well, you'd better get off to bed. So off to bed I used to get. That was it. And of course it was downstairs room and - I could look out of the window and - the road wasn't far off. If it was moonlight I use
d to pull the curtain, I'd sit and watch. I didn't mind curtain being drawn. I wasn't afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any contact with your parents during that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I used to write - to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she wrote back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. She wrote about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How often did you write to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Me? I'd writer perhaps about once a fortnight. I doubt if I'd have ever wrote and it was my mother that was chiefly concerned with. Always wrote because of - mother to let her know that I was all right you see. I thoug
ht that was - very necessary. I doubt if I would have ever wrote to anyone otherwise. Not to my dad - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never wrote to anybody else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did anybody else write to you or send you anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Only this - schoolteacher at Freel
and. She - she wrote to me once and she sent me - the - price - price - prize and a drawing I drew - Freeland church. And there was a competition between Northleigh, Freeland and North - Northleigh, Freeland and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 . And I won the third prise. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she sent this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, she sent it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
The - oh only a certificate - proving that I'd won. Whe - whether I had any money I can't remember. But - I won this and I think I won this chiefly because - this schoolteacher used to
 help me a lot. More than she helped anyone else and I can't think that I did it with my skill and she knew that I was going away - and I finished off before it was time for me to go. And I - I - I thought about it afterwards ; quite a lot about it, wheth
er she helped me and I've got an idea it was simply because - she knew I was going away. Out of sympathy. And I think she must have volunteered to go down to the station with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 It was she who went down with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. See me off. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never saw any friends or relations during that eighteen months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. Not at all. I never see anyone. I never went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you say your homesickness only lasted about three days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 About three days - less than that I should imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never used to long for your mother during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Ah - yes, of - yes, of course, now that was the homesickness, yes, that went but - that was different thought you see, my mother, my thoughts was continuously with my mother and longing for he
r and all that sort - but as regards to - that sickness that you have for home, that went almost immediately. That was different, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have newspapers in the house there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you manage to get a look at them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, I used to - Tribune them it was, I remember that. Paper called the Tribune.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that a daily paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was a daily, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And did they have magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, they had mag - magazines, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember Mrs Phelps reading aloud to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, not Mrs Phelps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who did read aloud then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh of course - that was up to Mr Phelps, he was continuously read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He read aloud to himself didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He read aloud to himself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He didn't read aloud to anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember anybody reading aloud to anybody else there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nobody read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. Nobody read to me, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Nobody thought that it would be nice to give you any instruction in anything - to help you in any way with your writing or reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. No, because you see - I was there for one purpose - to be disciplined I should imagine that was how it was thought of. Otherwise they wouldn't have - have - taken me out of schooldays unless it was for a 
purpose which they thought absolutely necessary and - the - the chief thing - idea was discipline. And of course as to - regards teaching me otherwise I - don't think they thought about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember a funeral there while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I can't - no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you knew whether Mr or Mrs Phelps took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so at that time, I wasn't interested in - in what they thought of pol - political life. I did realize that there was such a gulf bet
ween us that - it was unbridgeable and how I was going to approach them I never knew. I knew at that time - how much I needed a - other people but that was unfathomable. There was no one I could go to - there was no one who would understand me therefore I
 never attempted it. I just went along my own way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you pour out your thoughts to your mother at all in your letters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No, I wouldn't - I wouldn't do that - no. I - I always I wrote just absolutely contrary to what I was thinking - always -
 happy go lucky you know so that I was in - I was happy and I was - everything was good, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 To try and make her cheerful you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's right, because otherwise it wouldn't - no. Wouldn't - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you call Mr Phelps if you came into his room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Sir. Good morning Sir and always a pleasant smile. Hardly ever any response except that. 'Course I - I knew quite in regard to his illness was such - and the very reason that his family never disturbed him in the course of a 
day - except just for a fleeting glance - a look into the room and a smile of reassurance of - we're still about. And Mrs Phelps - she never stayed in the room - always just a brief - walk into the room, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I was never aware of that fact. I - I - I would never know except for the simple reason that - there was no one close in proximity to their house so that - I doubt so I think they were rather high church and the fact of that that they -
 they allowed Sunday games such as they did at Freeland. They played quite freely and rough and tumble cricket you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Phelps and - Mrs Phelps, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But not the old gentleman - he wasn't well enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh he never went out of his room. It's just possible on a very nice day in summer he would - he'd - reach the lawn. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 And the little birds would be fluttering about around him because the window was open in the summer they'd just flit into the window. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
He always fed them with - bread crumbs, you know, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But that's as far as it went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's as far as it went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you or the housekeeper go to church while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I went Sunday mornings and then again in the 
afternoon to Bible class. Which was always a thrill - for the simple reason - that - the clergyman read us a story from a book. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you go alone or did the housekeeper go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I went alone. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it the same church as the Phelps's attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, the same church. Yes. Sandhurst parish church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the housekeeper go to church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I can't remember. I - I don't think it was easy for - the housekeeper to leave the house. Because there was always
 someone about - going to Mr Phelps' illness. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The morning service you attended would that be the same service as the Phelps's would be at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. They usually went in the evenings. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember an occasion when you did attend at the same time as they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I can never remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was grace said at meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course I - I mean, I would never know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never happened to be in the room when it was said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. But I - you can rest assured it was. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You and the housekeeper in the kitchen, did she say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I wouldn't be aware of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Probably not because of his poor health do you think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh - oh yes, never approached Mr Phelps only - with this question of care. He remarkable man because - absolutely - sane. In spite of his illness, it wasn't - he read - from the Bible and read aloud and talked quite a lot but - lovely man to know. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did Mrs Phelps go out on her wn at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. They used to pay visits to - people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did Miss Agatha go with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Sometimes - not always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she have interests outside the home besides the visiting to do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Wha
t Miss Phelps? Well I - I don't think Mrs Phelps - except when she paid visits to friends - as regards other activities I'm not aware of. No. But I think the Miss Phelps's and there - was Miss }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Agatha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and Miss Cicely and the others was very interested in ch
urch work and I think I told you that Miss Cicely spent a lot of time in Liverpool - in mission work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you know if Mrs Phelps was on any committees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have friends that called at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well
 I - only one I can remember was a - a Mr Dover was escorting Miss Agatha and he was a son of a - of a Canon and - yes, that's only thing that I can remember in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have set times for friends to call?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They didn't have an at home day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so. I think - life then ran much in the same way - to a lesser degree than what it would to the - say the lower classes. I don't think life was organized to that extent, even to - well, say the upper classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember anybody coming to stay in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Only Miss Agatha's - friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This man who was courting her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He actually came to stay did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, he would stay for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He didn't live in Sandhurst?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, he'd stay - stay for a week or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did it make much difference to the organization of the house when he was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What sort of person was he - how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Wel
l of course I never came into contact - with him. He would never speak to me. No. That was thing - I always realized that I was someone apart. I was just the boy to - around the house. And - always with an idea that I was under discipline. Which I could n
ever understand, I never realized - what I'd done wrong. So that I - even with kindness to a degree and a sincerity of purpose I would never fault these people in anything wrong. It's a thing that they understood and thought proper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they have any dinner parties or large entertainments?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No, they would not you see for the simple reason - anything that could disturb or distract - their father would be abhorrent to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember any other callers besides the young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was he the only person who came to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the friends that she went to visit - didn't they come back and call on her
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, they never came there. No. That I think was well understood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because of his health?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. The least distraction I think came about in Mr Phelps's life was - of great concern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did they sit - he had his own room - they had a drawing room where they sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was the study - they had - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But you think even somebody coming to the house would distract and worry him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I'm positive about that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say that from as far as social class was concerned Mr and Mrs Phelps were from the same background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I would. Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What class would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well I would say that they were rather the upper class. But - I always understood from the housekeeper that there was a misfortune in - in money matters, which at that time I did not understand, but I take i
t for granted it was a question of financial loss and - some business or - in speculation, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The young man who came courting, was he the same social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think that Mrs Phelps and the Miss Phelps's were content
 with their station in life or do you think they would have liked a higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I don't think so, I think that was - accepted as a part and parcel of their very - life. Of course the tragic time in their life was in the - in the - ill health of Mr Phelps. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Have you any idea how long that had been going on when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I think it'd been going on for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You think he'd been in bad health for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. And then of course this asthma followed. Which was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had you ever known people like the Phelps before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, never. - And of course it was an extraordinary thing to me to come in contact with a situation such as that, being born in the country and thrown into a - into a new world, was
 most amazing and of course I had to make enquires of the house - keeper as to what the noise was because you see the - the language was completely different to any language that I'd ever heard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How do you mean the language?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In foreign language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Because he used to speak these foreign languages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
He used to speak in foreign - he used to read the - as I - of course I would think it was the Bible - there were words that I - fathomed out was - such as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Je}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Cree}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and - you know. And - but 
of course the thing that I was most interested why was this noise going on. And the housekeeper told me all about Mr ill - about Mr Phelps and his illness and how he loved to read and he was reading in a different language.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But when you say a noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he read very loudly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh, very loud. Sometimes it was - used to reach - well, it used - a high crescendo away you could hear him matter of - fifty yards away.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did the family react to this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh that was taken for grante
d - they went about their normal work and - so used to it that it was quite all right. There was nothing, in their way of looking at things, abnormal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did nobody come to call on him personally - no other vicars or any church people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - I think 
that the - the clergymen did call very, very occasionally. That was well understood that he was never to be disturbed. Even so, I cleaned his room out early in the morning - cigars - the butts of the cigars which would be seven, eight, nine and as I - I t
hink I mentioned about the spittoon - this business, yes, you see. Here was a man that was - one can only imagine the suffering of this man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did the manners of Mrs and Miss Phelps and their general behaviour seem very different from people you'd associated with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, quite so, yes, yes. In the extreme. Because you see, their way of life and ours - was so completely different that theirs were - was more or less an organized life. Ours was scramble for existence - in the well conducted - i
f one mentions well conducted families which it seems almost to me inconceivable in village life - then you see I could see the enormous difference - one never - had any organized existence in the village life, you got up in the morning, you scrambled to 
s
chool and the young mother I suppose with the best intentions in the world as families came along abandoned all hope of - of organization and - the children I think most - I think our family was typical of others - children more or less would - got dresse
d
 and went off to school - played, came home to meals and out something from the loaf and - and just shifted around. Life wasn't anything like one can imagine it is today, you came home, sit down to a - to a proper meal, said grace, no, you just simply wan
dered around and - did the best that you possibly could. And it was accepted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who it was a real change for you to be in a household of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Complete change - I never understood. Even so, the first - instance of a - of reaching the kitchen a
nd the lady gave me a visit and censored manners which I'd certainly been learned at home but not to that extent - immediately rising in the presence of a lady and - no, I didn't understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She came into the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She came into the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were working there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. The first - first evening, reaching the destination and - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She told you off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Here was a case of snatching my comics from me and - very first interview was - was quite startin
g to me - 'cos I'd been so used to comic papers and that sort of thing and my mouth organ was even taken away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you get those back again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I never had them back again. And whistling was most uncouth. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever go away for a holiday with them during that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, never. Oh no - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you left them can you tell me how it was that you heard you were going home again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. The housekeeper told me that - I would be going back home and that - Mrs Phelps th
at they could manage now - quite reasonably. And - I understood from the housekeeper - she told me in the kindly way that - I didn't quite answer their purpose. They found out I wasn't quite as nice as what - the boy was at - Mr Dover's, that was somewher
e
 - place in Ringwood. I don't know where Ringwood is but it was Ringwood. And - possibly I would be better - as a gardener. And I remember - Mrs Phelps buying me a book - Gardening for the Masses which was published by the News of the World. I've still go
t
 the book now around - yes, I have. And - and so from that - for that very reason I should imagine that I - came away. And do remember now that - I suppose my little collar that I wore, I got smudgy and I wasn't quite as tidy as what - this boy from Freel
a
nd - though he was an older boy than me - was. Then I can well remember meeting this lad in Oxford, he was sitting on a seat and I recognized he belonged to the - the Merry family and I got in conversation and to his utter amazement I said, I - I know som
e
thing about you. You work for Canon Dover and then I went on about Miss Agatha Phelps and he leaped from this seat and - how did I know all this? And then I - told him all about it. And what Miss Phelps - what Miss Phelps - what Mrs Phelps had told me abo
ut you, that you was a smart lad and all that sort of thing. And he knew - yes, he recognized the whole situation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did he take your place then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, he was at - at Canon }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Dover's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - a place called Ringwood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why had he gone to Cannon Dover's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well he - he was - he didn't leave them, he went from Freeland to Canon Dover's and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had he been sent there for disciplinary reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, no, not at all, he was - he went as a - quite as a good lad a start in life. Yes. But you see I was a different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 calibre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - I was more or less sent - reformed, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How much longer after the housekeeper had told you did you stay with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh about - fortnight after that. Then I left, yes, I left and I came away back to Northleigh. And a
s I say I always remember Mr Phelps - leaving his room, coming - to say goodbye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they give you anything - any little keepsake or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, not at all. No. Just a formal goodbye. That's how I left. And left with impressions of unkindly
 people - always in the background was Mr Phelps - of a man of - sort of angelic ways, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you got back what happened.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When I got back to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Back to Freeland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I went - came back to Northleigh. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You never saw your granny again did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh granny - oh poor granny was - yes, granny died. As I told you, when I left - I should always imagine granny wasn't very well at that time, I think the thought that I was going away distracted her and she was laying on her
 bed. Remember going in say goodbye to granny and - it was almost superhuman strength leaning forward, you know, I shall never see you again, boy, never see you again, you know, that anguished cry. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Which - I suppose it was a way of life to me a youngster, I wasn't distracted about it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I'll see you again granny. And away I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you got back there what job did you get - - was that the one at Witney working for the International Stores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was the first job you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That's my
 first job. That was to be five shillings a week. But previous to making a start there I had - bundle of leaflets to be distributed in Northleigh, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 Freeland}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you get those from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had them brought by an insurance man who wa
s in contact with the manager of the Co-op - of the International Stores and he left them with mother, and I set out with these things and I did distribute them all over the show. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 
scattered them about Northleigh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  Commons because I thought I had to get rid
 of them - I was rather stupid you know, I didn't realize it - and - I got rid of all these leaflets, never from door to door, I did certainly go round the village, Northleigh, Freeland and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14771744\charrsid5840491 
Hanborough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  but you know I - I - it wore me out and I certainly aum
ped a lot of the and when I went to Witney to actually start on a Monday morning the manager wanted to know where the other leaflets were. And he showed me that there was so many it was impossible for me to distribute them round the parishes. Well I didn'
t know anything about that and so I made a start there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did he say when you told him you'd got rid of them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well he just simply - told me how wrong it was. Very dissatisfied and very unhappy about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you find that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that was the - insurance agent told my mother that - this job going. And so of course I - went. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were the hours supposed to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 From - I think it was from eight 'til - any hour. There was no specified time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They didn't give you a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 
But you see I - I - immediately I went there I told them it would be from - say from eight 'til five.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did they say to that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - there was - non-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 committal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  about it but I was - realized - it was on a Tuesday when they sent me out for - to a long errand to - to High Cogges, just outside of Witney and I think I told you about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So anyway you left them at the end of the week didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I left. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you get your five shillings though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had you thought that was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, I did not. But then you see wages was desperately low then and it was accepted. Even so following - leaving there - I - it was - it was on the Thursday, I think I mentio
ned where we had the village club - there was a band and that which was great attraction. And for heavens sake, I must - go to club because I'd saved up a few coppers for that, and I certainly did stay away that day. It was on the Friday when the manager 
t
old me I must - I could go back home. I said, yes, I will, but you give me the money for what I've already earned. He said, you'd better stop 'til the Saturday. And then on the Friday I had to go out to a village - Nayleigh - and I was told that I must ta
k
e the money from certain places before I delivered the goods and I - of course I said yes, I must have the money before I - before I - you have the goods. And - one lady said, I shall certainly report you to the manager. But she did pay up. But then you s
ee, on the Saturday I finished. They desperately wanted me to stay on. But I would not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you got that five shillings what did you do with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well of course I took it home. Yes. Well I suppose I may have had tuppence back or something like that but very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you like the work or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh I - disliked it immensely I - that was - you see, anything in connection with work of that sort was - completely out of my - ideas. And I could never go in for work of that description 
because - I don't think I would ever been capable of - of - managing shop business. My background wasn't such.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get on with the other people who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, they were quite amused - with me especially when I brought the - th
e goods back that I was set out to deliver to other - to a place called High Cogges. You see, I started about quarter past four and got away about half a mile then realized that the time I got to High Cogges and back again it would be very, very late. So 
I returned back and told them that I would never be able to accomplish it in the time at five o'clock. It was about five minutes to five then. And that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did they say then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well the manager said - people are expecting the things and they mus
t be delivered. I said, but not with me. I told you five o'clock I finished. And the next morning those people in the shop, they was highly pleased about it - that I'd taken that attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well because the things prob - possibly that they dare not do but - I dared to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were you supposed to work a full day on Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, full day on Saturday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No half day. We had to work on Saturday, yes, all the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - oh yes, there would have been.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You left there and then did what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 My next job was - bird scaring - that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was for who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 For Masons. Eynsham Hall Estate. That was scaring the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 pheasants}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  and sparrows, all birds away 
from the corn which - young corn at that time - the pheasants would pluck up and - always just - just simply went around the field shouting and making as much noise as you could - had clappers, old tins and - disturbed the birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that a full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
That was a full time job - which of course included Sundays. Because they were just as mischievous on a Sunday as they was on any other day of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't have any time off then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no time off. Except - except I had a - a gi
rl friend - that time - a girl friend on a Sunday which would make a noise and shout about just - perhaps smaller type of way of doing it - so that if the - anyone made enquires - I had been around. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She'd do it for you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. Yes. And rattle the tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was that your first girl friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And she lived at - she lived at a lodge - in the parks, you know. 'Cos of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Her father worked there too did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. And you see, this lodge was - there wouldn't be ano
ther house anywhere near a quarter of a mile away - see - and that's what happened. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I was - I was about fourteen and a half. Yes. Then I remember later on when the corn was fully grown - I had a - two fiel
ds, used to go round and that was sparrows, ravenous then - in clods - starlings you see. You'd drive the birds off and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did you have that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That would be for a few weeks while the corn was ripening. You see. Just a few weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were you paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Six - six shillings for that. Yes. And following that later on - actually I got on - on the - on the farm. That was with the horses, see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The same estate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. But - my wages then was reduced to five shillings.
 You - you see I wasn't working on the Sunday then. That was five shillings a week. That was leading away from Northleigh - it would be two mile away. Remember I had a bicycle which what we called a cushion }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 tyre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - then it was solid tyres and - course that 
- took that - way to my work then was way through the parks and - cycled about two mile. 'Course that would be without bicycle lights - it didn't matter early in the mornings - the way down through the parks and to this - farm. About eight horses, I remem
b
er the first day with the carter - was an elderly man then - with a team of plough horses. Three horses - two in the follow, one at the side. Of course I was leading the furrow horse - it used to follow the furrow all the way down but it was the turn at t
he ends you see. All types of weather - providing the frost wasn't severe the plough could be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 manoeuvred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 and worked, yes, that was my job. Came whatever - I always remember you know as you walked along the dirt clinging to the boots and becoming very heavy and suddenly one foot being released and springing up in the air, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you get on there with the other people, with the team of horses, there'd be another man there wouldn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - well, yes. He was a man, carter was of a - he
 was a religious fellow, you know, followed the chapel trend and - used to whistle away, that will be glory for me and chapel hymns you know. But seldom conversed with me. Oh no, except - after whistling a tune - beautiful hymn - come along boy, touch tho
se horses up a bit, come along - you know. Yes, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have any dealings with Squire Mason when you were employed by him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no, never - I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who was over you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh - the farm bailiff. The man who used to c
ome round with a pony and trap - little - he was probably about between sixty and seventy - little old shorter and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How long did you stay at that job with the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that was about two year. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And then the bailiff said to you one day ------?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, I would have to leave because of - ploughing well it was finished and he'd got no other work for me to do and so I went over onto - onto the building side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you weren't unemployed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, only for a short time I reme
mber - being interested in cricket and being, I suppose, useful to them - the - the clerk that was confidential clerk to Eynsham Hall Estate saw the - the foreman on the building site and I got over onto this - I always remember going with the - bricklaye
r onto a farm which belonged to the estate and we were doing repairs there and - my money was improved to eight shilling a week, that was quite good that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The confidential clerk asked for the job for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes. And that's how I got this job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How had you got to work at the Eynsham Hall Estate in the first place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Ah now. Well I suppose it was someone must - I can't remember exactly - I can well imagine that someone had recommended me a boy could do that. I remember getting the job
. I was most interested in that job because it gave me - great liberty to saunter all round the fields you know and - catch - I remember - in a yard - in the farmyard place you know were mice - oh, all over the show. And I used to catch these little mice 
- catch them at the back of their - their neck you know and - you know. That sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do with them when you caught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well just simply killed 'em. And I had a sheet over - where they put underneath the - and then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 lifted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  the sheet up quick and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Pounce on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You preferred that to working with the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh well you see - working with the horses was quite a - a big thing to me. I was used to of course cattle, horses, yes. Now I always remember the firs
t time going into the stable - almost overcome with - ammonia from - from the horses you know, yes. And - my eyes used to water and - putting the harness on, yes. You know, that was quite a game - I didn't know much about that. But soon learnt. And the ri
d
e on the horses back, you know, to the field, the one was going to plough, and - sometimes quite fresh and frisky you know. But they even so I didn't mind that because I say I'd been used to riding - donkeys and horses in the field so I didn't mind one bi
t but - the cold - yes. Oh yes, bitterly cold first thing in the morning you know - after leaving the stables.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were your hours there when you were on the carting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 From - supposed to be down there at seven o'clock in the morning and work 'ti
l five o'clock 'cos one got in early with the horses - about four o'clock 'cos you got to - they got to be fed and - and everything prepared, you know, for morning. That sort of thing. And - always remember - coming in with he horses, having a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14630764\charrsid5840491 look}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  round i
n the managers for stray egg because hens used to lay very - the other side of the distance you see a cowman had a - a house near there and he looked after the pigs and - and the - chicken and if there was an egg going well of course I could always swallo
w that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Eat it raw would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes, yes, that was, yes, easily yes, swallow an egg. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And when you went into the building work did you keep on with that until the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You didn't have another job in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did you feel about the building work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Well the building work was mixing up the - mortar or concrete for the - for the bricklayer and - always remember in the early stages I - probably made a mess of thi
ngs but he learn - the bricklayer learned me quite quickly. Used to curse me and I thought what a horrible man he was. But - afterwards I realized he was quite a decent fellow. Then - as I conversed with him he was an interesting type of fellow because he
 - he was interested in - in what I used to talk about. Use to talk about the farmer on this estate and how he was making his money and whether he was going to - to use it properly and he used to say, well - what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The farmer was who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The farmer - the farmer on this estate - a farmer named }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 Buckingham}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So you weren't on Eynsham Hall estate when you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was on Eynsham Hall Estate and this was a farm belonging to Eynsham Hall estate which - which let out to the farmer and
 of course we was doing repairs on this estate for the farmer and - as I say, my - my bricklayer I was with - 'course I wasn't doing things right. And he was always trying to learn me what to do right and he got very angry. But as time went an I found him
 
quite a nice type of man. And he was interested in the things I used to talk about. And - things worked round in regard to the farmer - how he worked his land and the money he was making from it. Then he would talk to this farmer what I'd already said. An
d
 the farmer said, lad, he said, you seem to talk a bit of sense, you must get on in life. I said, well would you - could you give me a better job than I've got - I've got now? No, he said, I couldn't give you nothing - as much money as you're earning now.
 
And I said, why? Well, he said, because, he said, you wouldn't be worth it. Well, I said, you went me to work for you and I said you give me - you would pay me money just for the work I was doing but would you - you wouldn't employ me if you wasn't making
 
a profit out of me. Would you keep hold of the profits you made out of me and give me none back? He said, by, he said, you talk without any sense. You're work he said, I'd pay you for what you do. And - my mate - he told me - that - he says, yes, he says,
 that's all right what you says Bill, he said, but things don't work out that way. And my line of reasoning wasn't the line of reasoning of a - of the farmer. But it was the line of reasoning of the - of man I was working with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The bricklayer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think the bricklayer had thought this out for himself before or was he convinced by your argument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I don't think so because I think he must have had a kind of talk which followed much along the same lines as mine because I do remem
ber the farmer talking to me quite a lot after that. And he says, boy, he says, you ought to have another job. He says, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you think the bricklayer was interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think so. Yes, I think he was. Because you see - my line
 of reasoning as a youngster was - just a - simple thoughts that captured his ideas and also the farmers because - the bricklayer told me about what the farmer was likely to do. He - he would soon be leaving the farm and he would use - he would use things
 on the - on the farm to sow - grow form the land a good crop of corn and then leave it then the next man that took on the land would be in poor condition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In that job you gave the money to your mother as you had in the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And she gave you some back did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well I doubt whether it'd be a shilling. Perhaps sixpence anything but I - yes, probably about sixpence you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You joined up in what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Ah - that would be what - 19 - the beginning of war - 19
14. I can remember the meeting at the - at the - the church - near the church - inappropriate place I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 should}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
 have thought really but that happened and Mr Mason himself held the meeting. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Up until the first world war did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you feel at that time that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I - I knew very definitely that - the interest of - of the - people in - in position of a - of authority more or less - no con
ception of what could be - truth or justice from that point of view - law applied - strictly law applied, even so I remember at an early date and that was before actual war, I was no age then, we did - I was at a meeting when - could a man be honest in bu
s
iness? That was most interested in and even so at that time I said, no. Everyone agreed that one could be honest in business. But I went through this whole question again as regards - if I was employed by a farmer and I was sixty-five - then the profits t
h
at had accrued during that period, had I been allocated - my portion for labour or had I merely been paid and existing wage, which was about eleven shillings at that time, was that fair - and was the honest? And - they said well that was a - understood wa
ge - you paid your wage and you paid - and a farmer or whoever was a paying you was honest in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When was this meeting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That was a meeting before 1914 - before the war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This discussion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This discussion, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 How did it come up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That come about - in a school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 At school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well that was the ordinary - that was a meeting called for the parishioners, see. As a debate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And this was the topic of the debate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This was the topic. But - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who organized these meetings then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I think the - Mr Gardner - that was the confidential clerk and secretary, Eynsham Hall then - he was on the parish council then and - of course you see I was what - about ; between seventeen and eighteen then. And I did attend this meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you spoke did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And I spoke. Then I got up and in - in my way - talking at that time of day -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You said much what you've been saying to day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, what I've been saying to you, yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you also feel there were divisions of interest among the working people themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes, at that - of course that happened to people - yes. I wouldn't think so much - the division came about in regard to the work but the division came in the status of life, in a sense 
that - you belonged to the - the - the chapel and your life was made up life be staid and purposeful and - in a g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
nial type of way you emit the other fellow or lady or person that was of a - the rough and tumble type and of course you conversed in a normal
 way but - you never mixed in that way. You may be persuasive in the sense that you tried to persuade me over to - to the church or chapel as the case may be, but - there was that difference in the life of the people. There was quite people that had diffe
rent jobs - and you - you found your company - you found your company in the village - in the way that was - you - were used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was there a difference between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, yes, yes, you see, you got the stonemason
, you got the craftsmen, they more or less belonged to a clique you know, more or less assembled together. You see, the same thing would apply in a public house, be a room set aside for - for the elite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The elite would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would be - any - anyone in clerical work - couldn't be many. But there'd be the farmers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the stonemason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The stonemason, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 He's go in with the elite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What about the bricklayer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The bricklayer - he - he'd find his place more or less in the normal public house side. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life or had it been formed already do you think when you started work?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When I started - let's say when I went with the b
ricklayer or even early age with the - on the - on the farm, I think I was changing quite a lot. I think what had happened with me was - that I'd read a lot, you know, and stumbled more or less into - stumbled more or less into a different of - of thinkin
g.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Had this happened before you started work - before you went into service and then on the farm - or during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - I suppose what - what moved me quite a lot was going away in the first place to the Phelps's and thinking quite a lot ab
out things and even so reading even then quite a lot. I think I read a paper named the Tribune, a daily paper - wasn't socialist paper but it gave me quite a lot to think about. And - books - I had read - putting two and two together I thought there was s
omething very wrong. And as I - and as I thought more about these sort of things the more I became troubled in mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 That shoemaker who first interested you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you continue to see him - when did you stop associating with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well in the village saw him quite a lot. I remember the first occasion was - going to the village well - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you continue seeing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491  him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 - after you got back from the Phelps's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. I - no, I don't think - I saw much of him but - it was a starti
ng point and - a person that I could never eradicate from my mind. The very thought that he'd told me never to sell my labour cheaply was sufficient - was sufficient to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 instil}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  in my mind something which seemed to live on after that and the more I thought a
bout it the more I became - perplexed. That was a thought that sank very deeply in my mind because I thought I was worth something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were working after you came back from the Phelps's did you stay at home all the time - you lived at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, I stayed at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Would you say that when you started to work full time that it changed your relationship with your brothers at 11?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I think so, because you see when I came back I always remember bringing a little miniature type o
f football back and - going to the - into the big open field playing football - I'd learned quite a lot about the arts of football and the - Sandhurst youngsters, you know and suchlike, and they thought I was quite and expert at dribbling the ball and als
o - my - my way of talking was quite different because you see I - unconsciously I'd picked up quite a bit of the - Phelps's language and I know they mimicked me quite a lot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I didn't mind a bit. And - yes, that was - a
nd, you know, they did, yes, they mimicked me quite a lot. And - come - let's go back to the old oak tree, well the old oak tree was - as I told you, in the field - in the open field you know and - shall we have a - shall we have another lesson in - the o
ld oak tree, and I think this was kind of taking it out of me a bit. I'd say, I don't mind if we do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Another lesson about what would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Well - 'cos this was rather silly I suppose but I always remember that this old oak tree was a king of t
rees. This was a tree - that - when I was three and this was the tree that I used to spend - a lot of time under and I'd tell other kids this was the king of trees and this tree had been there since the world began - that silly type of thing you know. And
 
where all the - all the starlings flit down to feed and they did - this old tree - 'cos it was alone in the field and the starlings used to congregate there and always remember these starlings when the cattle - used to move about in the mornings you know 
- they'd flit down and follow the tread of the cattle you know and pick up the insects that sort of thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 
And it - it did happen that way and I used to - they - they were seeing it for themselves and - they always - when dusk came would come out from the -
 from some hole in the tree, you know, which I never discovered but they did and flit away to the farm you know and pick up the mouse they - this story they used to believe. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Yes. But that - that was going back to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were Ivy and Winifred still alive when you came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They'd died before had they
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh yes, yes, because you see that was in earlier times. Yes. Yes. 'Cos Ivy - yes. And yet I told you I think - I believe I did - and the only time that I used to scurry back and I never le
ft her really out of eyesight but cattle forever curious you know, they would - they would work up towards the pram and I used to hurry back fast and - before they got to close they - already found the - you heard - have you heard cattle when they snortin
g
 - ah yes, and I'd cheep along, they'd be unaware and get near then suddenly if you jump up cattle go away - Kicking - frantic you know and away went - whether they were in a playful mood or not I don't know, but they did. And scuttle across the field. An
d I doubt if far - if I'd ever been caught, been trouble because, you see, some - some of the cows may be heavy, you know, at that time and - be the wrong thing to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were working when you came back did you go to church or chapel or Sunday school at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. Because Freeland - I - I'd forsaken and Northleigh church was Reverend Bovey Scott - never - no, I never went - yes, occasionally I went, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you take an interest in politics at that time when you working on Eynsham Hall Estate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes, even then - yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What were your views on political parties at that time - did you support a particular party then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I - I don't think - in the early stage I had any idea of politics in that sense. To understand - except for - leaflets that would - and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 this's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  - I think in the early stage the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 leaflets}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  I had - expending the Labour idea - ideas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Where did you get those leaflets from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They were - they were taken - they were brought round or sent round at some election time. And - yes, I did try to - to read out of }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 curiosity}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  you see, but even before you see, I had become interested in - in life and that appealed to me the most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. So I thought quite a lot about that and became quite concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember when you first voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Hardly. No. No. No, I don't think I do. No. But of course it'd he after the war you see. When my - when my mind was first firmly made up. So that was easy really. I'd already become confirmed in my belief.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 In that period up to the first world war were you a member of any party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember - besides distributing the leaflets - do you remember doing any other political work - canvassing or talking to people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. Oh I - I - I don't think I was a - the person capable of - of expanding anything in that sense, except amongst my own pals. But to meet someone of a - of more advanced -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, my own friends. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you try and persuade them to vote for certain candidates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You had a Labour candidate then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I - no, not at that time - Liberal. No at that time - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 So these Labour leaflets you distributed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Who were they for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
I think they must have come from - I should - I can't imagine where they came from. They could have come I think possibly from Oxford. Could have been Ruskin college that would do a thing of that sort but there certainly were leaflets then distributed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What was the purpose of the leaflets - to get people to vote for somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 For general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, I should think so but - I'm rather hazy about that. All I do remember was that there were leaflets - of that nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Was it after the war or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After the war - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Do you remember before the end of the war feeling under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Before the war? Oh that - the pressu
re then was intense - I mean, a question the, it was between the Conservatives and the Liberals. - And the Liberals was the - supposed to be a tendency towards the left more than the right and the - you wouldn't divulge this to who you were going to vote 
for. You wouldn\rquote 
t expand any ideas of - that you was a Liberal. Even if - you'd lose your job probably - at least that was the thought upper most in - in one's mind. I do remember that quite well. That - even so that was before 1914 as a kid I can remember 
my people always - the way they used to talk it was never - let who you're going to vote for. Mind your own business. But if you was holding Conservative you - you would make that well known. That was quite a different thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you were working when you got back from the Phelps's did you continue with your cricket club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were still an organizer in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I was - worked hard for that because we had the second - we had - what - you know - the second eleven. That was
 a dash all over the village to the - to pick up the team for the Saturday you see because we had to - bat - paddle our own canoe. There - was the club already in - in - in being and that was O.K. but we had to work for ourselves. It's very difficult to -
 
to organize and get together but we did. I - I remember I had to - two more that was very keen and enthusiastic about it. Of course we had to go to East end of village which was long way. Then we - we did used to manage and - and got a formation of a - of
 a team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And you carried on with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 And we carried on with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 After the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Up to the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any other things that you did - things that you hadn't done in the earlier time - did you take up - any other interests o
r hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No, it was cricket and football. Very keen on sport - anything appertaining to sport. Then you could always bet I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you go out in the evenings - enjoying yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, well you see, in the evenings before 19 say
 14 - we'd go out - bird catching, that was with nets. You each side - you go - each side of the hedges you know and bash the hedges and collect these - well I don't like to think about it too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you make any new friends - you said you had this girlfriend - did she last long - did you have a lot of girlfriends at that time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, not really. You see, because that time I wasn't particularly interested in girls - I don't think at any stage of my - early life that I was interested in girls. I'm
 not conceited - I think they - thinking back I believe they was some interest in me, for what reason I can't imagine but this girl I remember at Eynsham Hall Estate she must have been interested in me - I don't know why but - yes, and I was interested fo
r
 a short time - I must have been tremendously interested because I went - used to go down and linger round about the place. That went on for about a week or a fortnight. But after that I couldn't have cared less. It just simply drifted away and - I gave i
t no more thought. That was my make-up I think then. I got enthralled with a girl for a time but that was - gone in a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 These boys and the girl, were they children you'd known all your life or did you meet new friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh yes, 'cos I use
d to - you see I drift - well I suppose used to go out to Witney then which was quite a - quite out of the - out of life you know because Witney was - a town. Yes I used to get away to Witney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you meet new people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I met new people there and new girls there - factory girls you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did they seem different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No, no not much because they - they'd broad dialect you know and - they were more - those girls worked in the factory they a wider expense of life than village girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever bring your friends home - girlfriends or boyfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Oh no. No. My mother - as I know now was very aware of my mixing with different people, and always her talk would be of - of girls you know and - not get mixed up with bad company
. I didn't want bad company really meant then. My mind wasn't - wasn't thought in a way to that extent - I didn't - no I never had any talk of that but apparently my mother had. She was very careful type of woman - with best intentions I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She didn't ask to meet your girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did she like to know who you were going around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 She definitely liked to know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 But she didn't want to meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. No. No, you see - there again - as far as my mother was conc
erned - her mind was obsessed all the time with - managing from day to day and - quick ideas of - of management and control. Very intelligent mind but - so enthralled with everything that was happening to - not with me - but sort - the other brothers as w
ell you know. As well, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
No. Time - time was no option - object, it was come day, go day, you got up in the morning and you went away and no one worried about you because they'd no cause to worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were friendly with this confidential clerk weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Were there any other special friends of your won sex that you had at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, there was schoolmaster. The schoolmaster. He was man from - he came from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The Northleigh schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 The - no, this is - this had changed hands. We are dealing now with a little later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 This is dealing with up to the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Oh I see. Oh yes. No, well then of course that again was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You were friendly with the confidential clerk at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes, that's true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Did you ever have any other particular close friends that you talked to and did things with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No - up to 1914 - no, I couldn't think of no one really in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12665509\charrsid5840491 particular.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491  A
t that I suppose I was - all - in regard to sport you see - you can - you can hardly think this because - perhaps appeared to be of a different nature but - I could - got tremendous kick out of life anything in - in sport but I had two minds. My - one min
d
 was absorbed with this - way of life of trying to see something different and what ought to be - and the lie that I'd lived under I'd already got formation of this idea that - it was a tremendous lie and - my mother - was - most loving type of person but
 
you se my mother had lived a lie and my father lived a lie and this already obsessed my mind that this was altogether wrong. And a life that should be completely to what I'd known it. The world was - full of - the shops was loaded with everything, there w
a
s good but always - out of reach and that was wrong and - I'd no idea how - how it came about or why it should be that way but - I was trying to find out - and I could never - I didn't find out but it was - in my little way of talk was - wrong. - So you s
e
e, I was very confused. And in between, these ideas and my mixture of football and cricket - you see - that I never much time to - to know - whether it was flights of fancy and nothing remains - static you see. And it was on the move all the time. And so 
I
 suppose really - up to the 1914 war - things was developing in a contra - contrary type of way, never with any - gradual sort of process of learning you know Wild random thoughts and then of course the war came and - it - became completely - different, y
es.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 When you came back after the war you went to Oxford did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 
Ah - oh yes. Well, yes, you see that - coming back was the completely - out of this world 'cos I think I - well I think we did - we went through that I believe last time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 I wasn't to know the actual jobs you've done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 You came back to Oxford and did you start working for the council as a pavier straight away in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 What did you do first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5247875 WB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 No. That was the job of - of doing nothing rea
lly, because you see I was - I was a millionaire, I'd got about - what - nearly seventy pounds in whatever you call that after - the war - bounty, you know, the money that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14629003 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11471752\charrsid5840491 They gave soldiers money?
